title: deep fried apple fritters
directions: Mix egg and milk.
Add other ingredients, except apples.
Mix well.
Dip sliced or quartered apples into batter and fry until golden brown.

title: quick-n-easy red velvet cake
directions: Mix cake mix by directions.
Add food coloring to tint red. Bake as per directions on box.
When cake is cool, mix confectioners sugar and cream cheese and spread on cake. Delicious; tastes like store bought.

title: never fail fudge
directions: Combine butter, sugar and milk; bring to a boil.
Boil 5 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients, except nuts.
Beat until well mixed.
Add nuts.
Spoon into buttered pan. Cool until firm; then cut.
Makes 5 lbs.

title: chocolate wreath balls
directions: Mix peanut butter, confectioners sugar, oleo and graham cracker crumbs and roll into small balls.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in top of a double boiler.
Dip balls and place on wax paper to cool.

title: goofy cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch pan and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: aunt ella's pumpkin bread
directions: You will need 3 or 4 (1 pound) coffee cans with lids to store after
baking
(freezes
well).
Mix
and bake in coffee cans. Fill 1/2 full and bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: pork chops southern style
directions: Peel and quarter enough potatoes to cover the bottom of Dutch oven. Cover with water and boil until tender. Pour most of water off. Add 3 cans sauerkraut and 2 pounds Polish sausage, cut in 2 to 3-inch pieces. Heat and serve. This is easy, quick and serves a bunch.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Save broth.
Remove chicken from bones and cut into bite-size pieces.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: elouise's pickled okra
directions: Wash, drain and trim ends of okra.
Pack okra firmly into jars.
Put garlic bud, hot pepper and dill seed in each jar. Bring to boil water, salt and vinegar.
Cover okra with hot brine; adjust lids.
Process in boiling water bath for 10 minutes.

title: mary lou's chicken casserole
directions: Mix all together and put into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Mix ingredients and form into small balls.
Add no salt. Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Bake cake (by directions) in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool in pan. Cook until thickened, milk, flour, oleo, sugar, oil and vanilla. Let cool and pour over strawberries.
Refrigerate.
It is better next day.

title: wine pecan cheese balls
directions: Mix together all the ingredients, except the pecans.
Form into 2 balls or 1 log roll.
Roll in
the pecans.
Wrap and chill for up to a week.
Serve with Ritz crackers or other butter type crackers.

title: stuffed french bread
directions: Melt butter and add altogether.
Spread on sliced French bread.
Wrap in foil.
Heat until cheese melts.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine ingredients in order as listed.
Bake in greased skillet.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hamburger rice pie
directions: Mix beef, bread crumbs, onion, green pepper, seasoning and 1/2 can tomato sauce. Spread in greased 9-inch pie pan, pushing mixture to sides of pan to form an edge. Mix rice, cheese, and remaining 1 1/2 cans tomato sauce. Place in meat shell. Bake in moderate 350 oven 30-35 minutes or until meat is done. Cut into six pie shaped pieces. Serve with green vegetable.

title: poff's split pea and ham soup
directions: Bring 5 cups of water to boil.
Add both packages of soup mix. Cover and simmer 1/2 hour.
Add chicken broth.
Simmer for another 1/2 hour.
Add carrots and onion.
Add pepper, brown sugar and wine.
Simmer for another 2 hours uncovered.
Add ham and 1 1/2 seasoning packets (from mix) about 10 minutes before end of cooking.

title: chocolate cookie sheet cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt.
In saucepan, mix butter, oil, cocoa and water.
Bring to a boil and add to dry. Beat well. Dissolve soda in buttermilk (it will turn frothy).
Add to mix with eggs and vanilla. Beat well. Pour in a 10 x 15-inch pan. Bake at 400° (or 350°) for 20 minutes.

title: cheerios treats(makes about 24)
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Microwave margarine or spread in large bowl on High for 45 seconds or until melted. Add marshmallows.
Toss to coat with margarine or spread.
Microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes or until smooth when stirred, stirring after 45 seconds. Stir in peanut butter.
Immediately add cereal. Mix lightly until well coated.
Using greased spatula or wax paper, press mixture into pan.
Cool. Cut into squares.

title: artichoke heart dip
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, until golden brown.
Serve with raw vegetables, chips or crackers.

title: quick corn relish
directions: Drain liquid from corn; reserve 1/2 cup. Combine corn, onion, green pepper and pimiento in a large bowl. In a small saucepan, combine the corn liquid and the balance of ingredients and bring to the boil. Pour over vegetables. Cool. Cover and refrigerate overnight, stirring occasionally. Makes 5 cups.

title: fancy chicken
directions: Combine stuffing, cheese and parsley.
Dip chicken pieces in melted butter, then roll in stuffing mix.
Arrange, skin side up, on large shallow baking pan.
Don't crowd.
Sprinkle with remaining butter and crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Don't turn.

title: peach ice cream
directions: Combine half of peaches and 1/4 cup milk in container of an electric blender.
Process until smooth.
Transfer to a medium bowl and repeat procedure with remaining peaches and 1/4 cup milk. Set aside.
Combine remaining 2 1/2 cups milk and next 3 ingredients in a heavy saucepan.
Cook over medium heat for 8 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and stir in peach mixture and nectar.
Pour mixture into freezer container of a 4-quart hand turned or electric freezer.
Freeze mixture according to manufacturer's instructions.
Pack freezer with additional ice and rock salt.
Let stand 1 hour before serving. Yields 1 gallon.

title: homer's chili
directions: Mix all together.
Cook slowly for hours.

title: bubble bread
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Place frozen rolls around sides and bottom of pan.

Mix next 5 ingredients and spread over rolls. Pour melted butter over rolls and place on cabinet overnight. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes; let stand 10 - 15 minutes before turning out and serving.

title: hobo bread
directions: You will need 3 (1 pound) coffee cans.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill and serve on lettuce leaves.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix well and bake at 350° until top starts to brown.

title: ritz cracker dessert
directions: Beat egg whites and other ingredients except crackers.
Fold in crackers last.
Grease 9 x 10-inch pan.
Pat the mixture into pan.
Bake 25 minutes in 350° oven or until lightly brown.
Cool well.

title: veggie squares
directions: Pat dough into a jelly roll pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°. Let cool.
Mix cream cheese, mayo and dressing.
Spread over cooled crust.
Top with shaved veggies.

title: easy chicken marsala
directions: Trim excess fat from chicken cutlets.
Place between 2 pieces of clear wrap.
Pound with flat side of meat tenderizer.
Combine flour, parsley and pepper on plate.
Coat chicken.
Heat butter in large skillet over medium heat.
Saute flour coated chicken in skillet until lightly browned.
Move chicken to one side of pan. Pour chicken bouillon and wine into pan.
Mix with remaining butter.
Arrange chicken in a single layer in wine sauce.
Cover with lid and simmer, turning chicken occasionally for 10 to 30 minutes.
It gets more tasty and tender the longer it cooks.
Serve with egg noodles and drizzle wine sauce over the chicken.

title: honey apple cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in honey.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in sour cream. Mix and sift flour, baking soda, salt and spices; stir in and blend well.
Stir in apples.
Drop by teaspoon 3 inches apart on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes or until edges are brown.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: carrot cake
directions: Blend oil and sugar.
Add carrots.
Add eggs, beaten in one at a time.
Sift flour.
Add baking soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Add flour mixture to carrot mixture.
Add nuts and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.
Makes 3 layers or 1 tube pan.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream together margarine and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Sift flour and soda together and add to creamed mixture.
Then add crushed potato chips and butterscotch morsels. Drop by teaspoon on a greased cookie sheet about 2 inches apart. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Makes approximately 3 dozen cookies.

title: paper cup frozen salad
directions: Combine sour cream, lemon juice, sugar, salt, pineapple, banana pieces and enough red food color to give a pink tint. Lightly fold in nuts and Bing cherries.
Spoon into fluted paper muffin cups (large size) which have been placed in 3-inch muffin cup pans.
Freeze.
Cover with plastic wrap and store in freezer. Remove from freezer 15 minutes before serving.
Peel off cup and place on salad greens.
Makes 12 cups.

title: hamburger steak
directions: Pat hamburger out on floured board, cut into squares.
Flour sides.
Brown in butter.
Pour 1 can of onion soup over steak and let simmer for 1 hour.

title: watermelon rind pickles
directions: Use on crackers or finger sandwiches.

title: spanish chicken and rice
directions: Cut chicken in serving pieces and brown in oil.
Place chicken in baking dish.
In pan, cook garlic, green pepper and onion (all chopped) until onion is golden.
Add tomatoes.
Add to the chicken in casserole and add chicken broth.
Add salt to taste, saffron and rice.
Cover casserole and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes, or until rice is tender.
Serves 4.
Chicken broth should be heated before adding to casserole.

title: rum balls
directions: Mix softened butter.
Add sifted sugar, then all other ingredients and mix well.
Put into refrigerator to harden a little.
Roll into small balls and ice with chocolate icing or roll in chocolate sprinkles or coconut.

title: chicken scallop
directions: Melt margarine; blend in flour and salt.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until mix is smooth and bubbly.
Stir in broth.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute; cool. Add eggs.
Prepare stuffing according to directions (less water is desirable).
Spread stuffing in 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Top with chicken and pour sauce over top.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes. Serve with sauce.

title: chicken chalupas
directions: Combine cheeses; reserve half.
Divide green onions into two equal portions.
Combine half cheese, half onions, all soup, chilies, sour cream and olives.
Set aside 1 1/2 cups for topping. Add chicken to remainder for filling.
Put filling in tortillas and roll.
Place seam down on lightly oiled baking dish.
Arrange in a single layer.
May need 2 dishes.
Spread reserved topping (soup mix) over tortillas.
Cover with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake uncovered 45 minutes at 350°.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.
Good made with leftover beef or pork.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: In a saucepan, combine brown sugar, salt and cider.
Mix well. Tie whole spices in a small piece of cheesecloth; add to cider with nutmeg.
Over medium heat, bring cider to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Remove spices.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Unroll crescent roll dough.
Separate into 2 rectangles. Press onto bottom and up sides of 11 x 17-inch baking pan, sealing perforations.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes or until light brown.
Cool to room temperature.

title: new mexico aztec platter
directions: Use 10 to 12-inch glass pie plate or similar shallow round plate.
For layer 1, mix refried beans and taco seasoning.
Spread onto plate, not quite to edge.

title: no bake cheesecake squares
directions: Combine crust mixture with sugar and butter as directed on package; press firmly into bottom of an 8 or 9-inch square pan. Prepare filling mix with milk as directed on the package.
Pour over crust.
Refrigerate at least one hour.
Cut into squares. Garnish with fruit, nuts, or drizzle with melted semi-sweet chocolate, if desired.
Makes 9 servings.

title: pork chop skillet meal
directions: Brown pork chops in a large skillet.
Put a slice of onion on top, then a pepper ring.
Put a tablespoon of rice in each pepper ring.
Pour the tomatoes around the pork chops.
Cover and simmer for about 30 to 40 minutes, or until chops are tender.

title: caramel nut pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and brown sugar.
Gradually add white sugar and continue creaming.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Combine baking powder, salt and flour.
Add shortening with milk to creamed mixture, beginning and ending with flour.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Blend well.
Pour into well greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Let cool 15 minutes before removing from pan.

title: cranberry swirl coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add eggs, baking powder, baking soda, flour, salt, sour cream and almond flavoring, blending well.
Layer half of the batter in a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Spread half of the cranberry sauce and sprinkle half of the nuts on top.
Add remaining batter and top with the rest of the cranberry sauce and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes. Cool and remove from pan.
Drizzle with glaze made by combining:

title: pumpkin bread to share
directions: Combine
all
dry
ingredients.
Add oil, eggs, pumpkin and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add pecans.
Divide batter into three parts and
bake
in greased and floured 1 pound coffee cans at 350° for 1 hour.
Let cool slightly and carefully remove from cans; place on wire racks to cool.

title: cowboy coffee cake
directions: Overlap biscuits in 8 or 9-inch cake pan in a spiral fashion. Combine oil, sugar, nuts and cinnamon.
Spread over biscuits. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: layered chili casserole
directions: Combine beef, onion and garlic in a large skillet.
Cook until meat is browned.
Drain.
Now combine meat mixture, sauce, water and seasonings in a medium sized bowl.
Stir well.
Place half of meat mixture in lightly greased 2-quart casserole.
Top with chips.
Repeat layers.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Uncover.
Bake 5 minutes longer.
Top with shredded lettuce.

title: spice cake
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Next, beat egg yolks until light with sugar and vanilla.
Mix with dates, nuts and flour.
Fold in with egg whites.
Bake in greased and floured loaf pan for 1 hour or longer at 300° to 325°.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Melt oleo over low heat.
Remove from heat.
Add brown sugar and stir until well blended.
Cool.
Stir in eggs.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt and stir into the other mixture. Add flavoring and nuts.
Spread in a well-greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake until when touched lightly with only a slight imprint remains.
Cut into bars when still warm.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and onion dip.
Spread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Brown ground beef; drain.
Add taco mix and spread evenly over cheese mixture.
Next layer on top the tomatoes, lettuce, onion and cheese.
Chill.
Let sit at room temperature 15 to 20 minutes before serving.
Serve with chips.

title: fried apples(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Melt the butter in a large, heavy skillet.
Add the remaining ingredients and cook over medium-low heat, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
As they cook, turn the apples carefully with a spatula without breaking them.

title: my peanut butter pie
directions: In medium bowl, combine the confectioners sugar and peanut butter.
Mix to a crumbly consistency (like a streusel) and remove about 1/2 cup of mixture.
Cover and set aside for later use. Pour the remaining mixture evenly over the pie crust.
Make the pudding according to the package directions.
Pour the pudding over the crumb layer, then cover and refrigerate overnight. Before serving, cover with whipped topping and top with the reserved peanut butter mixture.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease pan.
Sprinkle coconut and pecans.
Mix cake mix according to directions, pour over coconut and pecans.
Mix cream cheese, oleo and powdered sugar.
Drop by spoonfuls on top.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: bacon and cheese spread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve on Ritz crackers.
Keeps for days in the refrigerator.

title: strawberry cheese salad
directions: First Layer:
Dissolve 1 (6 ounce) box Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Add drained strawberries, drained pineapple and bananas and pour into an 8-inch square pan/dish.
Chill until set.

title: mary's pancakes
directions: Mix and bake and top with butter and your favorite syrup or preserves or honey.

title: grandma's tomato pudding
directions: Begin 1 1/2 hours before serving time.
Heat tomatoes to boiling in a 3-quart saucepan, stirring constantly.
Reduce to low heat, cover and simmer until tomatoes are soft, about 10 minutes. Uncover and cook 15 minutes longer, stirring (until slightly thickened).

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: Dissolve pudding with milk.
Add Cool Whip.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer as follows:
graham crackers, 1/2 pudding mixture, graham crackers, 1/2 pudding mixture and graham crackers.
Chill 2 hours.
Frost.
Chill 24 hours.

title: hot turkey sandwich
directions: On individual dishes, place stuffing, turkey and cheese.
Put in microwave to melt cheese.
Serve with Thousand Island dressing and bacon chips.
Makes 2 sandwiches.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients and spread in pan.
Bake until golden brown, 25 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: 3 bean and beef soup
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and garlic; drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat eggs; add oil, water and pumpkin.
Sift dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture.
One cup raisins, currants or nuts may be added here.
Fill greased baking pans 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tester comes out clean.
Time depends on size of baking pan used.

title: fajitas
directions: Cut chicken thighs in 4 slices.
Set aside in a large bowl with cover.
Melt butter in 2-quart sauce pan.
Put onions, Season-All and garlic powder in hot butter.
Saute.
Pour vinegar and lemon juice over onion mixture.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over sliced chicken.
Cover and let marinate in refrigerator at least 2 hours. Place chicken on grill and cook to doneness.
Serve on flour shells with guacamole.
Good side dishes are pinto beans and Spanish rice.

title: cooked dressing
directions: Stir together dry ingredients.
Add eggs, margarine, milk and vinegar.
Stir and cook until mixture begins to thicken.
Makes 1 cup.
Great for potato salad!

title: lemon angel roll
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line a 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan with foil, extending foil 1-inch over ends.
Prepare cake mix as directed.
Spread batter evenly into pan.
Bake about 30 minutes. Immediately turn onto a tea towel that has been sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Beginning at narrow end, roll up cake and towel, jelly roll fashion.
Cool.
Mix milk, lemon juice and rind.
Mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Unroll cake.
Spread with half of the filling.
Reroll.
Place on serving plate, seam side down.
Spread remaining filling over roll.
Garnish with coconut.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve with a colorful assortment of fresh fruits.

title: eight layer mexican dip
directions: Mix refried beans and bean dip together.
Spread the mixture into bottom of a pan.
Mix taco seasoning, sour cream and mayonnaise together and spread this layer over beans.
The guacamole is the next layer.
If you wish, top with jalapeno peppers.
Combine Jack and Cheddar cheeses.
Evenly spread this mixture over guacamole.
Layer with one chopped tomato, olives and green onions.
Serve with tortilla chips and salsa.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Chop artichoke hearts up fine.
Mix well with other ingredients.
Sprinkle some Parmesan on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Dip with crackers or veggies.

title: steak and parmesan salad
directions: Place steak and 1/2 cup of the dressing in sealable plastic bag and marinate in the refrigerator for 30 minutes.
Remove steak from marinade; discard marinade.
Grill or broil steak 5 to 10 minutes on each side or until cooked through.
Cut steak across the grain into slices.
Toss greens with tomatoes, squash and remaining 1/2 cup of dressing.
Place on serving platter.
Top with steak slices, sprinkle with cheese.

title: marinated pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over pork chops. Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours.
Remove from refrigerator.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Bake in marinade, covered, at 325° for 1 hour or until a meat thermometer registers 160°.
Yields 6 servings.

title: stir-fry green beans
directions: Heat oil in wok and add first three ingredients.
Stir-fry 2 minutes on high and then add soy sauce and water.
Cook covered for 3-5 more minutes, or untilo greens are done.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together and add shortening, cutting in until size of a pea.
Add milk to make a soft dough. Place on waxed paper or a board, kneading lightly for 15 seconds, using very little flour on board.
Roll out dough 1/2-inch to 3/4-inch thick.
Cut out biscuits with a cookie cutter.
Grease baking sheet or pan and place biscuits on.
Put in a hot oven (450°) for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 14 (2-inch) biscuits.

title: dan's favorite chip dip
directions: Let cream cheese soften.
Mix with mixer to make smooth and creamy.
Add milk, a little at a time, until desired consistency. Season with garlic salt to taste.

title: strawberry smoothie fat-free spread
directions: In a medium bowl, combine all ingredients.
Whisk until smooth.
Keep refrigerated.
Use as a spread on toast, bagels, muffins or crackers.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly the shortening, peanut butter, granulated sugar, brown sugar and egg.
Blend in flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Cover and chill.

title: spinach salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together as a tossed salad.

title: lasagna
directions: Beat 2 eggs and mix into cottage cheese.
Set aside.

title: no bake banana split cake
directions: Combine crumbs, 1 1/2 sticks margarine and sugar.
Pack in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 8 minutes at 350°.
Beat eggs, 1 stick margarine and powdered sugar until light and fluffy.
Spread over crumb mixture.
Add layer of sliced bananas, sprinkled with lemon juice.
Add layer of crushed pineapple.
Top with Cool Whip, sprinkled with chopped nuts and cherries.
Cool in refrigerator for at least 12 hours or can be frozen.

title: pecan pie(club member: brad smith)
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Put mixture into a pie shell. Bake at 350° until firm and brown.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt margarine and toss with dressing.
Mix 3/4 dressing with all the ingredients.
Place in greased 13 x 2 x 9-inch dish. Sprinkle 1/4 dressing on top.
Cook at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: celebration salad
directions: Drain pears, reserving 1 tablespoon liquid.
Combine reserved liquid, yogurt, dressing and ginger.
Toss half of the dressing with lettuce.
Place lettuce on serving dish; sprinkle with wheat germ.
Arrange pears and prunes over lettuce.
Drizzle with remaining dressing.
Serves 4.

title: chewies
directions: Turn oven to 400°.
Put oleo in 8 x 8-inch pan and melt. Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over oleo.
Add coconut, both chips and pecans.
Add in order given (do not stir).
Drizzle milk over this.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes or until light brown.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Combine graham crackers, margarine, confectioners sugar and peanut butter.
Mix until smooth.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips; spread over peanut butter mixture. Cut while warm.
Chill until set.
May be made in small muffin cups.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon; sift well. Beat eggs until thick.
To the dry ingredients, add eggs, sugar, strawberries and oil; beat well.
Pour into two large greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool at least 15 minutes in pans before removing loaves.

title: peanut butter-banana pudding
directions: Combine first three ingredients in a heavy saucepan.
Add eggs and milk, mixing well.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, 25 minutes or until thickened.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Spread about 1/2 teaspoon of peanut butter between 2 vanilla wafers, forming a sandwich.
Repeat procedure with remaining peanut butter and vanilla wafers.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Combine all ingredients but nuts in bowl.
Microwave on High for 2 1/2 minutes.
Stir until smooth.
Add nuts.
Pour out onto wax paper to cool.
Cut in pieces.

title: apple chutney
directions: In a large 6 to 8-quart kettle, combine all ingredients. Cover and bring to a boil.
Uncover and reduce heat to a simmer. Cook, stirring, after 1 hour or until mixture is as jam.
Can and seal or store covered in refrigerator as long as 3 weeks, or freeze as long as 6 weeks.

title: italian sauce
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil until golden brown.
Add any meat desired:
chicken, beef, veal or meatballs.
Brown evenly. Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Add parsley flakes.
Remove pan from heat and take out meat.
Add the tomato paste and tomato sauce.
Fill all cans with water and add to sauce.
Then stir well and add sugar and Italian seasoning.
Place meat back into sauce and simmer for 2 hours.
Add more water if sauce thickens.
Stir occasionally.
Serve with spaghetti, ravioli or gnocchi.

title: trifle
directions: Layer in the bottom of a bowl, slices of pound cake or angel food cake.
Prepare small box of strawberry Jell-O and pour over cake.
Refrigerate until set.

title: hot cakes
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Beat egg.
Add egg, milk and oil to flour.
Stir until smooth.
(Needs to be thin, so adjust milk.) Oil the griddle to start.
Makes 10 to 12 large cakes.

title: fudgie scotch candy
directions: Melt chocolate and butterscotch morsels with sweetened milk in double boiler until melted.
Stir occasionally.
Remove from heat. Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Blend well.
Pour into 8-inch square greased pan.
Chill.
Cut into 1-inch to 1 1/2-inch squares.

title: apple casserole
directions: Into a deep casserole, put in a layer of sausage patties, a layer of peeled and sliced sweet potatoes and a layer of peeled and sliced apples. Top with sausage patties. Bake until well done in 375° oven.

title: sausage dip
directions: Cook ground beef and sausage together.
Add to cheese that has been melted (microwave or double boiler).
Add mushroom soup, Ro-Tel tomatoes, minced onion, chili peppers and garlic powder. Serve hot from a crock-pot.

title: oatmeal blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Line 12 muffin cups. Combine flour, oats, 1/2 cup sugar, baking powder, baking soda, and salt in bowl. Combine oil, water and egg in separate bowl. Add all at once to flour mixture, stirring just until moistened. Fold in blueberries. Divide evenly among prepared muffin cups. Combine remaining 2 Tbsp. sugar and cinnamon, mix well. Divide evenly over muffins. Bake 18 to 20 minutes or until tester inserted in center comes out clean.

title: grandma maloney's marshmallow yams
directions: Boil yams until soft.
Skin yams when they cool down; slice yams and line them in a baking dish.
Sprinkle brown sugar, white sugar and marshmallows along the top.
Cut up about 1/2 stick of butter (depending on how many yams you have) and place on top of yams.
Broil until brown.

title: raisin sauce
directions: Combine the brown sugar, cornstarch and dry mustard in a saucepan.
Slowly stir in the vinegar; blend well.
Add lemon juice, lemon peel, water and raisins.
Stir over medium heat until thick, clear and bubbly.
Perfect for Christmas or Easter ham.

title: fresh vegetable marinade 1
directions: Separate cauliflower and broccoli into small flowerets. Combine all vegetables in a large mixing bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients; mix well and pour over vegetables, tossing gently. Cover and chill at least 3 hours.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Mix soup and half of cheese together. Add all other ingredients and mix well. Pour into large baking dish and sprinkle rest of cheese on top. Bake at 250° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream butter; add sugar, eggs and pumpkin well.
Sift dry ingredients.
Stir; drop by teaspoon on greased sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix dough and put in a bread loaf pan.
Bake in oven at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: old fashioned chicken and dumplings
directions: Simmer chicken until tender enough to bone and skin in salt water.
Put chicken back into broth and bring to boil.
Cut butter into flour and add eggs.
Mix well and roll thin as for pastry.
Cut into narrow strips and drop into boiling broth with chicken.
Cook for 10 minutes or until done.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients; add eggs and oil.
Stir until dry ingredients are moistened; do not beat or cake will be tough. Stir in vanilla, pineapple, pecans and bananas.
Put in well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Boil sugar, Karo, butter and salt for 5 minutes (hard boil stage).
Take off fire.
Add soda and vanilla.
Pour over corn. Stir well and bake 1 hour at 250°, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: hot crabcake dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Drain and flake crabmeat.
Combine all ingredients except almonds.
Mix until blended.
Spoon into 8-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Serve hot with raw veggies and crackers.

title: beef enchiladas
directions: Heat up the oil in a small frying pan.
Add a tortilla and cook it on both sides to soften, then put on a napkin to drain.
Fry all tortillas.
Add to cooked hamburger the cans of pinto beans, the enchilada sauce and the seasonings.
Put in a casserole and layer or stack up with tortillas, meat mixture and, of course, of shredded cheese.
Repeat layer.
Put in 350° oven for 1/2 hour.

title: calico salad
directions: Mix and store in refrigerator.

title: apple cheddar melts
directions: Preheat broiler. Mix curry powder and butter and spread on toast. Layer other ingredients. Shred 1/2 pound of sharp extra sharp cheese. Cover layered toast slices with cheese and broil 6-inches from broiler for 3 to 5 minutes or until cheese is melted. Watch closely to keep from burning.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix flour and soda and salt.
Set aside.
In large bowl, cream brown sugar and margarine until fluffy.
Beat in egg.
At low speed, beat in flour mixture alternately with milk until well blended.
Stir in vanilla and rhubarb.
Turn into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip on top.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all together.
Very good for all vegetables.

title: scalloped squash
directions: Cut squash up and put in a colander for 1 hour.
Grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Layer squash and sprinkle with flour and cut a few slices of butter between each layer.
Also add salt and pepper to taste between each layer.
After completing each layer, pour milk in, then sprinkle cheese on top and cook at 325° for 1 hour. Serves 4 to 6.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Measure flour; resift 2 1/2 cups with cinnamon, cloves and allspice.
Cream butter with sugar; add slightly beaten eggs, flour and liquids.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Cut up candied fruit; add nuts.
Mix with 1/2 cup flour.
Drop by teaspoon on greased and floured cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 25 minutes. Makes 6 dozen.

title: pepsi roast
directions: Put roast in oven safe pan, frozen.
Blend Pepsi and soup together.
Sprinkle soup mix over top.
Bake at 300° for 5 hours, uncovered.
Thicken liquid for gravy.

title: rice dressing
directions: Ground chicken livers and mix with ground meat. Fry with onions, parsley and green onions all together. When brown, let it simmer, then mix it with rice. Serve.

title: jumbo oat cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat together sugar, margarine and corn syrup.
Add egg whites and extract.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Drop onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 14 to 16 minutes.
Yields 1 dozen.

title: mushroom puffs(appetizer)
directions: Work first four ingredients together.
Fold in mushrooms. Spread on onion Melba rounds.
Broil until brownish.

title: real scotch shortbread
directions: Cream butter until light.
Add flour, sugar and salt.
Beat until stiff.
Divide dough.
Roll out between 2 sheets of wax paper to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut into shapes and lift with spatula.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 2, measure 1 cup servings.
Single serving equals 1 cup starch.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Mix together and drop
by spoonful into frying pan and cook like pancakes.
(Above mixture is similar to pancake mix only thicker.
You don't want to add so much flour and milk that you lose the taste of mashed potatoes).
Can add chopped onion to this although I don't.

title: jewish rye bread dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: chicken in a pot
directions: Put vegetables in bottom of crockpot. Arrange chicken on top. Add salt and pepper. Pour water over all. Sprinkle with basil leaves. Cover and cook 7-10 hours on low.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Cut up vegetables and egg. Mix mayonnaise, sugar, mustard and vinegar together.
Mix everything well.

title: sugar-free holiday nog
directions: Combine vanilla pudding, sugar substitute, 2 cups milk and vanilla extract in a bowl.
Mix according to pudding directions. Pour into a 1/2 gallon container with a tight fitting lid.
Add 3 cups milk; shake well.
Add 1 cup evaporated milk; shake well. Add 2 cups milk; shake well.
Chill before serving.

title: sausage cheese appetizer
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Mix well.
Form into balls of desired size.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Balls may be placed on cookie sheet and frozen.
Store in plastic bag in freezer.
May be baked without thawing.
Increase the baking time.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar in a large bowl.
Melt butter in small saucepan.
Add Coca-Cola and cocoa.
Bring just to a boil.
Stir into flour mixture.
Blend in buttermilk, eggs, vanilla, baking soda and salt.
Fold in marshmallows.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: fig preserve cookies
directions: Cut figs up into small pieces.
Mix figs and soda in a small bowl; let stand.
In a separate medium sized bowl, blend margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, figs and water.
Stir well.
In a separate large bowl, mix all dry ingredients together.
Now add other bowl. Add nuts and blend well.
Scoop teaspoon or tablespoon size and place on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
These cookies freeze well.
Yields:
16 dozen.

title: sausage balls
directions: Grate cheese.
Add uncooked sausage and Bisquick.
Mix thoroughly.
Add water as needed.
Shape into balls.
Cook at 375° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Use broiler pan for less greasy sausage balls.

title: baked beans
directions: Add all ingredients except beans.
Cook until all sugar has melted; simmer 5 minutes.
Drain beans and add.
Bake in 300° oven for 2 hours.
A covered cast iron pot is best.

title: sausage soup
directions: Brown sausage in soup pot; remove and set aside.
Saute onion, celery and garlic in a little of the fat from sausage until vegetables become soft.
Add all the other ingredients except noodles and beans (including sausage) and simmer 30 minutes.
Add noodles and beans.
Cook until noodles are soft, 8 to 10 minutes. Serve with a loaf of French bread.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in large bowl.
Mix last 4 ingredients in pan, cook 11 minutes and add first mixture.
Makes 5 pounds.
Spread in jelly roll pan.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix cranberries, pineapple and marshmallows together.
Let set overnight.
Next day, add sugar and Cool Whip.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Dissolve cherry gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in lemonade; add cold water and cranberry juice cocktail.
Pour over ice.
Pour in ginger ale.
Yield:
25 servings.

title: crock-pot stew
directions: Cut meat into small chunks.
Put into crock-pot.
Mix one can of water with soup.
Pour mixture over meat.
Turn on low heat. Let cook all day.
Meat will be tender and complete with gravy.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and salt.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well.
Add milk, vanilla and coconut.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: stew delight
directions: Cut stew meat in small pieces. Combine all other ingredients. Add to meat. Bake at 300° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: chess bars
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix cake mix, 1 egg, 1 teaspoon vanilla, stick of melted margarine and nuts.
Spread into pan.
Mix 3 eggs, powdered sugar and softened cream cheese. Spread over mix and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: peach dump cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Arrange peaches with the juice in bottom of a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over top.
Sprinkle nuts mixed with coconut and brown sugar on top. Drizzle melted margarine over all.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: pepperoni snacks
directions: Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Cut each pepperoni into 2 pieces.
Wrap each biscuit piece around a piece of pepperoni. Place on a pizza pan.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.

title: turkey ham and corn chowder
directions: In 3-quart saucepan over medium-high heat, saute onion in oil 3 minutes or until translucent.
Blend in flour and pepper. Remove pan from heat; slowly add milk, stirring constantly. Return pan to heat.
Add potatoes; bring mixture to boil, stirring constantly.
Add corn and turkey ham; return mixture to boil. Reduce heat to low and simmer soup 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender and mixture has thickened.
Serves 8.

title: beef biscuit roll
directions: Moisten ground meat to spreading consistency, using beef broth.
Combine Bisquick and milk to make soft dough.
Roll out about 1/4-inch thick.
Spread even layer of meat mixture over dough.
Roll, jelly roll fashion.
Slice into 1-inch slices. Place on buttered baking sheet.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes in a 450° oven.
Brush with melted margarine.
Serve with gravy on top.

title: bean salad
directions: May add green or red peppers for added color.
Mix vinegar, sugar and oil.
Cook carrots until tender-crisp.
Add all ingredients.
Mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve.
Keeps well for a week or so.
Use a large mixing bowl.
May adjust amounts of vegetables to your family likes.

title: scotch eggs(serves 5 to 6)
directions: Hard-boil the eggs; shell and dry them.
Sprinkle with flour and cover with sausage meat.
Roll in egg and breadcrumbs.
Fry in deep fat until golden brown.
Drain well.
Cut in half and serve hot with brown gravy or tomato sauce or cold with salad.

title: tomato sauce - marinara
directions: Saute onion in olive oil until lightly brown.
Add garlic. Add tomatoes, etc.
Add spices, usually 1/2 teaspoon or more to taste.
Add salt and sugar.
Bring to a simmer, cover and cook at least 25 minutes, but it can cook 40 to 50 minutes.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients.
Put in glass jar.
Mix the vinegar and sugar; bring to a boil.
Pour over kraut mixture. Chill and serve.
Makes 1 quart.

title: shrimp marinara sauce
directions: Mix together and cook until veggies are done.
Pour over linguini.

title: candied carrots
directions: In a skillet, melt oleo; add brown sugar, stirring until melted.
Add carrots.
Stir over low heat until glazed.

title: german onion potato scramble
directions: Peel and chop onions.
In 10-inch skillet, cook bacon until done.
Remove bacon; add onions and potatoes.
Saute until tender. Beat eggs with salt and pepper.
Add bacon.
Pour over potatoes. Cover and cook over low heat until eggs are set (about 5 or 6 minutes).

title: chuck and vicky maher's eggless date cake
directions: Pour boiling water over dates; add soda and shortening.
Mix well; set aside to cool.
Sift together flour, sugar and salt. Add dry ingredients to date mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Beat well.
Pour into well-greased angel food cake pan.
Bake about 60 minutes in moderate oven at 350° (bake 45 minutes, then cover last 15 minutes with aluminum foil to prevent excess browning).
Cool. Serve with whipped cream.

title: chocolate brownies
directions: Melt chocolate over hot water. Thoroughly cream butter and sugar. Add eggs and beat well. Blend in melted chocolate, vanilla and flour. Mix nuts into batter. Pour batter into a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Bake in slow oven (325°) 30 to 35 minutes. Frost with chocolate frosting, if desired.

title: bread cake
directions: Cream together sugar and butter until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs (1 at a time).
Add vanilla to milk and flour.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together oil, sugar and eggs.
Beat until thickened and creamy. Add flour and mix.
Stir in oats, raisins and walnuts. Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 11 or 12 minutes.

title: barbecue baked beans
directions: In a large skillet, brown ground beef or turkey.
Drain fat.

title: onion dip
directions: Mix ingredients with an electric mixer.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serve with chips or vegetables.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Mix together the drained and flaked tuna, soup, onion and green pepper.
Fill the buns with mixture.
Brush buns with butter.
Bake on cookie sheet in hot oven (400°), about 10 minutes.

title: marshmallow cheese salad
directions: Cream the cream cheese, sugar and mayonnaise together until smooth.
Add rice, cherries, pineapple and marshmallows.
Fold in whipped Lucky Whip.
Chill and serve.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients.
Beat at medium speed for 1 minute.
Drop with a teaspoon 2 inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: no-peek casserole
directions: Cut beef in bite sizes.
Mix all ingredients.
Put in casserole and cover.
Bake at 300° for 3 hours.
Do not peek. Good served over rice or noodles.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in medium sized bowl. Mix dry ingredients in large mixing bowl. Add first mixture to dry ingredients and mix well. Pour in greased and floured cake pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: beef stuffed eggplant
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Scoop pulp from eggplant halves, leaving
1/2-inch
shell.
Dice pulp.
Saute onion, garlic and eggplant
pulp in oil.
Add cubed, cooked meat, tomatoes, salt to taste
and basil.
Fill eggplant shells with mixture.
Top with wheat germ combined with cheese.
Put water 1/2-inch deep in bottom
of baking pan.
Add filled eggplant halves.
Cover with foil.
Bake
at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Uncover and continue baking until shell is tender enough to eat, about 20 minutes. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: scalloped hash browns
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine soup, mustard, sour cream, onion and pepper.
Fold into ham and potatoes.
Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes.

title: raspberry bars
directions: Beat margarine and sugar.
Add egg yolks and beat.
Stir in flour 1/2 cup at a time to form a soft dough.
Press 1 1/4 cups of dough into bottom of a 9-inch square pan.
Spread jam on it.
Pat remaining dough on top.
Sprinkle evenly with confectioners sugar and nuts.
Bake for 35 minutes at 375°.
Remove and cool.
Makes 36 bars.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Cut up rhubarb.
Add sugar and let stand while making pie dough.
Put in other ingredients and stir well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: almond cookies
directions: Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Don't overcook.

title: rolled oat cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar. Add water and vanilla. Mix well. Combine dry ingredients. Add to creamed mixture and mix well. Chill for 30 minutes. Shape into two 1 1/2-inch rolls. Wrap tightly in waxed paper. Chill for 2 hours or until firm. Cut into 1/2-inch slices and place 2-inches apart on greased baking sheets. Bake at 375° for 12 minutes or until lightly browned. Remove to wire racks to cool.

title: aunt bobbie's sad cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir until thoroughly mixed.
Pour into a greased long cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
This is an easy fix ahead recipe that goes well with a cup of coffee.

title: white chocolate almond fudge
directions: Butter square pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inches.
In medium saucepan, over low heat, melt vanilla milk chocolate chips and condensed milk, stirring constantly, until mixture is smooth.
Remove from heat. Stir in almonds and vanilla extract.
Spread in prepared pan. Cover; refrigerate until firm, about 2 hours.
Cut into 1-inch pieces.

title: skillet steak
directions: Combine the flour, salt and pepper.
Pound into both sides of meat.
Cut into 6 serving pieces.
Heat oil in large, deep skillet; brown meat.
Add bouillon cube, water, celery, onion and carrot; cover.
Simmer for one hour.
Add additional small amount of water if necessary.
Stir in nutmeg.
Simmer, covered, an additional 30 minutes or until meat is tender.

title: one step lasagne
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Drain grease.
Combine beef, water, salt and spaghetti sauce in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer 1/3 of the spaghetti sauce mixture, one half noodles, one half cottage cheese and one half Mozzarella.
Repeat layers ending with Parmesan cheese.
Bake, covered with foil, at 350° for 2 hours.
Remove from oven, uncover and let stand for 15 minutes before cutting and serving.
May bake in microwave on full power for 35 minutes.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Heat milk and margarine (don't boil).
Mix together eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Alternate flour and milk while mixing. Add baking powder last (gently).
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: decadent hot chocolate
directions: In a small heavy saucepan over medium heat, mix together the milk, half-and-half, sugar, chocolates, and brown sugar.
Heat until the chocolate melts and the sugar dissolves.
Do not bring to a boil, but make sure the mixture gets steaming hot.
Reduce the heat and keep the chocolate hot.
Place half of the mixture in a blender and mix until frothy.
Return to the pan, add the vanilla and pour into glasses.
Serve immediately.
Makes 2 servings.

title: lemon jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Put in cream cheese and beat until dissolved, then add cold water, pineapple and nuts.
Put in jello mold and refrigerate until molded.
Remove and put in jello dish.

title: squash and sausage casserole
directions: Cook squash in water with onion and margarine until squash is tender.
Drain well and place in bowl.
Mix in sausage, bread crumbs, cheese, eggs and salt and pepper.
Turn into greased casserole and bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: garden macaroni salad
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Stir together first 3 ingredients. Add all remaining ingredients including macaroni and mix well.

title: broccoli-cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on box.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients (except Ritz crackers) and mix thoroughly. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1/2 hour.

title: hand dipped fondants
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk, powdered sugar, melted butter and vanilla until creamy.
Place in freezer until cool and managable. Form into ball and refreeze.

title: pasta fasule
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil until translucent.
Add tomatoes and water; add beans and simmer for 30 minutes.
Cook ditalini according to directions; drain and add to sauce.
Serve immediately.
Top with grated cheese and serve with crusty bread.

title: beef jerky, oven dried
directions: Trim fat; cut into 1/2 to 1-inch wide strips, 1/8 to 1/4-inch thick, 4 to 6-inch long strips.
Mix ingredients and marinate meat in liquid mix overnight in refrigerator.
Drain and pat on paper towels.
Cover bottom rack of oven with foil (shiny side up). Spray top oven rack with Pam.
Hang or lay strips on top rack; do not overlap.
Dry meat at lowest temperature (150° to 200°) until it has turned brown and dry to the touch (4 to 7 hours).
Cool, remove from racks and store in airtight container at cool room temperature.
Keeps indefinitely.

title: bacon potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes; place in foil-lined pan.
Dice red onion and sprinkle over potatoes.
Salt and pepper to taste. Place strips of bacon over potatoes.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lemon crackers
directions: Pulverize ammonia with rolling pin.
Add to milk and let stand at room temperature until dissolved.

title: rum pecan pie
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients except pecans.
Fold in pecans.
Pour into cool cooked pie shell.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°, just until set.
Cool on wire rack.
Can be made ahead.
Cover and store at room temperature up to 24 hours.

title: fruit slush
directions: Boil about 3 minutes the sugar and water.
Then add frozen orange juice concentrate, strawberries and bananas.
Mix well and freeze.
Serve slightly thawed.

title: orange pecans
directions: Combine rind, sugar and orange juice in a heavy saucepan. Cook until it comes to a full boil. Stir in pecans.
Continue to cook, stirring until pecans are coated and all syrup is almost absorbed.
Remove from heat. Stir until pecans are separated. Spread on waxed paper.
Yields 5 1/2 cups.

title: white beans and canadian bacon
directions: Sort the beans and rinse well; place in a large saucepan and cover with cold water.
Let soak overnight, then drain.

title: crullers - liz' recipe
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Beat and add rest of ingredients and mix.
Add enough flour to make soft dough.
Roll on floured board, 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into 2 1/2 x 4-inch squares.
Make 2 slits in each.
Pull one corner to opposite slit.
Fry in shortening; turn to brown on both sides.
Roll in sugar.

title: moist pumpkin bread
directions: Cream shortening.
Gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs and mix well.
Stir in pumpkin and water.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda, salt, cinnamon and cloves. Add to cream mix. Add in nuts and raisins. Spoon into two well-greased loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until done.

title: chicken kiev with sherry sauce
directions: Pound each chicken breast half with flat side of meat mallet to 1/4-inch thick.
Sprinkle seasonings evenly over chicken pieces.
Cover surfaces with cheese.
Roll up each half breast with cheese enclosed.
Secure with a toothpick.
Heat oil in large fry pan.
Saute chicken rolls until golden brown, about 8 minutes.
Place in a shallow baking dish.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: low-fat tuna salad
directions: In a small bowl, combine all ingredients and mix well.
Makes about one cup (enough for three sandwiches).
Spread on bread and garnish with lettuce and tomato.
Calories: 247 per sandwich; 5 fat grams per sandwich.

title: golden crumb broccoli casserole
directions: In covered saucepan, cook broccoli in small amount of boiling, salted water, for 10 to 15 minutes.
Drain.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, cheese, pimento and lemon juice.
Pour over broccoli.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: baked eggplant casserole
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Peel eggplant and dice into 1 1/2-inch cubes.
Cook 10 minutes in boiling salted water to cover over moderate heat (about 250°).
Drain.
Immerse tomatoes in boiling water for 2 minutes.
Drain and remove skin; cut into thin slices. Fold together barbecue sauce, eggplant, garlic and parsley.
Spoon a third of the eggplant mixture into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with a layer of half the tomato slices.
Repeat layers and end with eggplant layer.
Mix butter, bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese; sprinkle over eggplant.
Bake 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: In large bowl, mix first 6 ingredients.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into shell.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: pizza dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm milk.
Add salt and flour; knead.
Add 1/2 cup flour or more until dough is not sticky.
Let rise half hour.
Press on cookie sheet.
Add toppings.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: frozen pumpkin parfait squares
directions: Mix cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and melted butter together. Press into bottom of 9-inch square pan.
Combine pumpkin, brown sugar, salt and spices.
Fold mixture into ice cream.
Pour into crumb-lined pan.
Cover and freeze until firm.
Cut into squares; top with whipped cream and chopped pecans.
Serves 9 to 12.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Pour over any meat.
Bring to a boil with the meat, then simmer on low heat so meat can absorb the great flavor.

title: cheese cake
directions: Cream together cream cheese, vanilla and powdered sugar; set aside. Mix together Cool Whip and milk; fold cream cheese mixture into Cool Whip mixture. Top with pie filling.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Stir all together and store into container.
Stir 3 teaspoons into 1 cup hot water.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Drain pineapple reserving 1/3 cup juice.
Halve pineapple chunks.
In a medium saucepan, combine tomato sauce, reserved pineapple juice, brown sugar, vinegar, onion and green peppers. Stir over medium-high heat until mixture boils.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes.
In a small bowl, combine cornstarch and water.
Stir mixture until smooth.
Add pineapple, cornstarch mixture and chicken into tomato mixture.
Stir over medium-high until thickened and bubbles.
Makes 3 cups.
Serve over rice.

title: pineapple filling
directions: Mix salt, sugar and flour.
Add pineapple.
Let boil until thick.
Spread between cake layers.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients with your hands.
When mixed real good, roll into small balls and put in container in refrigerator overnight.
In a double boiler, mix 1 large bag of chocolate chips and 1/4 pound of paraffin until melted.
Keep over hot water.
Take a pair of tongs and dip each ball of candy in melted chocolate. Place on waxed paper until chocolate hardens.
Store in covered container.
Makes 100 pieces.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and form into balls. Refrigerate balls for 1 hour.
Melt chips and wax in top of double boiler.
Use toothpicks to dip balls in melted chocolate.
Let dry on wax paper.

title: six can casserole
directions: Combine in casserole and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes. Serves 5 to 6.

title: party punch
directions: Pour juice into punch bowl. Sweeten with sugar. Stir in sherbet and add ginger ale.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together using 1 or more peppers.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes.

title: corn and zucchini saute
directions: In skillet over medium heat, melt butter.
Add zucchini, onion and spices.
Cook 3 minutes, stirring frequently until vegetables are crisp and tender.
Add corn; cook 6 to 7 minutes, stirring occasionally until vegetables are heated thoroughly.
Serves 8. Calories per serving:

title: iron skillet cornbread(low-fat, low cholesterol)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In iron (seasoned) skillet, put 1 teaspoon oil and spray lightly with vegetable spray.
Put skillet on low heat on stove top while mixing egg whites, canola oil, baking powder, salt, yogurt and milk.
Whisk all together very good.
Next, add cornmeal and flour and pour into hot skillet. Bake until brown, 20 to 25 minutes.

title: lazy man pie
directions: Heat fruit to almost boiling.
Mix up a batter of sugar, flour and milk (should be slightly thicker than cake batter).
Melt margarine in a pie pan on top of stove.
Pour batter into hot margarine.
Pour hot fruit over batter.
Bake in a 375° oven until brown.

title: monkey bread
directions: One can at a time, cut each biscuit into 4 pieces (makes 40). Shake well in a bag with 3/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon. Put into well-greased angel food cake pan (not with removable center).
Bring remaining ingredients to a boil.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let cool slightly and remove from pan.
Serve warm.

title: hershey pie
directions: Melt Hershey bars in double boiler just until last pieces of chocolate have melted (do not overcook).
Mix melted Hershey bars with Cool Whip and pour in crust.
Place in freezer for at least 1 hour.
Better after 1 day in freezer.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked 8-inch pie shell. Bake 35 to 40 minutes until light brown at 325°.
The texture and taste is like a pecan pie.
Very good.

title: rocky road candy
directions: Combine Eagle Brand milk and chips. Melt over hot water. Mix nuts and marshmallows into chocolate mixture. Spread in greased pan. Refrigerate until firm.

title: tangy meatballs
directions: In a large bowl, combine bread and milk.
Squeeze excess milk out of bread; discard milk.
To the bread, add beef, sausage, onion, mustard seed, seasoned salt, garlic, egg, salt and pepper; shape into 1 1/2-inch balls.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash and drain mushrooms.
Remove stems.
Chop stems.
Melt butter and saute onion 5 minutes.
Add crab, garlic and mushroom stems.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients.
Stir in broth last.
Stuff mushrooms.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: barbecued beans
directions: Brown beef, onion and green pepper; pour off fat.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well and pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: meatless lasagna
directions: Prepare lasagna according to package directions; drain.
In large saucepan, melt margarine.
Add onion and celery; cook until tender.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato paste, water, basil, sugar, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer 15 minutes.

title: boston baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight in water.
Drain.
Cook beans in 1-quart water until tender, about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Add more hot water, if necessary.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Put pork in bottom of a deep casserole.
Add beans and remaining ingredients. Cover and bake at 325° for 4 hours.
Add water if beans become too dry while cooking.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix together sugar, cocoa and flour.
Add milk, water and egg yolks.
Cook until thick, stirring all the time.
Add margarine, vanilla and salt.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Beat egg whites and place on top of pies.
Bake until brown.
Makes 2 pies.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix dry ingredients with fork.
Add shortening.
Mix with fork until crumbly.
In small bowl, mix 1/2 cup water, vinegar and egg with spoon.
Add to dry ingredients.
Mix until moist.
Divide dough into 5 equal parts.
Shape into flat round patties ready for rolling.
Wrap each in wax paper and chill 1/2 hour.
Roll out. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, 350° for 50 minutes.
(May be stored in freezer until needed or refrigerated 3 days.)

title: tostada dip
directions: Heat refried beans in a pan (careful not to burn).
Add hamburger (I cook up
my
hamburger using salt, pepper, garlic powder and a little
chili
powder
to
taste or use hamburger made up with a
packaged
taco
seasoning).
Next, add cheese, salsa and a little onion.
All
you want to do is melt part of the cheese and mix
all
of the flavors.
Adjust seasonings to your taste.
Serve with chips.

title: "hamen's hat"
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla together.
Mix baking powder, flour and salt; add to egg mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
On lightly floured board, cut circles (4-inches x 1/4-thick).
Pinch together to make 3 cornered hat.
Fill with pineapple, cherry, poppy seed, prune or jelly.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° until lightly browned.
Can dust with powdered sugar when completely cooled.

title: idaho potato cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Blend in potatoes and vanilla.
Combine flour, cocoa and soda.
Add alternately with milk, blending well.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool on a rack. Yields 12 to 16 servings.

title: ham casserole
directions: Saute seasonings in margarine; add cream of mushroom soup (add a little water), 3 or 4 slices American cheese and 1/3 block Cheddar cheese.
Simmer on low until cheese is melted.
Add ham. Boil macaroni in another pot; drain.
Add macaroni to mixture. Cook until seasonings are tender.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Pour in casserole dish.
Top with American cheese.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: carlton's catalina salad dressing
directions: Makes 1 quart.
Mix all ingredients well with a whisk.

title: chili-sausage supper
directions: In a large skillet, cook and stir meat, onion and green pepper until meat is brown.
Drain off fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer until noodles are tender.
Add more water, if necessary.

title: buttermilk bread
directions: Place ingredients in bread machine. Bake according to instructions with your machine.

title: lollipop cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat cake mix (dry), water and eggs in large bowl on low speed 30 seconds.
Beat on high speed two minutes.
Drop dough by rounded tablespoonful, 3 inches apart on to ungreased cookie sheet.
Insert wooden stick 1 1/2 inches into edge of dough.
Bake 8 - 11 minutes until puffed and almost no indentation remains when touched.
Cool one minute.
Remove from cookie sheet.
Cool on wire rack.
Frost and decorate.
Makes 20 - 24 cookies.

title: dump cake
directions: Lightly grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Layer the first 4 ingredients in the pan in the order listed.
Slice the oleo or butter into pats; place evenly over nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool or serve warm.
Add a dab of Cool Whip on top.
Serves 12.

title: bachelor's casserole
directions: Saute onions and green pepper in vegetable oil until tender; add ground beef and brown well. Drain off excess grease. Stir in remaining ingredients; pour into greased 2-quart casserole. Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes. Uncover and bake 15 minutes more. Serves 6 to 8.

title: mom's sour cream raisin pie
directions: Mix sugar and spices.
Add to the eggs with the raisins, sour cream, salt and vinegar.
Beat well.
Pour into deep pie shell and put on top crust.
Bake at 350° until crust is golden brown, 45 to 60 minutes.

title: apple dumplings
directions: For syrup, mix first 5 ingredients; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat; add butter.
Sift together dry ingredients; cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add mix all at once; stir just until flour is moistened on lightly floured surface.
Roll into an 18 x 12-inch rectangle.
Cut into 6-inch squares.
Place apples on each square.
Sprinkle apples with sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Dot with butter.
Moisten edges of pastry.
Bring corners to center and pinch edges together.
Place 1-inch apart in an ungreased pan.
Pour syrup over dumplings. Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until apples are tender.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour in greased and floured loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: "ajoe ojo" spaghetti with garlic and oil
directions: Saute 1/2 cup oil, garlic and salt on low in a saucepan; stir constantly until garlic is golden brown.
Cook spaghetti; drain and add garlic sauce.
Toss.
Add parsley, pepper and remaining oil into spaghetti and serve.

title: easy no bake cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese until creamy.
Add condensed milk, lemon juice and whipped topping.
Blend until smooth.
Pour into prepared crust.
Chill at least 4 hours or overnight.
Add fruit topping of your choice and serve.
Keep refrigerated.

title: taco salad
directions: Crumble hamburger and brown slightly.
Then add onion and cook until tender.
Drain off grease.
Add seasoning.
When ready to serve, add beans, lettuce, tomatoes and chips.
Mix well.
Serve with crackers.

title: strawberry figs
directions: Cook figs in water about 30 minutes.
Add sugar and jello; boil 10 minutes.
Put in jar according to canning directions.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix all ingredients; mix well.
Pour into greased pie pan. Makes own crust.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with nutmeg or cinnamon before baking.

title: hamburger rolls
directions: Cook hamburger meat, salt, pepper, garlic and onions together but not brown.
Mix together flour, oil and water.
Roll out like pie dough.
Cut into 2 x 8-inch strips.
Place hamburger on strips.
Roll up like cinnamon rolls.
Brush with butter.
Bake until golden brown.
Serves 8.

title: very good italian appetizer
directions: Mix. Bake at 325° to 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until bubbly.

title: honey rum dressing
directions: Mix and serve over fruit.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cut up cabbage in medium sized chunks and steam.
In greased 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish, put one layer of cabbage.
Add 1 scattered layer of grated cheese, then one layer of White Sauce.
Repeat until dish is practically full.
Melt 2 tablespoons margarine. Add bread crumbs and mix.
Cover cabbage casserole with bread crumb mix.
Dot with margarine and place in oven for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican corn and zucchini
directions: Heat oil in a skillet and saute onion and garlic until soft. Add zucchini and corn.
Saute for 3 to 5 minutes.
Add cumin, salt and pepper.
Add in tomato sauce and water.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes over medium heat and reduce heat to simmer.

title: super moist pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, sour cream and sugar together.
Add eggs and flour; mix well.
Add milk and cake mix.
Beat well and pour into a tube pan, sprayed with Pam cooking spray.
Bake at 350° until done (45 minutes to 1 hour).
The longer it sets, the moister it gets.

title: french fried okra
directions: Cut okra into one-inch slices.
Sprinkle okra with salt and buttermilk, stirring until well coated.
Let stand.
Drain okra well.
Drench in flour, corn meal and baking powder mixture.
Deep fry okra in hot oil until golden brown.

title: oatmeal scotchies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla until creamy.
Gradually add combined flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon; mix well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by level measuring tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 7 to 8 minutes for a chewy cookie or 9 to 10 minutes for a crisp cookie. Cool 2 minutes on cookie sheet and remove to wire rack.
Cool completely.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Boil potatoes and onion.
Drain.
Layer potatoes, cheese, beef and soup in casserole dish.
Salt to taste. Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugars.
Beat in egg, water and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and oats.
Nuts, chocolate chips or raisins can be added.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Stir together flour and salt.
Beat butter for 30 seconds. Add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add egg yolks and vanilla; beat well.
Add dry ingredients to beaten mixture, beating until well combined.
Cover and chill 1 hour.

title: pap paw's red eye gravy
directions: After frying ham in skillet, remove ham and add water. Bring to a boil and add coffee. Boil for 1 minute. Cured ham makes better gravy than fully cooked ham. Serve with eggs and hot biscuits.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook rotini noodles and drain.
Chop green peppers, onions and tomatoes.
Mix package of Good Seasons Italian dressing.
Add all ingredients together and chill.

title: chocolate ribbon pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar and tablespoon of milk in large bowl until smooth. Gently stir in 1/2 of whipped topping. Spread on bottom of crust.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put pecans and coconut on the bottom.
Mix cake mix as directed on box. Spread over nuts and coconut.

title: s'more cookies
directions: Melt chocolate and candy quick in microwave and mix together. You could use Marshmallow Creme instead of peanut butter or in addition to the peanut butter.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Mix soup, oil, sugar, vinegar and mustard.
Heat until boiling.
Pour mixture over carrots, pepper and onions.
Toss and marinate in refrigerator overnight.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken salad
directions: Toss all salad ingredients (except almonds and tomatoes) together with enough mayonnaise to obtain desired consistency. Taste:
Add more seasoning salt if necessary.
Cover and refrigerate.
Serve on lettuce; garnish with toasted almonds and tomato wedges.
Can top each scoop of chicken salad with alfalfa sprouts.

title: fudge pie
directions: Beat eggs into melted butter.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 30 minutes at 375°. Slice warm; top with vanilla ice cream and hot fudge sauce, if desired.
(Similar to Shoney's Hot Walnut Brownie Pie.)

title: mashed turnips and potatoes(heart smart)
directions: In large saucepan over medium heat, in boiling water, cook potatoes and turnips about 20 to 30 minutes or until fork-tender. Drain.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Mix together the 1/4 cup of sugar, cinnamon and apples.
Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add juice and vanilla. Add remaining ingredients, except apple mixture.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Blend all ingredients together.

title: potato doughnuts
directions: Beat eggs well. Gradually beat in sugar. Stir in potatoes, butter and vanilla. Sift dry ingredients together. Add alternating with milk to cream mixture. Chill thoroughly. Roll out on lightly floured surface to 1/2-inch thick. Cut with 2 1/2-inch doughnut cutter. Fry in deep fat about 3 minutes. Once drained, frost or sugar.

title: pudding delight
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar and oleo in 8 x 10-inch pan.
Pecans may be added.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes, stirring about 3 times.
Press down in bottom of pan.
Allow to cool.
Mix together powdered sugar, cream cheese and 8 ounces of Cool Whip.
Spread on crust.
Mix instant chocolate pudding with 1 3/4 cups milk. Spread over first layer.
Mix instant vanilla pudding with 1 3/4 cups milk.
Spread over chocolate pudding.
Top with 8 ounce container of Cool Whip and chocolate shavings.

title: moist devil's food cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 12-inch pan.
Blend margarine, sugar, egg, vanilla and cocoa.
Combine flour and salt.
Add soda to buttermilk and stir until fizzes.
Add flour and buttermilk alternately to creamed mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Cool before icing.
Makes 12 servings.

title: cheese and mushroom canapes
directions: Chop mushrooms in tiny pieces and cook in butter a few minutes.
Add cream cheese, onion, salt and pepper.
If necessary, add some cream to soften.
When ready to serve, heat in 350° oven until bubbly.
Spread on small thin rounds or squares of bread. French bread is delicious.

title: rigatoni
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Layer half the ingredients in the order listed, in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Repeat layers.
Bake, uncovered, 25 to 30 minutes until lightly browned.

title: my mom's "texas ranger" cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream sugar, margarine and Crisco.
Add other ingredients, mixing well.
Make a small ball and press down with a fork.
Bake 12 minutes.
Allow to cool on pan a minute before removing.
Makes 3 dozen 3-inch cookies.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Bring to boil; pour 1/2 peaches into Pyrex pan.
Cut up 1 pie crust and layer over peaches.
Pour in rest of peaches.
Top with other pie crust.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup sugar.
Cut slashes in crust.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: mud bars
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients and set aside.
In a separate bowl, beat the brown sugar, butter and vanilla until creamy. Add egg and beat well. Gradually add flour mixture. Stir in 1 1/3 cups chocolate chips.
Spread in a 9-inch square pan. Bake at 375° for 23 to 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and immediately put remaining chocolate chips on top. When they are shiny, spread evenly. When cool, put in refrigerator for 15 minutes to set chocolate.
Cut into squares.

title: snicker bars
directions: Melt chips and shortening over hot water.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into an 8-inch foil lined pan.
Refrigerate for 15 minutes.
Combine caramels, butter and water in pan and melt over boiling water until smooth.
Add nuts and spread over chocolate mixture in the 8-inch pan.
Refrigerate (about 15 minutes). Return remaining chocolate to heat until smooth again.
Spread caramel mixture and refrigerate.

title: apple drop cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease cookie sheets.
Sift flour with baking soda, salt and spices into large bowl.
Stir in walnuts, apple and raisins; set aside.
In large bowl of electric mixer, at medium speed, cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg and apple juice; beat until combined.
Stir in flour mixture; mix well.
Drop by tablespoonfuls 2 inches apart onto prepared cookie sheets.
Bake 8 minutes, or until golden brown.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: grandma's cabbage rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cabbage leaves, and make balls. Wilt cabbage leaves in water.
Use this juice for basting and 1 cup over pan of balls wrapped in wilted leaves.
Bake 1/2 hour, covered, for 30 to 35 minutes and uncovered at 350°.

title: groundnut stew(west africa)
directions: Place chicken pieces in a large Dutch oven.
Add water, 1/2 cup chopped onion and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer 10 minutes, adding 1 teaspoon ginger root.
Remove from heat; set aside.
In a large frypan, place peanut butter and 1 cup of stock from chicken; stir to make a paste.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly with a wooden spoon until mixture is smooth and well blended. When mixture is thickened, add remaining onion and ginger root, tomato and tomato paste.
Cover and reduce heat to very low, stirring constantly until mixture becomes oily on top, about 20 minutes.
Add chicken and remaining stock to peanut butter mixture.
Cook over low heat about 45 minutes, stirring often. (Watch carefully!
Peanut butter mixture burns easily.)
Serve with rice.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: glorified rice
directions: * Reserve small amount of each fruit to garnish completed salad top.

title: cabbage goulash
directions: Smother meat and sausage; add onions and garlic.
Saute, then add vinegar, tomatoes and chili powder.
Cook for about 15 minutes.
Then shred cabbage and add to mixture.

title: chicken noodle scallop
directions: Bring soup and milk just to a boil; remove from heat.
Add peas, noodles, chicken, onion, paprika and pepper.
Mix well.
Pour into baking dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: orange blossom punch
directions: Combine all ingredients except sherbet.
Add ice cubes as desired and fruit garnishes.
Add sherbet just before serving. Yields 50 servings.

title: mexican soup
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and form into meat balls.
Cook - simmer the rest of ingredients for 1 hour.
Drop meat balls into soup.
Simmer 30 minutes longer.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Peel and slice apples; place in greased 8-inch square dish. Mix remaining ingredients and sprinkle over apples. Bake until topping is golden brown and apples are tender (about 30 to 45 minutes).

title: pasta with vegetables
directions: Steam broccoli until soft, then saute in olive oil.
Saute mushrooms and zucchini in olive oil.
When vegetables are soft, put them in pan together.
Add broth and stewed tomatoes; simmer. Cook pasta; mix together with vegetables.
Add grated cheese to taste.

title: pot roast super chili
directions: Pour wine and onion soup mix on roast.
Cover and bake until tender.
Shred roast.
Save all juices.
Add rest of ingredients and juices.
(I double all cans to make super large pot.)
Simmer together.
Serves 12 to 24.
Serve with French bread and grated cheese on top.

title: sausage jambalaya
directions: Saute sausage, onions, peppers and garlic. Combine with remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; stir, cover and simmer for 25 minutes.

title: russian honey cake
directions: Blend thoroughly eggs, sour cream, honey and butter.
Add sifted dry ingredients and mix well.
Spread in a greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan and bake in a moderate oven at 350° for about 30 minutes.
While still warm, glaze and sprinkle with nuts.

title: western lite broil
directions: Combine soy sauce, water, lemon juice, honey, onions, and garlic powder.
Add steak and turn to coat thoroughly.
For best results, marinate 24 hours.
Broil beef to medium rare (do not overcook).
Cut across grain into thin slices.
Sprinkle lightly with toasted sesame seeds, if desired.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: hot beef dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl.
Top with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: quick baked haddock
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray 13 x 9-inch pan.
On waxed paper, combine bread crumbs, salt and pepper.
In shallow pan, beat egg whites and 1 tablespoon water.
Dip fillets in egg and water, then the crumbs.
Place in pan and spray butter Pam on top.
Sprinkle with paprika.
It is done when fillets flake when tested with fork.

title: crock-pot mac and cheese
directions: Combine all ingredients in a crock-pot. Cook on "slow" 3 hours.

title: pistollettes
directions: Brown meat.
Add Tony's seasoning.
Cook broccoli according to directions.
Add cheese and broccoli to meat.
Cut end of pistollettes off.
Cut center out with knife.
Stuff pistollettes with mixture.
Melt butter.
Add garlic powder.
Roll each stuffed pistollette in butter.
Put in pan and bake until golden brown.

title: cinnamon buttons
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Shape into button-size cookies; bake 5 minutes at 375.
Shape into regular-size cookies; bake 10 minutes at 375.

title: chocolate meringue drops
directions: Preheat oven to 200°.
Line 2 large cookie sheets with foil. In small bowl with mixer at high speed, beat egg whites, cream of tartar and salt until soft peaks form.
Beating at high speed, gradually beat in sugar 2 tablespoons at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add cocoa and almond extract and continue beating until meringue stands in stiff peaks.
