Drop mixture by level tablespoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Sprinkle some chocolate pieces on top of each cookie.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.
With metal spatula, carefully loosen and remove cookies from foil; cool completely on wire racks.
Store.
Sprinkle in tightly covered container.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: easy fudge
directions: Place all ingredients, but nuts, in heavy nonstick pan.
Heat on medium heat until butter melts; mix well.
Add nuts.
Pour into buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.
Refrigerate.

title: homemade italian spaghetti
directions: Brown beef, sausage and diced onions together in large skillet or Dutch oven on medium heat.
Drain all fat from mixture.
Add all remaining ingredients and simmer on low heat for 20 to 25 minutes, uncovered, stirring occasionally.

title: venison stuffed bacon rolls
directions: Partially cook bacon; remove from drippings and set aside. Cook onion and garlic in drippings until tender but not brown.
In large bowl, combine egg and tomato sauce.
Stir in bread crumbs, mushrooms, onion mixture, parsley, salt and pepper.
Add meat and mix well.
Divide mixture into 4 parts.
Form into meat loaf style rolls.
Place 3 slices bacon side by side on wax paper.
Place meat at one end of bacon and roll up jelly roll style.
Secure with toothpicks if necessary.
Place rolls seam side down in large baking dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Turn and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: cheese pocket
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients until smooth. Roll out and spread 1 tube of crescent rolls in ungreased 9 x 13 pan. Pour mixed ingredients on top and spread evenly. Roll out other tube of crescent rolls and lay on top of filling. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes (until slightly golden).

title: enchilada pie
directions: Place half of chili on bottom of greased 1-quart baking dish. Cover with half corn chips, onion and cheeses.
Repeat with layers of remaining chili, corn chips, onions and top with cheeses.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pudding torte
directions: Mix crushed cookies with melted butter; pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 8 minutes at 350°.
Allow to cool.
Beat cream cheese and powdered sugar together.
Add 1 container Cool Whip and beat until fluffy.
Pour over cooled crust and refrigerate.
When chilled, spread pudding over cream cheese mixture.
Top with remaining whipped topping.

title: buttermilk sweet dough
directions: In large bowl, dissolve yeast in water.
Add buttermilk, eggs, 2 1/2 cups flour, butter, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Blend on low speed for 1/2 minute, then 2 minutes on medium speed.
Stir in enough flour to make dough easy to handle.

title: marinated london broil
directions: Marinate London broil 8 to 24 hours.
Grill to desired doneness.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Combine gelatin and water, let stand 5 minutes.
Heat soup, add in gelatin and cream cheese just until melted, remove from heat and let cool.
Stir in remaining ingredients and chill in serving dish for 3 hours or until firm.
Serve with crackers.

title: freezer cukes
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in refrigerator overnight.
Put in freezer jars (do not fill to top).
Put in freezer.
Thaw to eat.
Will keep in refrigerator after thawing for 1 week.

title: marshall field's cinnamon crunch muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter or margarine.
Add the sugar and cream until fluffy; blend in eggs.
In a bowl, combine sour cream and baking soda.
Set aside.

title: susan's salad
directions: Sprinkle dry Jell-O over cottage cheese and mix.
Add drained pineapple and oranges.
Fold in Cool Whip; chill.

title: breakfast pizza(this recipe is perfect for overnight guests and brunches)
directions: Cook sausage until browned; drain.
Press rolls into ungreased 12-inch lipped pizza pan.
Spoon on sausage.
Sprinkle on potatoes.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
In a bowl, beat together eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour into crust.
Sprinkle Parmesan over top.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.
Cut like a pizza.

title: country ice cream
directions: Add sugar gradually to beaten eggs.
Continue to beat until mixture is very stiff.
Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Pour into a chilled 1 1/2-gallon container and freeze.
(Use either electric or hand-turned freezer.)

title: breakfast take alongs
directions: Beat together butter, sugar, egg and vanilla until well blended.
Add combined flour, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in oats, cheese, wheat germ and bacon. Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.

Bake in preheated moderate oven at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes or until edges are golden brown. Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet. Remove to wire cooling rack. Store in loosely covered container in refrigerator or at room temperature. Makes 3 dozen.

title: ribbon salad
directions: Lightly oil a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Prepare lemon gelatin according to package directions.
Pour into pan; chill until firm. Soften unflavored gelatin in cold water.
Bring fruit cocktail syrup to a boil.
Remove from heat and dissolve unflavored gelatin in hot syrup.
Stir into cottage cheese.
Add fruit cocktail; spread evenly over lemon gelatin.
Chill until firm.
Prepare cherry gelatin according to package directions.
Chill until mixture mounds when dropped from a spoon.
Pour over cheese layer. Chill until firm.
Unmold on lettuce.
Slice and serve with crackers.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat, onions and celery.
Add soups.
Simmer, uncovered, on low heat for about 2 hours.
Serves 18 to 20.

title: fish fillet in paper bag
directions: Prepare fish.
Top each fillet with 1 sprig dill, 1 to 2 slices mushrooms, 2 slices peeled ginger root, 1/4 teaspoon minced garlic mixed with 1 teaspoon butter.
Cut paper bags to sheets large enough to fold generously over fish and butter inside of bag.
Fold over each prepared fillet and place on a cooking tray.
Bake in a 350° preheated oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Serve in bag.

title: garden lite spaghetti(low calorie)
directions: In a large saucepan, cook onion and garlic in margarine until tender.
Stir in flour, salt and thyme.
Gradually stir in milk. Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture thickens.
Stir in cheese. Cook and stir until melted.
Add broccoli, carrots and mushrooms. Heat through.
Serve over hot cooked spaghetti.
Makes 6 servings, approximately 260 calories per serving.

title: little chippers(cookies)
directions: Beat butter and shortening on medium to high for 30 seconds. Add sugar, cocoa powder, baking soda and salt.
Beat until combined.
Mix in flour using spoon if necessary. Chill about 45 minutes or until easy to handle.
Shape dough into small balls. Place on greased cookie sheet.
Place one chocolate chip onto each ball, flattening it slightly. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: harvard beets
directions: Drain beets; reserve liquid in 1 cup glass; pour beet liquid and add enough water to make 1 cup liquid.
In one quart microwaveable casserole dish or bowl, combine sugar, cornstarch, salt, pepper, and vinegar.
Stir in beet liquid; cook uncovered on high 2 1/2 to 3 minutes.
Stir occasionally until mixture thickens and is clear.
Add beets and stir lightly.
Cook covered on high about 5 minutes.

title: our favorite meat loaf
directions: In small bowl, mix tomato sauce, mustard, vinegar and brown sugar; set aside.
Mix beef, onion, egg, crackers, salt and pepper.
Add half of tomato sauce mixture and blend.
Shape into loaf and make depression in center.
Pour the rest of the tomato sauce over the top of the loaf.
Cook for 18 to 20 minutes, uncovered, or until center is cooked.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

title: chicken satay(with peanut sauce)
directions: Soak the skewers in cold water for 30 minutes before broiling.

title: pecan cups
directions: For pastry:
Cream butter and add cream cheese; cream together. Stir in flour.
Press into mini muffin pans (like pizza dough). Add a little chopped pecans to the bottom of each cup.

title: yum-a-setta
directions: Brown hamburger and drain. Add seasoned salt, pepper, dill, brown sugar, onion, mushrooms and tomato soup. Cook noodles; drain. Add cream of chicken soup.
Layer 13 x 9-inch pan with hamburger mixture and then noodle mixture.
Put cheese, half between, then on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix dry ingredients together and set aside.
Mix milk and egg. Add chopped onion and jalapeno.
Mix with dry ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into hot oil.
Fry until golden brown.

title: bill's mom's spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute onions and mushrooms in a little olive oil in large heavy pot.
Drain off oil.
Add all other ingredients.
Bring to a boil, then simmer until thick (2 to 2 1/2 hours).
Keep covered. When slightly cooled, refrigerate.
Serve next day.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, syrup, salt, vanilla and butter.
Place the pecan pieces in the bottom of the uncooked pie shell.
Add filling.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then reduce to 350° and bake until mixture sets, 30 to 35 minutes.

title: waldorf-astoria red velvet cake
directions: Grease and flour 2 (9-inch) pans.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream shortening.
Add sugar and eggs; beat well.
Make a paste of the cocoa and food coloring.
Pour into creamed mixture and blend well. Combine salt and vanilla with the buttermilk; add to creamed mixture alternately with sifted cake flour.
Mix vinegar and baking soda in small bowl; fold into batter, do not beat.
Pour batter evenly into prepared pans and bake for 30 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched.
(Cake can also be baked in 13 x 9-inch pan for 35 to 40 minutes.)
Cool and remove cakes from pans. Split each layer in half to make 4 layers; frost.

title: molded chicken salad
directions: *If you use Dream Whip, reduce sugar to 1 1/2 teaspoons.

title: pecan fudge pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In saucepan over low heat, melt chocolate and oleo.
Stir in Eagle Brand, hot water and eggs; mix well.
Remove from heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into prepared pastry shell.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes, or until center is set.
Cool; chill 3 hours.
Top with ice cream. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: old fashioned corn bread
directions: Preheat oven oven to 425°.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Add the cornmeal and stir until well mixed.

title: pineapple cake roll
directions: Filling:
Make into paste.
Cook until thickened and cool 1 cup canned milk and 3 tablespoons flour.
Beat until fluffy sugar, shortening, vanilla and salt.
Add to paste and beat.
Add pineapple.
Make cake mix as directed.
Bake on two foil-lined cookie sheets at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Place filling on cake.
Roll like a jelly roll after filling.
Refrigerate.

title: tuna burger
directions: Mix ingredients (except buns) in a medium size bowl until well blended.
Divide portions of tuna mixture onto hamburger buns. Wrap buns in tinfoil and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before unwrapping from tinfoil.

title: bread pudding
directions: Heat milk.
Put bread in it.
Remove from burner.
Let sit for 5 minutes.
Add butter, salt, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Mix.
Pour into greased dish and bake inside a pan of hot water for 40 to 50 minutes until firm.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix eggs and oil. Add dry ingredients. Mix well. Add carrots and nuts. Bake 350° for 30-35 minutes.

title: claire's home-tested recipe for a happy marriage
directions: Mix ingredients well with much Care and Sharing.
Watch constantly to prevent boiling over.
Test often while cooking. Sprinkle generously with Kindness and Affection.
Add seasoning of Children, according to your taste.
Yields a lifetime of Happiness.

title: easy chocolate sauce
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar and cocoa and stir to combine well. Blend 1/2 cup of the milk.
Boil to a full boil for 1 minute. Remove from heat and stir in 1/2 teaspoon vanilla; add remaining milk.
Good warm or cold.

title: mamaw's chicken gumbo
directions: Boil chicken and cut in small pieces. Boil rice. Saut chicken pieces in butter for a few minutes. Take chicken pieces out of butter. Set aside. Add bell pepper, onion and celery to butter. Saut until onion becomes clear or changes color. Add chicken to vegetables. Stir. Add cooked rice, mixing well.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix meat, soup mix and garlic powder together. Form mixture into small balls.
Add ketchup and beer to saucepan and mix together.
Add meatballs, cook to boiling, then simmer for 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine butter and cracker crumbs; spoon 1/2 the crumbs into a 2-quart casserole.
Cover with chicken.
Combine sour cream, soup and broth; pour over chicken.
Top with remaining cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: crock-pot pork-potato dinner
directions: Place potatoes, then pork and then bacon in layers in crock-pot.
Sprinkle salt, pepper and rosemary on top of each layer.
Cover barely with water.
Cook 6 to 8 hours until tender. Serve with hot cornbread or rolls.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Combine shortening, butter and sugar; cream until light and fluffy.
Add
eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine	flour
and
baking
powder; add to creamed mixture
alternately with milk and vanilla, beating well after each addition.
Stir in crushed pineapple.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix flour, powdered sugar and margarine.
Put in an 8 x 8-inch square pan, building up 1/2-inch edge.
Bake at 350°
for 20 minutes.
Beat eggs until fluffy and add rest of ingredients. Beat well.
Pour over hot crust.
Bake an additional 25 minutes or longer until imprint remains when touched.
Cool.
Cut into squares.
(Sprinkle top with powdered sugar while hot if desired.)

title: strawberries (candy)
directions: In a large bowl, mix nuts, coconut and jello.
Add condensed milk and vanilla and mix well.
Cover and chill 1 hour.
Pour water into a small bowl.
Color green with food coloring.
Add almonds and mix until almonds are a deep green color.
Lift almonds out onto a paper towel to dry.
Shape chilled mixture into strawberries,
using about 1 teaspoon for each.
Roll in red sugar and dip ends in green sugar.
Use the almond slivers for stems.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all of the ingredients in the mixer for 3 minutes.
Pour into a well greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° about 50 minutes. Cool.
Invert after 20 minutes and remove cake.

title: tortilla salad
directions: Boil eggs.
Cut lettuce into bowl.
Set aside.
In separate bowl, dice onion, tomato and mushrooms.
Crush chips in bowl with lettuce.
Add together lettuce mix and diced vegetables.
Bring sauce to a boil.
Add sauce to mixture.
Stir together well and serve.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; spread in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with coconut and pecans.
Mix last 3 ingredients together, blending well.
Spread over coconut and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix all together and pour in pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 60 minutes.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix Oreos and butter.
Press into an 8-inch pie plate.
Mix remaining ingredients and spoon into crust.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: italian sweet pie(ricotta cheese cake)
directions: Make shell first; soften margarine with hand.
Mix eggs, orange juice and vanilla.
Add sugar, flour and baking powder. Knead until dough holds together and forms a ball.
Roll dough out to make crust and place in 9-inch pie pan.

title: overnight french toast
directions: Combine eggs, milk, baking powder and vanilla extract.
Pour over bread to soak.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
In the morning, combine frozen strawberries, bananas, sugar, and apple pie spice.
Put fruit mixture in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Top fruit with soaked bread.
Sprinkle with cinnamon sugar.
Bake in 450° oven 20 to 25 minutes.

title: friendship tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together and store in an airtight container.
Use 2 teaspoons of the mixture per cup.

title: brown sugar raisin pie
directions: Cook until thick.
Stir in raisins.
Pour in a baked 8-inch pie shell.
Beat egg whites for topping.
Brown in oven.

title: marinated cocktail mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms.
Cook in boiling salted water for 10 minutes. Drain well.
Combine with remaining ingredients.

title: 7up cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and make sheet cake or layer cake. Bake at 350 degrees until golden brown.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Break in small pieces.
Cook broccoli.
Place broccoli in a large baking dish.
Put chicken over broccoli.
Put soup and cheese plus 1 can of water in a small pot. Heat until cheese melts.
Pour over chicken.
In a large bowl, break bread up and pour melted butter over it.
Toss until covered. Put layer over top of chicken.
Bake in a 350° preheated oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until brown and bubbly.

title: jello punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and sugar in hot water.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Pour over ice to serve.

title: cheese crackers
directions: Mix cheese, butter, celery seed, salt, onion and flour.
Form a ball of dough and then roll out on a lightly floured work surface.
Cut into squares.
Transfer to an ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 450° for about 8 minutes.
Yields 18 crackers.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients in order given in a 4-quart casserole.
Top with mixture of cornflakes and margarine.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 10.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Combine gelatin and water, let stand 5 minutes.
Combine next 8 ingredients.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until mixture begins to thicken.
Add gelatin and stir until dissolved. Cool.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add remaining sugar by tablespoonfuls.
Fold into pumpkin mixture into cool baked pie crust.
Chill before serving.

title: sweet potato cake
directions: Mash potatoes (fresh potatoes may be used). Then blend all the remaining ingredients.
Pour into a greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° until done, approximately 60 to 70 minutes.

title: rose ann's pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a bowl, beat eggs, then add light corn syrup and light brown sugar, butter or margarine and vanilla until
well blended.
Put pecans on the bottom of the pie shell. Then pour over the pecans the liquid mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool.
Top with whipped cream and enjoy! Makes 8 servings.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine in microwave dish.
Bake for 7 minutes or until cheese bubbles.
Put more cheese on top and let melt.
Put toasted bread crumbs on top.

title: hollandaise sauce
directions: Melt the butter over hot water.
Remove from heat and cool. In the top of a double boiler, blend egg yolks into butter.
Add boiling water slowly, stirring constantly, until thickened, over hot water.
Remove from heat.
Stir in lemon juice, salt and cayenne pepper.
Yields 1 1/4 cups.

title: tomato sauce with sausage and meat balls
directions: Put tomato paste in large pot and add water slowly, mixing with a whisk or spoon.
Add oregano, basil and garlic.
Bring to boil and lower heat to slow boil.
Add onion and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Cook for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spray 9 x 13 pan with Pam. Sprinkle bottom of pan with nuts and coconut to make a layer. Prepare cake mix according to package directions and spread over nuts and coconut. Mix together the confectioners sugar, margarine and cream cheese. Dollop or spread over cake mix layer. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: green chili dip
directions: Mix together cream cheese, sour cream, diced chili and garlic. Refrigerate overnight.
Note:
May use non fat products.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Flatten chicken with meat mallet to 1/4-inch thickness. Flour breasts,
thin
dip
into
egg, then bread crumbs.
Cook chicken in
oil on medium-high heat until well browned on both sides; be sure
not
to
overcook.
Pour spaghetti sauce into baking dish and
place chicken on sauce and top with Parmesan cheese.
(Dish can be prepared one day ahead and stored in the refrigerator.) Bake
in
oven
for 15 to 30 minutes; put Mozzarella on the last 5 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add vinegar, meal and vanilla.
Beat eggs in one at a time.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: haddock with asparagus
directions: Heat up can of soup and milk in skillet.
Whisk until hot. Add haddock and juice of lemon.
Cover and cook for approximately 7 to 10 minutes.
When haddock is cooked, add asparagus pieces and heat until hot.
Remove and serve over toast

title: peach dumplings
directions: Mix together flour, baking powder, salt, shortening and milk. Roll as
for pie dough and cut into squares.
Wrap each square around a
peach.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Make the following syrup
and	pour
over
the dumplings.
Bake at 375° about 45 minutes.

title: celebration punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and serve.

title: marinated fish
directions: Combine ingredients except fish and bread crumbs and cook 5 minutes.
Cool and pour over fish.
Marinate covered and refrigerate several hours.
Remove fish, dip into bread crumbs and fry until brown and tender.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: whole wheat raisin and nut quick bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees.
Grease loaf pan and line with waxed paper.
Mix all ingredients except raisins and nuts.
Add the raisins and nuts and mix again.
Bake for 1 hour.
Turn onto a rack to cool.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients until Sure-Jell is dissolved, then add remaining ingredients.
Boil 4 minutes and pour into sterilized jars and seal.
Yield:
About 4 pints.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook in large skillet, onion, green pepper, celery and garlic in oil until tender, but not brown.
Fry bacon until fairly crisp. Drain and crumble.
Cook hamburg in frypan or microwave until there is no pink.
Combine with vegetables in large skillet.
Add undrained tomatoes, rice, sugar, chili powder, pepper and 1 cup of water.

title: blueberry rhubarb jam
directions: Cook rhubarb until soft, (do not add water) add sugar and blueberry pie filling. Cook until boiling, add jello.
Stir until dissolved, cool in jars, and freeze.
If I double the batch, I use an additional 3 oz. pkg. of jello as jam tends to be too thin. Makes about 10 (8 oz.) jars.

title: dottie's cranberry gelatin
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients and let set overnight to blend flavors.
Mix with hot water only the jello.
When cool, stir in cranberry mixture and nuts.
Pour into large ring mold. Chill until firm. Unmold and fill center with waldorf salad. Garnish with salad greens.

title: chocolate banana shake
directions: Combine milk, corn syrup, sugar and vanilla in a blender and blend for 5 seconds.
Add ice cream and banana and blend for 30 seconds or until smooth and frothy.
Contains 3 servings.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chocolate chips. Beat well. Toss chips with small amount of flour. Fold into batter. Pour into buttered Bundt pan. Do not flour. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: plantation bars
directions: Blend together the shortening and brown sugar.
Add the flour, soda and salt.
Stir in the rolled oats.
Press 1/2 mixture into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Spread with the mincemeat.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken and noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles in salt water.
Mix other ingredients together and cook until melted good, then add noodles.
Put into a buttered casserole dish.
Top with seasoned bread crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Combine pudding mix with 2 cups of milk in a bowl.
Mix well. Fold in whipped topping.
Layer graham crackers on bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread with half the pudding mixture. Repeat layers, ending with graham crackers.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: When tomatoes are turning yellow, pick and wash. Slice thin. Salt and pepper to taste, then flour.
Drop in hot oil. Cook until golden brown.
This is a Southern delicacy.

title: cheesecake
directions: In blender, mix cream cheese, sugar, egg, vanilla and juice. Pour into prepared crust.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 45 minutes or until set.
Top with your favorite fruit topping.

title: best doughnuts
directions: Beat eggs and sugar; add shortening.

Add flour, sifted with salt, baking powder, and spices, alternately with milk. Roll on lightly floured surface to 1/2 inch thickness and cut with doughnut cutter. Fry in deep hot fat (365 to 375 degrees) until brown.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Makes 3 dozen doughnuts.

title: easy fudge
directions: Measure all ingredients first.
Melt butter or margarine.
Add cocoa.
Stir in powdered sugar quickly.
Add vanilla last.
Spray loaf pan with Pam.
Let stand in pan 1 hour, then it's ready to devour.

title: apple dumpling cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together by hand. Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: mimi's cornbread
directions: Mix well.
Pour into greased pan or muffin pan.
Bake at 400° until nice and brown.
Enjoy!

title: country breakfast casserole
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, add hash browns to bacon drippings. Brown slightly; turn over.
Add in layers the eggs and bacon.
Top with cheese.
Cover and cook over low heat for about 10 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix well (fingers work best).
Form into walnut sized balls. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: marinated slaw
directions: Alternate cabbage, onions and sugar in a bowl.
Mix together and bring to a boil the vinegar, oil, salt, mustard, celery seed and sugar.
Pour over cabbage.
Let stand at least 24 hours in refrigerator before serving.
Slaw will keep for several days in refrigerator.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: Combine onion, carrots and mushrooms; set aside.
In small mixing bowl, combine cottage cheese, eggs, Parmesan cheese and oregano.
In 3 quart oblong baking dish, layer half of spaghetti sauce, 3 lasagna noodles, all onion-carrot-mushroom mixture and half of cheese mixture.
Cover with remaining noodles, spaghetti sauce, spinach and cheese mixture.
Top with tomatoes and Mozzarella cheese.
Microwave on High (100%) for 18 to 21 minutes.

title: sugar-free banana cookies
directions: Put together apples, dates, raisins and boiling water.
Let cool.
Cream oleo, sweetener and egg.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Add banana, vanilla, nuts and oats.
Add dates and raisins last.
Drop by teaspoons on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: scalloped corn and broccoli
directions: Cook frozen broccoli according to directions on package.
In a bowl, mix corn, beaten eggs, milk and crushed crackers.
Add broccoli and put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until done, 50 to 60 minutes.
Should be lightly brown.
Makes a good amount for potlucks.

title: loaded potato soup
directions: Saut onion in butter; stir in flour. Cook for 1 to 2 minutes. Don't let it burn. Add salt, pepper and milk. Keep stirring. Cook 5 to 6 minutes. Add cooked potatoes and cheese. Cook 10 to 15 minutes. Top with cooked bacon, shredded cheese and scallions.

title: barbecued roast pork
directions: Fry onion in oil until tender, but not browned.
Add tomato sauce and steak sauce, seasoning to taste, and roast pork.
Serve on toasted hamburger buns.

title: eggplant parmigiana(mama's)
directions: Prepare egg batter; you may need to add a bit more flour or milk to make a good batter consistency.
Slice eggplant in 1/8-inch round slices.
Heat skillet with oil and cook slices 1 1/2 minutes on each side, then dip them in batter and fry on each side until lightly browned.

title: sweet and crunchy caramel corn
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
In a large roasting pan, place popcorn and set aside.
In 2-quart saucepan, combine brown sugar, butter, corn syrup, salt and molasses.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until mixture comes to a full boil (8 to 12 minutes).
Continue cooking, stirring occasionally, until candy thermometer reaches 238° or small amount of mixture dropped into ice water forms a soft ball (2 to 6 minutes).
Remove from heat. Stir in baking soda and vanilla.
Pour over popcorn.
Sprinkle peanuts over caramel mixture.
Stir.
Continue baking for 25 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Immediately place caramel corn on waxed paper.
Cool completely.
Break into pieces.
Store in tightly covered container.
Yields 6 quarts.

title: baked scallops
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Coat individual ramekins with olive oil. Melt 3 tablespoons butter and mix in pepper, onion, garlic, salsa, parsley, lemon juice, dill and vermouth (or chicken broth).
Stir in scallops, gently coating them well.
Divide the mixture in two ramekins.
Sprinkle bread crumbs and Hungarian paprika over top to taste.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: chicken in red wine
directions: In frying pan, melt margarine and brown chicken breasts over medium heat for about 15 to 20 minutes.
Cover and let simmer about 30 minutes longer.
Remove chicken from pan.
Add onion, mushrooms, wine and sour cream into pan.
Stir together until hot. Add the chicken and cook over low heat about 10 minutes (covered).
Serve over rice.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown hamburger in a large pot.
Then drain.
Add all other ingredients.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 2 hours.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Chop broccoli, cauliflower and red onion; add raisins and bacon bits.
Mix dressing ingredients separately.
Chill overnight.
Pour over salad and stir well.

title: creole wax beans
directions: Cook onion and green pepper in fat until onion is yellow. Blend in flour; add tomato juice gradually.
Cook for 5 minutes. Add salt, pepper and beans.
Heat thoroughly.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites and salt until foams, add sugar and beat until stiff.
Add nuts and chips.
Spoon mixture on greased cookie sheet with teaspoon.

title: tanuki "crab" cake hors d'oeuvres
directions: Remove any icky parts from the salmon.	Place all ingredients except oil in a bowl and mix together gently.
Form into half dollar sized cakes.
Cook in frying pan with just enough oil to prevent sticking, cook for three minutes on each side.
Serve with lemon wedges and/or tartar sauce.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
In greased casserole dish, place several slices of bread to cover the bottom or use crushed corn flakes.
Pour mixture over bread and bake for 15 minutes at 400°.
"Excellent casserole."

title: oriental stir-fry
directions: Bring water to a boil and steam broccoli and carrots over the water for 3 minutes.
Combine cornstarch, sugar, soy sauce and sherry.
Mix well.
Preheat wok or skillet 1 minute with 1 tablespoon oil.
Add all the vegetables and stir-fry several minutes.
Remove vegetables.
Add remaining oil to skillet.
Add beef and brown, stirring well.
Add soy mixture, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens.
Return vegetables to skillet or wok.
Cover and cook 1 minute.
Serve with rice.

title: stuffed chicken cutlets
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl and refrigerate.
Take chicken and pound thin between wax paper.
Take mixture and put ball of mixture in center of chicken.
Roll, dip in flour, egg and bread crumbs.
Place in baking pan close to each other and dot with butter.
Bake in 350° oven until brown, 30 to 40 minutes.

title: morgan's favorite holiday sugar cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine sugar and butter flavored Crisco in large bowl. Beat on medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Add eggs, syrup and vanilla.
Beat well.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Combine peanuts, sugar, syrup and salt in a 2-quart bowl. Microwave 8 minutes.
(Stir after 4 minutes.)
Stir in butter and vanilla.
Microwave for another 3 minutes.
Remove from oven and stir in soda.
Stir gently until light and foamy.
Pour onto foil-covered pan with butter and let cool.
Break into pieces and store in airtight container.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well together and spread on platter. Top with layer of salsa, lettuce, tomatoes, black olives and shredded cheese.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: scrumptious beef
directions: Place everything in a casserole.
Do not brown meat.
No need to mix.
Place, uncovered, in 300° oven for 6 hours (if meat is raw).
Serve with noodles, rice, potatoes or biscuits.
No need to add seasoning.

title: hamburger roll-up
directions: Combine all ingredients except bacon.
Form into a 10-inch roll.
Cover with bacon.
Refrigerate overnight.
Slice 1-inch thick.
Broil 6 to 8 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: sugar glazed peanuts or pecans
directions: Mix on top of stove on high until water evaporates.
Put in shallow pan and bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: quick fudge pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and melted oleo together.
Add eggs, milk, vanilla and pecans.
Mix well and pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: 24 hour chicken casserole
directions: Combine ingredients.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Serves 8.

title: ham appetillas
directions: Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise, green onions and olives; spread evenly on tortillas.
Arrange 4 ham slices over each tortilla; roll up tightly and wrap each individually in plastic wrap.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Cut tortillas into 1/2-inch slices.
Yields 8 1/2 dozen.

title: olde fashioned homemade burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into patties and fry in skillet with Pam or grill outdoors.
Place on toasted hamburger bun with your favorite condiments.

title: creole baked catfish
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and garlic in oil until tender.
Add tomatoes and tomato sauce and simmer 10 minutes.
Place catfish (salted and peppered) in oiled 3-quart casserole.
Pour sauce over all.
Cover and bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Great with green salad and hot garlic bread.

title: seafood casserole combo
directions: Heat frozen oyster stew in
2-quart
saucepan, stirring occasionally until thawed.	Simmer vegetables
in
another pan about 15 minutes or until tender.
Remove
oysters	from
stew and set aside.	Blend flour with water	until
smooth and add. Cook, stirring constantly until smooth
and
thickened.
Drain tuna and rinse off oil.
Add frozen	peas
and
heat
together gently for about 5 minutes or	until
peas
are
tender-crisp. Stir in Worcestershire sauce, sour cream and reserved oysters. Heat just to boiling point but don't boil.
Serve immediately. Makes 6 to 8 servings.
(Can use extra
oysters if you like; 1 can.)

title: diabetic easy baked apples
directions: Core apple, leaving bottom intact.
Peel about 1-inch around top.
Fill each apple with raisins and jelly; dash cinnamon over apples.
Pour 1-inch of water around base of apples.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes or until apples are tender at 350°.

title: pistachio cake(use 9 x 12-inch pan)
directions: Beat first 5 ingredients for 2 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cookie cups
directions: Freeze dough until firm, about an hour.

title: mom's quick meat
directions: Brown beef and onion in a skillet.
Drain off the grease.
Add the mushroom soup.
"Rinse" the can with about 1/4 can of milk and add to beef.
Simmer over low heat.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Serve over noodles or rice.

title: gadsby's sally lunn bread
directions: Butter cookie sheet.
Heat milk and shortening to the temperature of a warm baby bottle.
Mix flour, salt and sugar in a separate bowl.
Add the warm milk and melted shortening to the bowl of flour, salt and sugar.
Add the eggs, yeast and water. Beat the entire mixture until it comes off the side of the bowl which should be clean.
Cover; let rise in a warm place until double in size, about 1 1/2 hours.
Knead the bread down in size and shape into a round loaf.
Place on the cookie sheet and let rise again to 1/2 again as big, about 45 minutes.
Bake bread at 300° for approximately 45 minutes.
After 30 minutes, baste the top of the bread with butter and also again after it has finished baking.
Serves 8.
Preparation Time:

title: slush - great for luau
directions: Put dry ingredients in gallon size container.
Add enough hot water to dissolve.
When dissolved
well, add pineapple juice, then fill to gallon level with water.
Freeze and enjoy.
Can put chunks in blender to make a good slush consistency.

title: punch
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients; chill.
Add ginger ale when serving.
Some punch may be frozen in cubes or ring to prevent weakening when serving.

title: peach enchiladas
directions: Melt butter. Add sugar and cinnamon. Unroll crescent rolls. Place one peach slice on large end. Rollup. Place in a 12 x 10 x 2 baking dish. Pour butter mixture over top, then pour Mountain Dew over top. Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes or until golden brown. Best served warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: hamburger summer sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into 3 logs.
Wrap in aluminum foil and refrigerate overnight.
Place rolls on a cookie sheet and poke several holes in the bottom of each roll so juices will drain. Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Cool and slice.

title: pat taylor's sugar cookies
directions: Combine shortening, salt, lemon rind, nutmeg, sugar and eggs. Beat until smooth.
Sift flour, baking powder and baking soda. Add to shortening mixture and blend.
Add milk and mix well. Measure level tablespoons of dough onto greased baking sheet. Flatten cookies with a flat bottom glass covered with a damp cloth.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake in 350° oven.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: chicken salad
directions: Sprinkle French dressing over chicken.
Cover and let stand in refrigerator at least 1 hour.
Add mayonnaise.
Mix thoroughly. Serve on lettuce.
Garnish as desired.
To vary, add diced celery or canned artichokes, cut small.
A delicious combo is chicken, cubed cucumber, chopped nutmeats and tiny canned peas.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add oil, squash and vanilla.
Mix well; add dry ingredients and blend.
Add nuts and raisins.
Pour into 2 well-greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 325°. Remove from pans at once.

title: marie's cornflake cookies
directions: Bake in oven at 350 degrees for 10 minutes.

title: chicken cordon blue
directions: Slice a pocket in the underside of each chicken breast. Insert a slice of ham and a slice of cheese in each pocket.
Close pocket; dredge chicken breasts in flour, dip in eggs, and coat with breadcrumbs.
In skillet, heat oil and fry chick on both sides until done.
Makes 2 servings.

title: chicken and biscuits
directions: Cook the first 5 ingredients 10 minutes.
Add the paprika on top and simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Sprinkle parsley on top.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: Whisk eggs with oil and molasses.
Add zucchini and vanilla and mix.
Combine flour, sugar, cinnamon, salt, baking soda and baking powder.
Add to wet ingredients and mix until moistened. Don't overmix.
Dredge raisins and walnuts in flour and add to batter; fold in.
Pour into 2 greased 9 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: "texas" hash
directions: Brown beef in skillet and drain off excess fat.
Put all ingredients in crock-pot.
Stir thoroughly.
Cover and cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.

title: swedish nuts
directions: Toast nuts in slow oven (325°) until light brown.
Fold sugar into egg whites; beat until stiff peaks form.
Fold nuts into meringue.
Melt margarine in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread nut mixture over margarine.
Bake in slow oven for about 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes, or until nuts are coated with brown covering and no butter remains in the pan.
Cool.
Makes about 4 cups.

title: microwave cinnamon candy
directions: Mix together the sugar and syrup in microwave bowl.
Cook on High 4 minutes.
Stir and cook for 3 to 5 more minutes.
Add cinnamon and red food coloring.
Stir and pour onto greased cookie sheet.
Cool and break into pieces.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together in a
bowl
until well blended.
Form ball and roll in paprika and pecans until covered.
Can add a green leaf for decoration.

title: mashed potatoes supreme
directions: Beat all together until fluffy; put in a buttered casserole dish.
Drizzle a little melted butter on top of it.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Take cover off for the last 10 to 15 minutes.

title: stuffed mushroom caps
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms.
Wash caps and stems.
Set aside caps.
Chop stems and saute in butter with Chablis, garlic cloves and salt and pepper to taste.
Set aside to cool.

title: mrs. cates potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets until tender.
Run cold water over potatoes and peel.
Cut up in small cubes.
Add chopped celery, pickles and onion.
Add mayonnaise, a little pickle juice and sugar.
Add salt and pepper.
Place in bowl and cover overnight or for several hours in refrigerator.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Combine oil, milk and vinegar.
Mix dry ingredients together and then pour liquid ingredients over the dry ingredients.
Add egg and vanilla.
Beat 4 minutes.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Makes 3 layers or large sheet cake.
The cake is moist.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar, and flour together and put in boiling water.
Stir until gravy like.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.

title: sorry cake
directions: Mix well and bake in 9 x 13-inch well-greased and floured pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: easy swiss steak
directions: Cook steak with flour; lightly salt and pepper.
Coat a skillet with shortening and quickly sear steak on both sides until brown.
Dice onion into tomato juice and put a small amount into the bottom of a glass baking dish.
Add the browned steak and the rest of the tomato juice and onions by layers.
Bake in a 375° oven for 1 hour or until steak is tender enough to pull apart easily with a fork.
(Can also be microwaved in 15 to 20 minutes.)

title: golden bubble ring
directions: Soften dry yeast in warm water.
Combine milk, shortening, 1/2 cup sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add 1 cup flour and beat well.
Add yeast mixture and eggs; beat smooth.
Mix in remaining flour or enough to make a soft dough., Knead on lightly floured surface until smooth and elastic, 8 to 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl, turning once to grease surface.
Cover and let rise in warm place until double, 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down.
Cover and let rest 10 minutes.

title: carnival caramel corn
directions: Combine brown sugar, corn syrup and butter and bring to a boil.
Boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in peanuts. Pour boiling mixture over popped corn and spread on greased baking sheets and bake at 225° for 45 minutes.
When cool enough to handle, remove from baking sheet and break into pieces.
Store in covered container.
Great for halloween!

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Mix shortening, brown sugar and sugar until creamy.
Add egg and vanilla to mixture.
In another bowl, mix flour, soda and cinnamon.
Put raisins into a small pan.
Pour water in the raisins until they are covered.
Heat until the raisins are plump.
Now take your flour mixture and add half to your sugar mixture, then take your 1/4 cup of water from off the cooked raisins and pour it into sugar mixture.
Then add the rest of the flour mix.
After well blended, add oats and stir in drained raisins.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: stuffed celery
directions: Combine ingredients and fill celery stalks that's been washed and dried.
Cut to desired lengths.

title: chicken kapama
directions: Cut chicken into serving pieces.
Sprinkle with lemon juice, cinnamon, salt and pepper.
Brown chicken in butter.
Remove from flame.
Saute onion and garlic.

title: coconut oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift flour, salt, baking powder and soda together.
Cream shortening, add sugars gradually and cream together until light and fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla and beat well.
Add flour, oats and coconut and mix thoroughly.
Shape dough into small balls and place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen cookies.

title: shrimp and pasta salad
directions: The night before, arrange onion, dill pickle, black olives, shrimp and green olives in layers, starting with the diced onion. On the following day, cook macaroni; drain and stir in some pickle juice, tossing several times to allow flavor to blend in.
You should have about 3 cups of the macaroni.
Add remaining ingredients to the macaroni and then combine all with the first mixture, stirring lightly.
Cool several hours or overnight.

title: baked pyrizhky
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients; let rise 40 to 50 minutes.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Knead dough well.
Take half dough and roll out to little less than 1/4-inch thick.
With glass about 3-inches in diameter, cut out dough.
Put about 1 tablespoon filling in center of circles.
Fold over; pinch edges together well and form into a crescent.
Put stuffed crescents on well-greased cookie sheet and let rise 1 hour.
Brush tops with melted margarine and bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Recipe can be halved.

title: apple crumb squares
directions: Peel, core and slice apples.
Mix with 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Arrange pie crust in a 9-inch square pan to cover bottom and 1/2 inch up sides.
Pour apple mixture in crust. Mix remaining ingredients; sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Lower heat to 350°; bake 30 minutes more.
Delicious with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well and drop onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen medium cookies.

title: lo-cal zucchini soup(hot or cold)
directions: Slice onion in butter and cook until glossy.
Add 1/2 cup water, sliced zucchini and chopped parsley.
Season with bouillon, salt and basil.
Cook over low heat for a few minutes until vegetables are soft.
Turn into blender and puree.
Add 1 cup skim or 1/2 percent milk and heat to serve or you can put in the refrigerator for an hour or two for cold soup.

title: fancy fruits
directions: Layer fruits in dish.
Combine pudding mix and Tang.
Sprinkle mixture over fruit.
Cover and chill for 24 hours.
Stir several times.

title: walnut cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together until they can be handled with hands.
Make into rolls and refrigerate overnight.
Slice and bake in hot oven at 350 degrees.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Peel and grate potatoes.
Add egg, onion, baking powder, flour, salt and pepper.
Fry like pancakes on hot griddle.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large skillet. Cook over medium-high heat; turn chicken until evenly cooked, approximately 45 to 60 minutes. The sauce will thicken into a tangy, sweet sauce.

title: vina's salmon puffs
directions: Mix all ingredients in order listed.
Drop by tablespoonfuls into deep fryer.
Fry until golden brown; drain.

title: classic lasagne
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Steam zucchini over boiling water until tender-crisp, about 5 minutes.
Drain.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter together.
Add eggs and sour cream, mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Flour may be added for easier handling.
Let dough stand all night in refrigerator.
Roll out and bake in oven of 350° for 8 minutes.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Put soup, milk, oleo and Cheez Whiz in saucepan over low heat. Stir occasionally.
When mix is hot (not boiling), add rice and broccoli; let stand for a while.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes. Stir occasionally; do not let boil.

title: meusli
directions: Mix in large roasting pan or baking pan the first 7 ingredients; set aside.
Heat together in saucepan the honey and oil.
Pour over cereal mixture; mix well.
Bake in a slow oven, 300°, for 20 minutes or longer.
Stir often.
The longer the cooking time, the darker and crispier the mixture becomes.
When cool, add 4 ounces raisins or other dried fruit.
Store in airtight container to maintain freshness.

title: jello pinwheels
directions: You can double this recipe.
Use large package of Jell-O and double water and marshmallows.

title: 20 minute (more or less) tamale pie
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add tomatoes, corn with liquid, sour cream, corn meal, olives and seasonings.
Stir until thoroughly mixed.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: sweet and sour red cabbage
directions: Brown sausage and onion in skillet. Remove.
In the same skillet, cook apple and cabbage in 1/4 cup water for 5 minutes. Return sausage and onion to skillet.
Add vinegar, wine, salt, pepper and butter or margarine. Cover and simmer for 10 minutes. Serves 6.

title: butter pecan ice cream
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, evaporated milk, flavoring and pudding well. Add
pecans and butter.
Pour in freezer bucket and add milk. Freeze and enjoy.

title: brown sugar drop cookies
directions: Cream together the oleo, lard and brown sugar.
Stir together the eggs, milk, soda, baking powder, salt and vanilla.
Add the flour to this mixture.
Mix the flour mixture and cream mixture together.

title: stupendous, tomato beef stew
directions: Dust meat with flour.
Brown in shortening in large heavy pan. Add soup and water; cover, simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover, cook 1 hour or until vegetables are tender. Stir now and then.
Uncover and cook down to desired thickness.

title: cheerios snacks
directions: Cook Karo and sugar until bubbly.
Add the peanut butter and Cheerios.
Shape into balls.

title: jolly pops
directions: Boil to 300°.
Add food coloring and oil flavoring of your choice (1/2 to 1 teaspoon).
Pour into small oiled muffin or cupcake pans.
Set popsicle sticks in each.
Let cool.

title: pecan rolls
directions: Mix white sugar, brown sugar, cinnamon and pecan pieces in shallow bowl.
Dip each biscuit into the melted butter and then coat with sugar mixture.
Dribble any remaining butter and sugar mixture over top of biscuits.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes or until tops are golden brown.
Serve hot.

title: quick cinnamon buns
directions: Let bread thaw but not rise.
Break one loaf into pieces and toss into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover with brown sugar mixture and sprinkle with nuts, raisins and cinnamon. Break up second loaf and toss on top of mixture.
Let rise until double (about 2 hours).
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Invert onto platter.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix after each item.

title: prune puree
directions: Blend together in blender on high speed.
Use immediately or store in fridge for 3 weeks.
Purchase lecithin granules at health food stores.

title: lazy daisy cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour an 8-inch pan.
Beat the eggs until thick.
Add the sugar; beat well.
Add the vanilla. Sift together the sifted flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to first mixture.
Heat to boiling point the milk and shortening. Add all at once to mixture; heat well.
Pour into prepared pan; bake for 30 minutes.

title: mamie eisenhower's fudge
directions: Break bars into small pieces in a large bowl. Add chocolate chips, nuts and marshmallow.
In a pan, cook the sugar, butter, salt and milk until it comes to a rolling boil.
Boil 6 minutes. Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan and a square pan.
Pour hot liquid over chocolate mixture.
Mix and pour into pans.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion and margarine.
Mix together with all other ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 350° until it begins to brown, about 30 minutes.

title: tortillas
directions: Mix flour, shortening and warm water.
Add a little at a time until consistency of pie dough.
Knead 50 times.
Divide into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Put in a bowl and cover with a cloth for 20 minutes.
Roll out thin.
Fry in hot skillet 10 to 15 minutes each side.
Serves 20.

title: corn dogs
directions: Combine corn meal, flour and salt.
Add milk, egg and oil; mix well.
Insert wooden skewers in one end of each hot dog.
Coat with additional flour; dip into corn meal mixture.
Fry a few at a time in deep hot (375°) oil, until brown.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Combine all ingredients, except carrots, in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Pour over carrots.
Refrigerate and serve cold.

title: broccoli, rice, chicken & cheese casserole
directions: If using chicken tenderloins, cook and cut into bite-size pieces.
Cook broccoli and drain.
Combine chicken and broccoli with 1 c. cheese and remaining ingredients.
Pour into 2 qt. baking dish.
Bake at 325° for about 30 minutes.
Top with remaining 1 c. cheddar cheese and bake long enough to melt cheese.

title: chocolate dessert
directions: Mix flour and melted butter together; add pecans to mixture. In bottom of glass oblong baking dish, layer the mixture to form a crust.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Remove and cool.

title: pina colada cake
directions: In sheet cake pan, bake cake according to directions on box. After it is cool, punch holes all over cake with ice pick.
Mix creamed coconut and Eagle Brand milk together and pour onto cake, a little at a time and all the liquid is absorbed into the cake. Cover with Saran Wrap and refrigerate for 8 hours.
Frost with Cool Whip and sprinkle with coconut.
At Christmas, you can add red or green cherries to the top for color.

title: barbecued turkey-burgers(excellent)
directions: Combine first 10 ingredients listed.
Cook for 10 minutes. Add turkey; simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve on buttered buns. Serves 10.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken; take off bones and put aside.
Save broth.
Melt margarine and stir into dressing.
In a greased 13 x 9-inch dish, put a layer of dressing and layer of chicken.
Pour celery soup, diluted with 1 can of chicken broth, over all.
Repeat using chicken soup, diluted with broth.
Top with crumbs and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until brown.

title: sourdough hot cakes
directions: About 12 hours before serving, mix starter, flour, milk and salt.
Let stand in a cheese covered bowl in a warm place.
Just before baking, remove 1 cup batter to replenish sourdough in crock, to the remaining batter, add soda, eggs, shortening and sugar.

title: broccoli au gratin
directions: Cook vegetables; drain.
Place in shallow baking dish (10 x 6 x 2-inches).
Stir soup; blend in milk.
Pour over vegetables.
Top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until hot.
Garnish with bacon before serving.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: easy everything cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together; drop by spoonful onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Melt butter in large casserole dish. Combine all other ingredients and mix lightly.
Add to butter and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Clean mushrooms.
Slice and fry in butter.
Open green beans (drain off liquid).
Place in baking dish.
Add mushrooms and soup and mix.
Top with onions.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini crescent pie
directions: Cook and stir zucchini and onions in margarine for 10 minutes. Stir in parsley, salt, pepper, garlic powder and oregano.
Beat 2 eggs and add cheese.
Add to zucchini mixture.
Separate crescent rolls into 8 triangles and place in 9-inch ungreased pie pan, joining edges together.
Spread mustard over crust, then pour in zucchini.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: apple crunch
directions: Place apples in greased, shallow baking dish (2-quart casserole).
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Combine dry ingredients, add melted butter, mixing until crumbly.
Sprinkle crumb mixture on top of apples.
Bake in a moderate oven at 375° for 30 minutes or until apples are tender.
Serve warm or cold with ice cream or whipped cream.
If apples are very tart, sweeten slightly.
Serves 6.

title: "simple strawberry cake"(just mix by hand, don't bother with the mixer)
directions: *I use Hodgeson's unbleached plain, for everything.

title: peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: In a bowl, stir together flour and baking soda.
In a large mixer bowl, beat margarine with electric mixer on medium speed for 30 seconds.
Add peanut butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Beat until fluffy.
Add carrot, egg whites and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients to beaten mixture.
Beat until well combined.
Stir in oats.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart onto a nongreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 375° oven about 10 minutes or until done.
Remove cookies from cookie sheet.
Cool on wire rack. Makes 48 cookies (24 servings).

title: low-fat french fries
directions: Cut potatoes lengthwise into thin wedges.
Place in a plastic bag.
Spray wedges lightly with coating.
Add Parmesan cheese and paprika to bag; toss to coat wedges.

title: chicken with oyster sauce
directions: Cut chicken into bite-size pieces and coat with flour.
Heat shortening and garlic, then add chicken.
Stir until brown on high heat.

title: easy frozen bread caramel rolls
directions: Thaw, but do not permit to rise, 2 loaves of bread.
Break 1 loaf up in chunks. Place in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Melt butter.
Add brown sugar, pudding mix, milk and cinnamon. Mix all together, then pour 1/2 of mixture over broken bread in pan. Break second loaf on top and pour remaining caramel mixture over broken bread.
Let rise 2 1/2 to 3 hours. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Turn out of pan on tinfoil.
Nuts and raisins may also be added.

title: butterscotch meringue pie
directions: Combine sugars with flour in a heavy saucepan.
Add hot milk gradually.
Add salt and cook over low heat, stirring constantly, to make a smooth mixture.
Continue cooking, stirring occasionally, 15 minutes, until thickened.
Pour some hot mixture into the egg yolks, stirring constantly.
Pour back into the pan; mix well and cook 3 minutes longer.
Add butter, stirring to melt.
Cool.
Add vanilla and pour into baked crust.

title: cajun potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in water wtih shrimp and crab boil seasoning packet. Saute chopped onion in melted butter.
Pour over cooked and drained potatoes.
Add sour cream and cheese; mash together. Serve hot or at room temperature.

title: pasta salad
directions: Boil noodles 10 to 15 minutes or until soft.
While noodles are boiling, prepare other ingredients.
Drain noodles; pour into a large bowl.
Add other ingredients.
When cool, add cheese. Keep chilled.

title: quick chocolate sheet cake
directions: Bring first four ingredients to boil.
Let boil a few minutes and put in mixing bowl.
Add flour, sugar and soda; mix.
Add milk and vinegar; mix.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix and pour on greased and floured cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: pink salad
directions: Let jello and hot water thicken (will not take long).
Mix cream cheese and sugar together.
Beat this mixture into jello and fold in nuts, Cool Whip and pineapple.

title: orange julius
directions: Blend on high for about 45 seconds until blended.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Dice chicken breasts. Saute them in rosemary, garlic and olive oil. When brown, add mushroom soup. Mix and cook for 3 to 5 minutes. Make stuffing mix. Spray round casserole dish. Layer a casserole dish with chicken mix, stuffing, cracker mix, stuffing and top with grated cheese. Bake
at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: veal scallopini
directions: Veal should be about 1/4-inch thick.
Cover cutlet with cheese, salt and pepper.
Brown meat in oil.
Add garlic.
Add wine, consomme, lemon juice, spices, parsley and mushrooms.
Cover skillet and simmer 45 minutes.
Serve over cooked buttered noodles.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake brownies according to directions; cool.
Punch holes in brownies; pour coffee over brownies.
Set aside.
Whip up chocolate mousse according to directions.
Break candy bars into small pieces in food processor or by tapping them with a hammer. Break 1/2 brownies and place in trifle dish.
Cover with 1/2 of the mousse; layer with 1/2 candy, then add 1/2 whipped topping. Repeat layers with remaining ingredients.

title: ranch style salad dressing
directions: Mix everything together with an electric mixer.
Refrigerate overnight to be used the next day.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes until done. Cut 1/4 off lengthwise. Scoop out potato into bowl; mash well. Add oleo; mix in sour cream, pepper to taste, several shakes of Parmesan cheese and about 2 teaspoons bacon bits. Place mashed potato mixture into potato skins. Put potatoes in baking pan; bake at 350° for 10 to 20 additional minutes or until warm.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients except ketchup and soy sauce.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat then add them.
Get mixture hot and remove from heat.

title: layer bar cookies
directions: Melt butter in 13 x 9 x 2 inch pan.
Sprinkle crumbs evenly over butter.
Layer with chocolate and butterscotch chips, coconut, and nuts.
Pour milk over all.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Cool. Cut into bars.

title: victoria creams
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1/2 cup water.
Heat cream and sugar just before boiling.
Add gelatin.
Remove from heat.
Add sour cream. Stir until smooth.
Add vanilla extract.
Mold in individual (plain) salad molds.
Refrigerate until molded.
Serve or top with raspberry or strawberry syrup.
This makes enough for about 25 to 30 servings.
Elegant.

title: miss stella magee's raisin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° until done.
Can bake in muffin tins or frozen pie tart shells.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes until lightly brown.

title: wacky cake
directions: Stir dry ingredients into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch ungreased pan. Level off and punch 3 holes into mixture with back of spoon.
Into one hole pour the vinegar, into another the oil and into third vanilla.
Pour water over all and stir thoroughly with a fork. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done when tested with toothpick.
When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar or frost or use Cool Whip or ice cream.
Can be doubled and baked in an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: sausage pie
directions: Cook sausage; drain and crumble.
Mix cheese and sausage together and sprinkle into pie shell.
In another bowl, combine all other ingredients, then stir into egg.
Pour into shell over sausage.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish and place slightly thawed potatoes in dish.
Mix remaining ingredients in bowl and pour over potatoes.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: senate bean soup
directions: Wash beans and soak overnight in large kettle.
Next morning, add water to make 5 quarts.
Add bone and simmer 2 hours or until beans begin to fall apart.
Simmer 1 hour longer after adding potato, onion, celery and garlic.
Remove bone.
Cut up meat; return to soup.
Season to taste.
Makes 4 1/2 quarts of soup.

title: honey dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix until blended.
Also good served over broiled chicken. Serve with assorted vegetables.

title: beefy noodle soup
directions: Brown beef, onion and oil. Add water, bouillon, bay leaf, basil and pepper. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, 1 hour.
Add carrots, celery and tomatoes. Cook 30 to 45 minutes. Stir in noodles. Cook until tender, about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: chicken breasts in curried cream sauce
directions: Cut the chicken strips about 1/2-inch wide. Melt the butter in a skillet and when it is hot, add the chicken pieces. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Stir until chicken strips lose their raw look. Add shallots and curry powder. Stir to blend and cook about 1 minute. Transfer chicken to a bowl. Add the wine to the skillet and cook over high heat about 3 minutes or until reduced to about 1/4 cup. Add any juices that have accumulated in the bowl containing the chicken. Add the cream to the skillet and cook over high heat about 4 minutes. Add the chicken and stir to blend well. Serve over rice. Makes 4 servings.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Garnish hot soup with Parmesan cheese or cold soup with sour cream.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown hamburger and drain. Add Velveeta cheese, tomatoes and green chilies and Tabasco sauce. Stir until cheese is melted.
Put in crock-pot. Serve with king size corn chips.

title: empanadas
directions: Roll biscuits flat.
Take egg and brush on flat biscuits. Brown ground beef; drain.
Mix all ingredients well.
Spoon on center of biscuit.
Fold over and press edges with a fork.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes on baking sheet.

title: scalloped squash supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 2-quart casserole.
Wash squash and slice into 1-inch pieces.
Cook squash and chopped onion until tender, approximately 10 minutes.
Drain.
Combine egg, pepper, milk, butter, salt, fresh crumbs and cup of cheese.
Arrange squash and onion in casserole and pour egg mixture over them.
Sprinkle top with remaining cup of cheese.
Add a dash of paprika for bits of color.
Bake 30 minutes.
Makes 6 luscious servings.

title: cream cheese whipped topping pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip, and sugar until smooth.
Pour into pie crust, then top with blueberries.
Chill and serve.

title: goat milk ice cream(vanilla)
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Stir and cook them over low heat, or in double boiler, until about to boil.
Remove from heat and cool.
Put in ice cream freezer following directions for the freezing machine you have.
May add fruit to mixture.
We like to add strawberries.
May add chocolate syrup, but use only 1 tablespoon vanilla.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs with mixer.
Stir in sugar, oil, zucchini and vanilla.
Combine flour, salt, cinnamon, baking soda and baking powder in a separate bowl.
Add to egg/zucchini mixture; mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan or two greased 8 x 4-inch loaf pans.
Bake for 1 hour to 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool.
Store 1 to 2 days before serving.

title: freezer salad
directions: Combine white vinegar, sugar, water and celery seed in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Stir occasionally.
Remove from heat and cool.
Put broccoli and other ingredients in a bowl.
Add the vinegar mixture and toss.
Makes 4 (1 pints) or 8 cups.
Put this in refrigerator for 8 hours before serving.
Can freeze for 1 month and take out and let thaw before serving.

title: oven broiled chicken
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Prepare cracker crumbs and flour.
Salt chicken and roll in crumb mixture.
Lay in pan skin side up.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes, turn and bake 35 minutes.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Heat sugar, vinegar, oil, celery seed, salt and pepper together until sugar is dissolved.
Cool sauce.
Pour over vegetables. Cover and marinate overnight.
Shake or stir and serve.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine.
Mix in graham crumbs.
Pat mixture in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: layer cookies
directions: Use 11 x 12-inch oblong glass baking dish that has been greased with butter.
Layer 1 graham cracker crust made of the following:
6 tablespoons butter, 3 tablespoons sugar and 16 graham crackers (crushed).
Mix and press into dish.

title: fig jam
directions: Mix all ingredients in a saucepan.
Boil 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour in glass jars.
Cover with 1/8-inch of paraffin.

title: peggy's spinach dip
directions: Mix well and chill until served.

title: gravy baked pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare and brown pork chops on both sides.
Drain.
Mix soup, milk and water; pour over chops.
Bake for 45 minutes or until tender.
Remove chops and stir gravy well.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Pour boiling water over jello.
Add sour cream and blend until smooth.
Stir in pineapple and salt.
Place in a bowl and refrigerate.

title: quick blueberry muffins
directions: In a medium bowl, mix ice cream and flour. Add butter and sugar. Fold in blueberries. Stir until mixed well. Spoon into six or eight muffin cups.

title: broiled fish almondine
directions: Place fish on greased broiler pan; brush with 1 tablespoon shortening.
Place fish about 4 inches from broiler unit; broil about 5 minutes.
Turn; brush with remaining shortening and broil about 4 minutes longer or until fish flakes easily with a fork. Season with salt and pepper.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Bring to a boil the sugar, cocoa, butter and milk, stirring constantly.
Cool; add vanilla.
Using a mixer, gradually add powdered sugar until smooth.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash.
Drain and mash.
Add margarine, soup, sour cream and onion.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: low-fat cheese cake(easy)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Work with hands into baking dish.

title: lemon supreme cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together, then add 1 egg at a time, beating well after each egg is added.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.
Do not open oven while baking.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash and onions until tender.
Add salt to taste. Drain.

title: hot dog manicotti
directions: Boil manicotti noodles until done.
(Do not overcook.) Drain and set aside.
Slice each hot dog lengthwise, being careful not to cut completely through.
Half each slice of cheese and fold lengthwise.
Stuff each hot dog with 1/2 folded cheese slice, then stuff each manicotti shell with hot dog.
Cover bottom of baking pan with chili.
Line stuffed manicotti over chili, then cover with remaining chili.
Cover and bake at 375° for 45 minutes. Remove cover and bake another 15 minutes.
(You may sprinkle shredded Mozzarella or Cheddar cheese on top during final 15 minutes of baking.)
This recipe is a real wiener!

title: layered beef and zucchini
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease square baking dish, 8 x 8 x 2-inch. Cook and stir ground beef in skillet until brown; drain.
Place zucchini slices in single layer in baking dish.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup baking mix.
Top with beef and spaghetti sauce.
Mix 1 cup baking mix, cottage cheese and egg until soft dough forms.
Spread over sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake, uncovered, until hot and bubbly, about 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: polynesian vegetables
directions: In skillet, combine preserves, vinegar, soy sauce, ginger, garlic powder and 3/4 teaspoon salt.
Add peppers and onions. Cover and cook (stirring occasionally) until vegetables are tender but crisp.
Add tomatoes and pineapple.
Heat through and serve.

title: my favorite salad dressing
directions: Mix together in a jar and shake well.
Let stand out of refrigerator overnight.
Shake vigorously often.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat oil, sugar and eggs until well blended.
In a bowl, stir together flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and cloves.
Add to sugar mixture.
Drain the pineapple.
Add carrots, walnuts and pineapple to mixture.
Blend to mix well.
Pour batter into greased and floured 9 or 10-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Cool Cake.
Prepare frosting.

title: peach salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add pineapple and strained peaches.
Whip together softened cream cheese and condensed milk. Stir into jello mixture and combine.
Congeal in a mold.
Sprinkle chopped pecans when served, if desired.

title: chinese fried walnuts
directions: About 1 1/2 hours before serving or up to 2 weeks ahead: In a 4-quart saucepan, over high heat, heat water to boiling.
Add walnuts and heat to boiling; cook 1 minute.
Rinse walnuts under running hot water; drain.
Wash saucepan and dry well.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix together thoroughly the sugar, Crisco and eggs.
Stir in buttermilk and bananas.
Add self-rising flour and soda.
Beat until mixed well.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Let stand 20 minutes before baking.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: poor man's cobbler
directions: Pour butter in 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Mix together Bisquick, sugar and milk.
Pour batter over melted butter.
Pour fruit over batter and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: low calorie banana bread
directions: In large bowl, mix flour, oats, corn meal and wheat germ.
Add rest of ingredients and stir well. Pour into two greased and floured loaf pans. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until done. Makes 2 loaves with 155 calories per slice.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix first four ingredients, beat well.	Add flavorings.
Mix flour, salt, soda and add to first mixture.
Add sour cream and mix well.
Pour into tube pan and bake at 350° about 15 to 20 minutes.
Then bake at 325° about 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chicken tenders
directions: *This cheese mixture comes in a can (like Parmesan cheese).

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Drain fat.
Mix all dry ingredients.
Coat chicken in mixture.
Melt butter in baking dish.
Place chicken, skin side down.
Drain fat from pan, turn chicken.
Bake chicken 45 minutes or until thickest pieces are done.
Once chicken has been turned, reduce oven to 375°.

title: sweet-sour beef 'n' cabbage
directions: In skillet, cook beef, onion, celery and green pepper until meat is browned.
Drain off excess fat.
Sprinkle meat mixture with oats, parsley, the 3/4 teaspoon salt, garlic powder and the 1/8 teaspoon pepper.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix and make into 6 patties the hamburger, bread crumbs, salt, pepper, egg and 1/4 of the onion soup. Brown the meat on both sides and pour off the excess fat.

title: italian pasta bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef (with seasonings) in skillet.
Add onion and green pepper to meat when lightly browned. Cook meat until done.
Drain.
Cook macaroni as package directs and drain.
Mix Cheddar and Mozzarella cheeses and halve.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Cook unpeeled potatoes.
Cool, peel and shred.
Melt oleo and cheese.
Blend in sour cream, onions, salt and pepper.
Fold in potatoes.
Put in buttered casserole dish; dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: tyler's chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken 20 to 25 minutes or until done. Mix vegetables, soup and milk. Chop chicken in to bite size pieces and add to mixture. Put mixture in a 9x12 inch greased baking dish. Place biscuits, one at a time, on top of mixture and bake at 325 degrees for 30 minutes or until biscuits are browned.

title: play dough for children
directions: Heat together until ingredients form ball.
Add food coloring if desired.
Work it in until all is soft and pliable.
Keep tightly closed when not in use.

title: rum balls
directions: Mix crushed vanilla wafers
with icing sugar, cocoa and walnuts.
Add rum, corn syrup and water.
Mix well and let stand for awhile.
Form mixture into 1-inch balls and roll in fruit sugar.
Store in a cool place.

title: tortellini pasta salad
directions: In bowl, mix all ingredients, except Parmesan cheese. Stir well, coating everything with Italian dressing. Refrigerate overnight, stirring 3 or 4 times before going to bed. Next day, add Parmesan cheese before serving.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening, and sugar until light and fluffy. Add lemon and vanilla extract and blend well. Add eggs one at a time and continue beating after each addition. Sift together flour, baking powder and salt; Add alternate to cream mixture with milk. Pour into large tube pan. Bake in 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours, or until cake tests done.

title: straw hat casserole
directions: Lightly grease an 11 x 14-inch baking dish or 2-quart casserole dish.
Layer tortilla chips, unwrapped tamales, chili, cheese and onions.
Cover and bake for 45 minutes at 375°.
Serves 6.

title: sauerkraut casserole
directions: Arrange kraut in greased baking dish.
Spread sugar over kraut.
Spread tomatoes over sugar.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with bacon crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let cool before serving.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 11 to 13 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: fruit dip
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature; mix.
Store in covered container in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Slice chicken (or turkey) breasts and put in buttered 8-inch pan.
Cover with a layer of cheese, then pour soup and milk mixture over all.
Top with dressing.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: *ravani 1
directions: Beat egg whites (room temperature) until stiff.
In a separate bowl, cream the butter and sugar 5 minutes on medium speed.
Add egg yolks.
Beat 5 minutes more until light and fluffy.

On low speed alternately beat in flour mixture with milk and vanilla mixture, blending until smooth. Blend in egg whites, beaten stiff. Add 3/4 cup nuts. Divide in two 9 x 9-inch pans or one oblong 10 x 15-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.

title: yummy tater chicken
directions: Wash and dry chicken.
Mix cheese and potatoes together.
Dip in chicken or shake in bag.
Place in baking pan.
Pour over with butter.
Bake 1/2 hour at 325° to 350°.

title: fried zucchini
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Peel zucchini and chop into 1/4-inch slices.
Add to onion and mix in soy sauce.
Fry until zucchini is tender (about 15 minutes).

title: baked beans
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain.
Reserve 2 tablespoons drippings.
Crumble bacon.
Cook onion in reserve drippings until tender, but not brown.
Add with crumbled bacon to remaining ingredients mixing well.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart bean pot or casserole dish.
Bake uncovered at 350° about 2 hours.
Serves 6.

title: mexican layer dip
directions: Spread the beans on a large platter. Mix sour cream, Miracle Whip and taco seasoning together and spread over beans. Layer the green onions, then the green chiles and tomatoes on top of sour cream mixture. Spread cheese over top to cover.

title: mud slide
directions: Mix all crust ingredients.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let crust cool.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Sprinkle pecans and chocolate over bottom of pie shell.

title: frozen salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, using juice from fruit cocktail with cream cheese,
first.
Then add remaining ingredients. Pour in loaf pan and freeze.
May be sliced and served on lettuce leaf.

title: easy enchilada casserole
directions: Cut tortillas into strips.
Mix the cans of chicken, mushroom soup and chilies in a bowl.
Mix the grated Cheddar and Jack cheeses in another bowl.
Put a layer of soup mixture on the bottom of the casserole dish.
Put a layer of the tortilla strips in the dish.
Cover with a layer of soup mix.
Sprinkle on cheeses.
Repeat tortillas, soup mixture and top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: steaks in wine sauce
directions: Brown steaks in a frying pan; season with seasoned salt, garlic salt, and/or pepper as desired.
Remove steaks from pan and drain off fat.
Add 1 tablespoon butter and several minced green onions to pan; cook for about 1 minute.
Add 1/2 cup dry sherry and boil down.
Remove from heat and beat in some butter.
Season with pepper and parsley, as desired (and salt if necessary). Serve over steaks.

title: pineapple cheesecake
directions: Drain pineapple well.
