Prepare Dream Whip according to directions. Blend in cream cheese and powdered sugar until smooth. Add pineapple and stir well.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill until set.

title: banana split
directions: Line long Pyrex dish with whole graham crackers.
Beat eggs well; add powdered sugar and margarine.
Mix well.
Spread over graham crackers.
Add a layer of sliced bananas.
Spread pineapple over the bananas.
Spread Cool Whip and sprinkle nuts and cherries on top.

title: pineapple beets
directions: Drain syrup from pineapple and mix with water and vinegar. Combine the brown sugar, cornstarch, salt and ginger.
Blend the two mixtures.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add beets and heat.
Add pineapple chunks.
Serve hot or cold.

title: raspberry mousse
directions: Mix well and set in freezer until jelled.
Mix in Cool Whip; whip with hand mixer or wire whisk.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and freeze.

title: garden supper casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix bread cubes, cheese and 2 tablespoons butter; spread half the mixture in a greased 1-quart casserole and top with peas.
Cook and stir onion in 3 tablespoons butter until onion is tender.
Blend in flour and seasonings; cook over low heat, stirring until mixture is bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in milk; heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.

title: cheese ball
directions: Beat cream cheese with mustard and wine until smooth.
Add olives and Cheddar cheese.
Form into ball.
Wrap in waxed paper and chill.
Roll in sunflower nuts or finely chopped walnuts before serving.
(Nice to keep on hand during holidays for "drop-in" visitors.)

title: african drumsticks
directions: In a small bowl, combine tomato sauce, cola, chutney and red pepper flakes.
Spread mixture on drumsticks and grill or broil according to package direction (usually 15 to 20 minutes), turning frequently.

title: appetizer pie
directions: Combine cream cheese and milk.
Add smoked beef, onion, green pepper and pepper; mix well.
Add sour half and half.
Spread into an 8-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle nuts over top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: white chocolate crunch
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Pour melted chocolate morsels over mixture. Mix well. Press onto a cookie sheet. Freeze for 10 minutes. Break up into pieces (chunks).

title: sugar-free banana bread
directions: Combine ingredients in order given. Pour into a loaf pan sprayed with nonstick cooking spray. Bake about 2 hours at 350°.

title: teddy's cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, grated Cheddar cheese and cheese spread. Add Worcestershire sauce, salt, onion and
lemon juice.
Form into a ball.
Chill at least 1 hour before serving.
Roll ball in pecans or chipped dried beef.

title: chop suey
directions: Combine meat and all vegetables in large frying pan, browning meat and vegetables.
Add soy and Worcestershire sauce, bean sprouts and cream of mushroom soup.
Let simmer for about 45 minutes.
Good over rice or noodles.

title: blueberry and rhubarb pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix the sugar, flour, cinnamon and salt. Stir into blueberries and rhubarb.
Turn into pastry lined pie pan; dot with butter.
Cover with top crust.
Bake for 25 minutes. Reduce heat to 375°; bake 10 to 20 minutes longer.

title: green beans a la moore
directions: Combine butter and crumbs.
Spread half in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Saute onion until limp in butter.
Mix with beans, soup, sour cream and cheese.
Spread over crumbs.
Top with rest of crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: root beer
directions: Mix sugar and extract.
Dissolve yeast in small amount of water.
Add to sugar mixture.
Add 1 gallon lukewarm water and mix very well.
Store in a dark, cool place for 24 hours or longer. This can be bottled and capped after yeast has stopped working which would be longer than the 24 hours mentioned.

title: fish loaf*
directions: Mix ingredients and form loaf in an oiled loaf pan.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) until brown and firm.
Serve with desired cream sauce.
This is a recipe guaranteed to make your family fish eaters!

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix in saucepan. Stir over medium heat. Bring to rolling boil. Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and oats.
Spoon onto waxed paper to cool.

title: strawberry angel food cake
directions: Put in 8 x 8-inch pan the cut up angel food cake.
Set aside. Prepare jello mix as usual.
Cover.
Put in refrigerator until almost set, then add cut up, cleaned fresh strawberries to jello mixture.
Pour over cut up cake.
Stir a little to get mixture through cake a little.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts (optional).
Refrigerate.

title: citrus juice appetizer
directions: Mix fruit juices and chill.
Just before serving, add to chilled ginger ale.
Garnish with a few leaves of mint, if desired.

title: sour cream frosting
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese in a mixing bowl. Gradually add confectioners sugar and vanilla. Beat well.
Enjoy on favorite cakes or sweets.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Saute ground beef and onion. Drain.
Add spaghetti sauce to the meat mixture.
Prepare lasagna noodles (follow directions on package).

title: cauliflower and broccoli
directions: Spray skillet with cooking spray.
Saute mushrooms and onion. Add 1 cup of water and bring to a boil.
Pour in cauliflower; cover and cook for 5 minutes.
Stir in broccoli; cover and cook for 10 minutes.
Stir often.
Reduce heat and add 1/2 cup water, sugar and cornstarch until sauce thickens.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt, cinnamon, baking powder, soda, cloves, nutmeg and nuts together.
By hand blend in Crisco oil, eggs and pumpkin.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Cool in pan.

title: baked salmon with stuffing
directions: Melt butter in skillet and saute the chopped vegetables until translucent.
Mix vegetables with crumbs, soy sauce, thyme and pepper.
Moisten with stock or melted butter if it seems too dry. Rinse and dry fish.
Place in a well-greased baking dish or foil lined pan.
Brush inside and out with melted butter.
Sprinkle with a little salt and stuff loosely.
Bake at 450°, allowing 10 minutes per inch of thickness of the stuffed fish.
It is done when fish flakes easily with a fork at the thickest part.

title: carter peanut butter refrigerator cake
directions: Combine and bake first 3 ingredients (press into a 9 x 12-inch pan) at 350° until light brown.
Cool completely.
Combine cream cheese, powdered sugar and peanut butter.
Beat until smooth. Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread over first layer.
Mix chocolate pudding, vanilla pudding and milk together.
Beat.
Spread over second layer.
Spread on Cool Whip over third layer.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Refrigerate all day.

title: baked cucumbers
directions: Wash and peel cucumbers.
Cut crossways in half and remove seeds.
Mix bread crumbs, ham and cheese.
Moisten with tomato sauce and season.
Place cucumbers in a baking dish.
Fill with mixture.
Dissolve the bouillon cube in a cup of hot water.
Pour around the cucumbers.
Bake in 350° oven for 3 minutes.
Sprinkle on buttered bread crumbs and continue baking until brown.

title: caesar dressing
directions: Combine lemon juice, water and salad dressing mix in a jar with a tight fitting lid.
Shake 10 seconds.
Add oil and remaining ingredients.
Shake again.
Makes 1 cup.

title: meatballs gingerly spiced
directions: Combine the first seven ingredients lightly, but well.
Form into 30 meatballs, using a rounded tablespoonful for each.
In large skillet, combine ketchup and ginger ale; heat to boiling and add meatballs.
Simmer uncovered 40 to 45 minutes or until meatballs are cooked and sauce is desired consistency.
Stir occasionally.
Serve meatballs and sauce over rice or noodles. Makes 6 servings.

title: skinny soup
directions: Cook all together until it tastes like soup to you.
Adjust the seasoning to your taste.
Each cup contains 80 calories.

title: oh henry bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add syrup, oats, salt and vanilla. Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 14 minutes. Melt chocolate chips and peanut butter together.
Spread over lightly cooled mix.
Cut into bars when set.

title: smoked salmon spread
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a medium bowl; stir well. Transfer mixture to a serving bowl, cover and chill thoroughly. Sprinkle with chopped parsley before serving.
Serve spread with Melba rounds.
Yields 16 appetizer servings.

title: special coffee spice cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan. Combine shortening and sugar. Beat until well blended. Beat in eggs and molasses.
Mix well. Combine flour, baking powder, cinnamon, ginger, salt, baking soda and cloves.
Add to shortening mixture alternately with coffee. Pour into prepared pan.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pan 15 minutes. Remove from pan and cool on wire rack.
Serve with Mocha Whipped Cream.
Makes 12 servings.

title: glazed pecans
directions: Bring water and sugar to a boil in a pan.
Stir in pecans until well coated.
Cook for about 2 minutes.
Dip out pecans and spread on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 200° for about 20 minutes, stirring frequently.
Take out of oven and cool.
Store in an airtight container.

title: trifle
directions: Prepare pudding as directed.
Layer in trifle bowl as cake layer, fruit, pudding, nuts, Cool Whip and coconut.
Add second layer in same order.
Decorate top with maraschino cherries.

title: molasses muffins
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs until light and fluffy.
Add molasses and blend.
Add soda to buttermilk and set aside.
Combine flour, baking powder and spices.
Add to creamed mixture, alternating with buttermilk.
Add vanilla, nuts and raisins, if desired.
Bake in greased muffin pans at 350° about 25 minutes. Makes 18.
Good with a lemon glaze.

title: sausage and cheese quiche
directions: Mix together all of the ingredients and pour into pie shells. Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: prune spice cake
directions: Sift together first 7 ingredients; set aside.
In a large bowl mix soft shortening, sugar and eggs at high speed for 1 1/2 minutes.
Add cooked prunes; add sifted flour mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Beat on low speed, while scraping sides of bowl, only long enough to blend (2 minutes).
Pour batter into two prepared 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Ice while warm with caramel icing.

title: guacamole
directions: Peel and mash avocados.
Add remaining ingredients.
Moisten with margarine and stir well.

title: irish potato pie
directions: Put cooked potatoes through strainer.
Add butter while hot. Add sugar, salt, cream and eggs; mix thoroughly.
Add baking powder and enough milk to make a medium batter.
Season to taste with lemon juice and grated rind of lemon, lemon extract, vanilla and nutmeg.
Pour into pan lined with thin pie crust.
Makes 2 large or 3 medium pies.
Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Beat eggs, then add oil, bananas and sifted dry ingredients. Mix after adding each ingredient.
Pour into greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, then 325° for another 20 minutes until brown.
Test with toothpick.
Makes 2 loaf pans or 1 1/2 dozen cupcakes.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and nutmeg.
Beat eggs and add to dry ingredients.
Beat well;
add milk.
Stir in melted butter.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: apple butter(no sugar)
directions: Combine all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cover.
Cook on high for 1/2 hour, then turn low and leave all night or all day (6 to 8 hours).
Seal in sterilized jars.
Yields 6 pints.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil; add eggs and beat well.
Add dry ingredients, carrots and nuts.
Bake at 300°.

title: sugar plum pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients and put in a heavy saucepan and bring to a boil.
Pour over cake immediately after taking out of oven. This may be served from the pan too.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together. Pour into greased casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: double chocolate cream pie
directions: Combine pie filling mix, milk, butter or margarine and chocolate chips in saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full bubbling boil.
Remove from heat.
Cool 5 minutes, stirring twice.
Pour into shell.
Refrigerate 3 hours. Garnish with whipped topping if desired.

title: tex mex dip
directions: Peel, pit and mash avocados with lemon juice and pepper.

title: salmon souffl
directions: Make a cream sauce with the first 3 ingredients by melting butter, adding flour and slowly adding milk.
Add cheese to this and then take off burner. Add well-beaten egg yolks and salmon, crushed fine.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Put in buttered mold and bake in pan of hot water 30 to 40 minutes at 350°. When nearly done, cover with shredded almonds.

title: chicken alderette
directions: *Use fresh herbs, if possible, and double amounts.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Cut or break chicken into small pieces.
Melt butter in bottom of 9 x 11-inch dish sprayed with Pam.
Place chicken on top of butter.

title: fruit smoothie
directions: In a blender, combine frozen fruit, canned fruit and honey. Blend until smooth.

title: master mix(bisquick)
directions: Stir baking powder, milk, salt, cream of tartar and sugar into flour.
Sift together 3 times into a large bowl.
Cut in the shortening until mix is the consistency of cornmeal.
(The easiest method of mixture is flouring the hands and applying finger power.) Makes 28 cups.
Use for muffins, gingerbread, coffee cake, biscuits, pancakes/waffles (recipes follow).

title: layered strawberry-sour cream salad
directions: Dissolve boxes of Jell-O in 3 cups of boiling water.
Add boxes of strawberries and stir until thawed.
Add cans of pineapple.
Put half of the mixture in a glass dish and chill firmly. Spread sour cream over firm layer.
Pour the other half of the mixture over top of the sour cream and chill again until firm.

title: citric acid punch
directions: Mix citric acid with sugar.
Add pineapple juice and frozen orange juice; mix well.
Add up to 20 cups water.
Chill well and serve.
Can be made several days ahead.
Tastes best if frozen and served slushy.

title: lasagne
directions: Boil lasagne until tender; drain.
Brown ground beef in skillet with 1 teaspoon seasoned salt; drain.
To assemble, layer lasagne, meat and then cheese.
Keep layering until all is used. Put foil on top.
Cook in 400° oven for 45 minutes.

title: sonora breakfast casserole
directions: Spray 13 x 9-inch pan with Pam.
Line with 6 slices of bread. Top with ham, cheese, seasonings and chilies.
Beat eggs; add milk.
Add to top 6 slices of bread to pan and pour milk-egg mixture over all.
Saute cornflakes in butter and top casserole. Bake covered 30 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes more.

title: orange creamsicle cake
directions: Prepare and bake cake mix according to package directions for a 9 X 13 pan.
Poke holes in cake while still hot with the round handle of a wooden spoon.
Make Jello with only one cup of boiling water.
Pour liquid Jello over cake while hot.
Cool cake completely.
Make vanilla pudding with only one cup of milk.
Stir in vanilla and orange extracts.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spread evenly over cake.
Refrigerate cake for at least one hour before serving.

title: simply wonderful pancakes
directions: In a large bowl, combine milk, oil and eggs.
Beat well. Combine the dry ingredients, add to liquid mixture and stir just until lumps disappear.
If necessary, thicken with a little additional flour or thin with a little more milk.
Pour batter, about 1/4 cup, onto a lightly greased griddle that has been heated to 375°.
Bake until bubbles break and edges start to dry; turn and bake other side.
Serve immediately.

title: zucchini oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Beat egg, oil and both sugars until well blended. Set aside. In separate bowl, combine flour and next 4 ingredients. Stir into egg mixture. Add oatmeal, zucchini and mix well. Drop by teaspoonfuls on nonstick cookie sheet, 2-inches apart. Bake 12 minutes or until golden. Makes 2 dozen.

title: cranberry-wine mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Cool.
Add wine and cranberry sauce.
Chill
until
partly set.
Fold in remaining ingredients and place in 1 1/2-quart mold.	Chill until firm.

title: butterhorn rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Cool milk.
Add the milk, salt, sugar, egg and flour to the yeast mixture.
Mix and knead until well mixed.
Place in greased pan, covering with a towel; let rise until double in size.
Roll out in circles; brush with melted butter or margarine.
Cut in pie shaped wedges; roll up.
Brush with margarine again.
Let rise.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, or until brown.

title: mrs. fields chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugars.
Add eggs beating well after each egg.
Mix together flour, oatmeal, salt, soda, powder and add gradually to sugar mixture.
Add chocolate chips, Hershey candy and nuts.
Mix well.
Drop by tablespoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: low-fat potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Coat casserole dish with vegetable spray.
Place mixture evenly in casserole dish.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: fresh cranberry sauce
directions: In a saucepan, mix sugar and water.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Bring to a boil; add cranberries and return to boil, then reduce heat.
Boil gently 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Can be used hot or chilled.

title: snack plate dip
directions: Blend all ingredients together and mix well.
Refrigerate overnight to blend flavors.

title: danish ris a l'amande
directions: Cook the rice in the water until tender, together with the vanilla and sugar.
Stir in half the cream and the chopped almonds.
Whip the rest of the cream and fold into the mixture. Serve cold with preserved cherries.

title: green bean salad
directions: Toss vegetables and make a marinade with the vinegar, oil, sugar, salt and paprika.
Refrigerate 24 hours before serving.

title: french bread
directions: Add yeast, sugar and salt to warm water.
Mix Crisco with 1/2 the flour and all milk until mealy, then add yeast mixture.
Add rest of flour; let rise in greased pan until double.
Roll out in long rolls; brush with milk.
Let rise again, then bake at 400° for about 30 minutes.

title: baked sausage meat ring
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease lightly a 7-inch ring mold, press cornflakes onto the bottom.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix jello and hot water.
Add frozen strawberries.
This will thicken the jello.
Take half the cake and pinch into bite size pieces; add to the jello mixture.
Then mix Cool Whip with the ingredients.
Place in serving dish and chill.
Cut into squares and serve.
Top with Cool Whip if desired.

title: cheese and vegetable chowder
directions: Cook garlic and onion in butter over low heat, stirring, for 10 minutes or until onion is transparent.
Add ham and mushrooms, stirring for 3 minutes.

title: humdingers
directions: Melt dates, sugar and margarine over low heat for about 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and add Rice Krispies, pecans and vanilla.
Mix all together well.
Make into small balls and roll in powdered sugar.

title: cabbage and noodles
directions: Chop cabbage and onions into small pieces.
Saute vegetables and soup mix in butter until cabbage is soft and green in color. Set aside.
Cook noodles in boiling water until just limp (about 5 to 8 minutes).
Drain noodles and mix with cabbage.
Season to taste with seasoned salt, Accent, salt and pepper.
Simmer about half an hour.

title: cheese ball
directions: Use mixing bowl.
Heat cream cheese for 35 seconds or until melted.
Cut ham in tiny pieces and put in bowl.
Put a dash of parsley and minced onion in.
Add garlic.
Stir until mixed. Shape in a ball.

title: irish potato soup(yields 3 quarts.)
directions: Melt butter; add onions and potatoes.
Cook until thoroughly done (about 30 minutes), adding just enough water to keep from browning.
Add milk and seasonings; heat thoroughly before serving.
Do not boil.

title: country-style scalloped corn
directions: Melt butter and beat eggs.
Drain the whole kernel corn. Combine all the ingredients together, adding the muffin mix last. Pour mixture into a greased 7 x 11-inch baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 10 servings.
Prep time:
10 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar for dressing.
Toss remaining ingredients.
Add dressing and toss.
Salad is better if it sets for 4 hours in refrigerator or overnight.
Keep refrigerated.

title: cake-like brownies
directions: Melt shortening, butter and cocoa.
Add sugar and eggs.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Mix well with spoon (beater not required).

title: molded asparagus salad(serves 10 to 12)
directions: Heat soup to boiling.
Remove from heat.
Add gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Add cream cheese and blend well.
Add celery, green pepper, pecans and onions.
Blend together the water, mayonnaise and lemon juice and stir into mixture.
Pour into a mold and chill until firm.

title: raspberry sherbet angel cake
directions: Form 7 to 8 small scoops of raspberry sherbet; place on pie plate.
Cover and place in freezer until serving time.

title: turkish hamburger
directions: Put first 11 ingredients in a large bowl; work with hands to combine.
Don't overmix.
Form meat into 8 patties.
Grill or broil 3 inches from medium heat.
For rare meat, cook 8 minutes on the first side and 5 minutes after turning.
Place patty on bottom half of each roll.
Garnish with Italian sweet peppers, plum tomatoes and red onions, then top with remaining 1/2 of roll.

title: broccoli cheese squares
directions: Mix all ingredients and set aside.
Beat eggs until foamy and add to milk.
Pour milk and egg mixture, a little at a time, into dry ingredients.
Add broccoli, onion and cheese.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan greased with the margarine.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until firm in center and cheese is lightly brown.
Cool for a few minutes and cut into squares.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Cut butter into small pieces.
Add oatmeal and pour in boiling water.
Let stand for 20 minutes.
Add brown and white sugar and eggs.
Beat well.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Beat well.
Add vanilla and beat well.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sara's favorite pumpkin pie
directions: Sift flour and salt together.
Cut shortening into it with pastry blender until size of peas.
Sprinkle water in and mix it with a fork.
Form into a ball and flatten on a floured surface. Roll from center to edge until 1/2-inch thick.

title: ginger creams
directions: Cream the Crisco, sugar, egg, molasses and water.
Blend in remaining ingredients and chill.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 minutes in a 350° oven or until no imprint remains when touched lightly in the center.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil sugar, butter, cocoa and milk for 2 minutes.
Add peanut butter, oats and vanilla.
Spoon on cookie sheet and chill.

title: turkey meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and shape into a loaf.
Place in loaf pan and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: frittata(italian style omelet)
directions: In saucepan cook onion in 1 tablespoon of the oil, butter or margarine until tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vegetables or meat.
Combine eggs, salt, pepper and vegetable or meat mixture. In a 10-inch ovenproof skillet, heat the remaining oil, butter or margarine over medium-low heat.
Pour egg mixture into skillet. As eggs set, run a spatula around edge of skillet, lifting egg mixture to allow uncooked portion to flow underneath.
Continue cooking and lifting edges until mixture is almost set (surface will be moist).
The total cooking time should be about 6 minutes. Place skillet under broiler, 5 inches from heat.
Broil for 1 or 2 minutes or just until top is set.
Sprinkle with Parmesan or Romano cheese.
Loosen bottom of Frittata and slide out onto plate.
Cut into wedges.
Makes 4 to 6 side dish servings.

title: meat loaf
directions: Beat egg; add to bread crumbs.
Mix meat, onions, salt, pepper, egg and bread crumbs mixture and 1/2 cup catsup thoroughly.
Place in greased baking dish and pour remaining catsup over top.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: diabetic peanut butter delight
directions: Beat egg whites and salt until foamy. Add sugar and beat until peaks form. Fold in peanut butter. Drop 1 inch apart on greased sheet and bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: easy frozen pies
directions: Let ice cream partly melt so it can be whipped. In a large bowl whip ice cream with Cool Whip. Spoon into cookie crust and turn plastic top that came with pie crust over pie. Place pie in freezer until firm.

title: mincemeat diamonds
directions: Butter an 8-inch square baking pan.
Grate 1 1/2 teaspoons zest from lemon and squeeze 1 tablespoon juice.
Combine mincemeat, lemon juice and 1 teaspoon of the zest.
Put flour, remaining 1/2 teaspoon zest, the sugar and salt in food processor.
Pulse once or twice to mix.
Cut butter in pieces and add to processor.
Pulse until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Beat egg lightly.
Pour in egg with processor running.
Process until large crumbs form. Remove 1 1/4 cups of the crumbs and set aside.
Continue to process mixture just until dough is smooth.
Press this dough into prepared pan.
Cover dough with mincemeat.
Sprinkle with reserved crumbs. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes until edges brown.

title: veal scallopini
directions: In large saucepan, saute garlic and onion in oil until lightly browned.
Add meat; stir for 4 minutes.
Add stock; simmer over medium heat until stock is reduced.
Add tomatoes and seasonings. Cook 5 minutes.
Add peppers; cook until peppers are tender. Serves 6 to 8.

title: quick caramel frosting(makes enough for one 9 x 13-inch or two 8-inch layers)
directions: Combine first four ingredients in saucepan.
Cook, stirring, until sugar is dissolved.
Continue to cook without stirring until mixture boils.
Pour into mixer bowl and beat on high until it begins to thicken.
Add vanilla and cream.
Continue to beat.
Add confectioners sugar until of spreading consistency.
Quickly spread on cake.

title: crab meat mold
directions: Blend soup and cheese; simmer.
Add rest of ingredients; put into oiled 4 cup mold.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Beat together the eggs, butter and sugar.
Add flour, soda and cinnamon; mix well.
Combine chopped nuts with the mixture.
Make in form of 2 rolls.
Wrap each roll in wax paper.
Chill, then slice and bake at 425° for 5 to 6 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cheeses with mixer.
Pour in liquid garlic and mix more. Form into ball with hands and pat sides of ball with chili powder.

title: easy chocolate cake delux
directions: Combine well and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: shrimp with black bean sauce
directions: Rinse beans and mix with pork, garlic and ginger.
In hot wok, add oil and shrimp.
Stir-fry about 3 minutes.
Remove from pan. Add pork mixture to pan and stir-fry about 5 minutes. Add broth and heat until boiling.
Mix in shrimp and onions. Serve with rice, noodles and/or a bed of shredded nappa cabbage.

title: garbanzo dip or spread
directions: Puree garbanzos, salt and garlic in blender.
Add remaining ingredients and blend well.
(If too thick, add small amount of liquid drained from garbanzos.)
Use as dip for raw vegetables or as bagel or bread spread.

title: butter frosting
directions: Mix ingredients together; add enough milk or cream to make of spreading consistency.
Will frost a pound cake or two 8 or 9-inch layers.

title: penne with artichokes
directions: Cook artichokes in water and lemon juice until tender.
Cool; cut into quarters.
Reserve liquid.
Cook and stir the 5 garlic cloves in 1 1/2 teaspoons of oil until golden.
Reduce heat to low; add artichokes and tomatoes and simmer 1 minute.
Stir in artichoke liquid, red peppers, parsley, salt and pepper.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Cook and stir the bread crumbs and 1 tablespoon of garlic in 1/2 tablespoon of olive oil.
In a large bowl, pour the artichoke sauce over the cooked penne.
Toss to coat.
Sprinkle the bread crumb mixture and grated cheese over the top.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Peel and cut up sweet potatoes.
Cook until tender and drain and reserve 2/3 cup liquid.
Mash and set aside (need 2 cups). Combine flour, soda, salt and spices in extra large bowl and set aside, after sifting.
Combine eggs (beaten well), then sugar, sweet potatoes and reserved liquid.
Mix well and stir into flour mixture.
Mix well by hand.
Stir in pecans and raisins.
Divide dough into 3 greased 8 x 4 x 2-inch deep or 7 1/2 x 3 1/2 x 2-inch loaf pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Cover with foil the last 10 minutes to prevent overbrowning.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes, then remove onto cake racks and cool completely.
Wrap and store overnight before serving.
Makes 3 loaves.
Delicious!

title: tartar sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: cream cheese bars
directions: Melt margarine and mix with cake mix; add 1 beaten egg.
Press mixture into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese with 2 beaten eggs and gradually pour in the box of sugar.
Pour this over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Let cool and serve.

title: sour cream rolls
directions: Combine all ingredients and spoon in ungreased muffin tins. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cool whip trifle
directions: May use any seasonal fruit (peaches and blueberries are great too).

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Cut chicken into 2-inch pieces.
Mix shoyu, water, sugar, salt, garlic and ginger together (always remember that shoyu sauce is very salty).
Marinate chicken for at least 4 hours or overnight.
Roll chicken in flour and fry in hot oil, then put in oven for doneness for about 1/2 hour.
Serve either cold or hot.

title: "french fried" onion rings
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch glass dish, combine the egg and milk.
Add onion rings; toss to coat and let stand 30 minutes, turning frequently.
In a shallow bowl, combine the bread crumbs, chili powder and salt.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Spray a baking sheet with nonstick cooking spray.
Dredge onion rings in bread crumb mixture.
Place rings in pan, drizzle with oil and bake 5 minutes. Turn with spatula and bake until golden, about 5 minutes. Serves 4.

title: lemon bisque
directions: Add sugar, jello and lemon juice to hot water (boiling).
Stir until dissolved. Set aside.
Whip milk until stiff and fold in lemon mixture.
Sprinkle bottom of a 9 x 12-inch baking dish with crumbs. Save about 1/4 cup to sprinkle over top.
Pour mixture over crumbs.
Sprinkle some crumbs on top. Refrigerate until set.

title: slimmers "dip"
directions: Put all in blender or food processor until smooth.
Sprinkle with more parsley.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: lulu's brownies
directions: Beat until smooth.
This recipe has saved many, many, many mothers!
It can also be cut in half easily.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown steak in margarine.
Add garlic powder, pepper, water, vegetable juice and onions.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes or until meat is tender.
Stir in pepper and gently fold in tomatoes.
Cook 10 minutes or until peppers are tender.
Serve over hot rice. Yields 6 servings.

title: harvest stew
directions: In a large, heavy pan, brown beef in shortening.
Pour off excess fat.
Add soup, water and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover; cook over low heat about 1 1/2 hours.
Add carrots and onions. Cook 45 minutes more.
Add beans; bring to boiling, stirring to separate beans.
Cook 10 minutes more or until meat and vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally. Thicken sauce, if desired. Serve over hot noodles.
Serves 6.
Freezes well.

title: caramel fudge cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix as directed.
Pour 2 cups batter into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: strawberry glazed cheese cake
directions: Mix.
Pat firmly in bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: french-fried sweet potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes; cut into thin strips.
Fry in hot oil until crisp and brown outside and tender on inside.
Drain on paper towels. Serve hot.
Serve plain or sprinkled with salt or sugar.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch cubes.
Mix together chicken, water chestnuts and celery.
Blend together the sour cream, fat-free dressing, curry powder, soy sauce and lemon juice.
Pour over the chicken mixture.
Stir in the grapes.
Chill several hours.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In medium bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
In a small bowl, beat milk, margarine and eggs.
Stir into dry ingredients just to moisten.
Fold in blueberries and spoon batter into 12 well-greased or paper-lined muffin cups.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: 7 layer dip
directions: Mix picante and refried beans together.
Spread in 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Spread layer of sour cream, then avocado, cheese, olives, torn lettuce and then cut up tomatoes.
Cover and chill until ready to serve.

title: beef and cabbage
directions: Spread 1 can of crescent rolls in baking pan.
Brown ground beef, season and drain.
Cook cabbage and onion together, then add ground beef and cream of mushroom soup.
Pour mixture over crescent rolls, sprinkle with cheese.
Put the other can of crescent rolls on top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Set oven at 350°. Reserve 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 cup onion for the top.
Combine all ingredients and bake, covered, for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle reserved cheese and onions on the top.
Bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes until onions are golden.

title: crunchy tuna bake
directions: Combine cheeses, tuna, celery and onion.
Mix lightly.
Spoon into an 8 1/2-inch dish. Top with croutons. Combine milk and eggs. Pour over croutons.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 4.

title: pickled canned beets
directions: Drain contents of cans of sliced beets, reserving the juice. Place beets in a 32 ounce pickle or fruit jar with a wide top.

title: cranberry congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add cranberry sauce and stir to dissolve.
Add drained pineapple.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Chill overnight.

title: hurry-up skillet meal
directions: Prepare Rice-A-Roni according to package directions.
In another skillet, brown ground beef, celery and green pepper.
Add salt and pepper.
Add to Rice-A-Roni.
Continue cooking.
(May be put in a casserole and topped with grated cheese.)
Heat in 350° oven until the cheese melts.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Melt oleo and marshmallows.
Add to other ingredients.
Line a box with foil and press firmly in the box.
Store in refrigerator. Let stand 2 to 3 days before cutting.

title: chicken divan
directions: Place broccoli in baking dish.
Add chicken.
Mix remaining ingredients; add to dish.
Cover with cracker crumbs or almonds. Bake 40 minutes at 325°.

title: baked chicken a la mushroom sauce
directions: Disjoint chicken.
Dip in seasoned flour and fry in fat until golden brown.
Place in casserole.
Cook mushrooms in the same skillet about 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients; heat, then pour over chicken.
Bake, covered, until chicken is tender (1 to 1 1/2 hours) and sauce is thick.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: sure bet macaroons
directions: Soften sherbet in bowl; add cake mix and almond extract. Blend until just well mixed.
Stir in coconut.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 13 minutes.

title: hominy casserole
directions: In a large bowl combine hominy, half of the cheese (remainder to be used later), sour cream and chilies (or peppers).
Spoon into a greased 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with rest of cheese.

title: orange sherbet salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water; add sherbet and fruit.
Don't wait! The jello sets quickly.
Serves 12.

title: shipwreck casserole
directions: Slice potatoes into 4-quart casserole dish or small roaster. Slice onion on next, then add ground beef.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour on the pork and beans, add the tomato soup.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: grandma k's salad dressing
directions: Mix together the confectioners sugar, dry mustard, paprika and celery salt.
Add this mixture to the mayonnaise and stir well. Now add vinegar and salad oil.
Mix together well.
Serve on tossed salad.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and bake at 350° until firm, about 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: leta's shrimp dip
directions: Drain shrimp very well and pour into mixing bowl.
With fork, break shrimp into pieces.
Add cream cheese.
Add Italian seasonings.
Mix all very well and chill.
Serve with favorite crackers.

title: mexican cookies
directions: Beat sugar, oleo, shortening, egg and anise together.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix until smooth.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Roll dough and cut with cookie cutters.
Sprinkle with colored sugar.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 400° for 6 minutes.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Beat margarine and sugar until very well blended.
Beat in flour.
Mix in crushed potato chips.
Chill dough.
Roll into balls.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheets.
Press down with bottom of glass dipped in powdered sugar.
Bake 15 minutes at 350° just until edges are lightly browned.
Do not overbake.

title: apple cheese casserole
directions: Drain apples and place in buttered 8 x 8-inch casserole dish. Melt margarine in double boiler.
Add sugar and flour.
Add cheese and stir until mixture is creamy.
Pour mixture over apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pack into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Drain off juice before unmolding.
Serves 8 to 10.
Serve with Honey-Dijon Mustard Sauce.

title: cape cod cranberry meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine cranberry sauce and brown sugar in the bottom of a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Combine remaining ingredients, except for the bay leaves, and mix well.
Shape into a loaf and place over sauce.
Top with bay leaves and bake 1 1/4 hours.
Remove bay leaves before removing to a warmed platter. Drizzle pan juices, especially the cranberries, over the loaf before serving.
Serves 4 to 6 generously.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Arrange broccoli, top with chicken and combine soup and milk. Pour over chicken; spread cheese on top and sprinkle with 1/2 bag of Pepperidge Farm dressing mix over cheese.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes until hot.

title: strawberry fruit cake
directions: Separate whites of eggs.
Beat egg whites and add sugar gradually.
Fold in egg yolks into this mixture.
Add flour gradually, vanilla, lemon peel, lemon juice and oil.
Fold together and pour into pan.
Butter spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes until done.

title: shrimp ring
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1/2 cup cold water.
Bring soup to boil and dissolve cheese in it.
Dissolve gelatin in soup mixture and let cool.
Add celery, onion and mayonnaise.
Let firm in refrigerator for 5 minutes.
Alternate shrimp and sauce in layers in greased mold and return to refrigerator to firm.
Yields 5 cup mold.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake in loaf pan in 300° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients; blend well.

title: chicken no peek
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Pour rice into a baking dish.
Add soups. Stir until well blended.
Add enough water to make rice mixture "soupy".
Place chicken breasts over top of rice mixture. Sprinkle with gravy mixes.
Bake 1 hour or until rice is thoroughly cooked.
Check after 30 minutes to make sure mixture is not getting too dry.
If needed, add more water.

title: forget 'ems
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Beat egg whites.
Add sugar, vanilla, coconut, pecans and chocolate chips.
Stir.
Drop by teaspoon on foil lined cookie sheets.
Place in oven, turn off and forget 'em until oven cools completely.

title: b and b on rye
directions: Spread one slice of rye bread with horseradish, add roast beef and bacon.
Spread small amount of light
mayonnaise on second slice of rye.

title: almond joy cake(makes two 9 x 13 cakes)
directions: Make according to box directions.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients.
Add rest of the ingredients. Chill overnight.
Roll out.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
I like a soft cookie, so I roll them out 1/4-inch thick.

title: oven fried chicken or pork chops with zing
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place mustard in a dish large enough to fit your biggest piece of chicken into.
Place bread crumbs on a plate.
Dip chicken into mustard covering both sides.
Coat with bread crumbs on both sides.
Place into baking dish, repeat with all pieces.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: easy amaretto cake
directions: Sprinkle 1 cup almonds into bottom of a well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan; set aside.
Combine next 7 ingredients in a mixing bowl; beat at low speed until dry ingredients are moistened.
Increase speed to medium; beat 4 minutes.
Stir in remaining 1/2 cup almonds.
Pour batter into tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool cake in pan 10 to 15 minutes; remove and cool completely.

title: icy pink punch
directions: Mix lemonade packages and concentrate, sugar and water; add pineapple, apple and grape juice to mixture. Pour mixture in gallon freezer Ziploc bags and freeze. When you use, add 1 large bottle ginger ale to each bag.

title: german potato salad
directions: Add flour to bacon drippings.
Stir until thick paste is formed.
Mix the remainder of ingredients and add to paste. Simmer until thick.
Add potatoes and onion.
Serve warm.
May make ahead and reheat before serving.

title: chocolate cookie sheet cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cinnamon and salt in bowl. In saucepan, mix margarine, cocoa and water and bring to boil. Remove from heat. Pour over flour mixture; mix well. Dissolve soda in buttermilk; add to first mixture. Add eggs and vanilla. Pour in 12 x 18 cookie sheet pan and bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Five minutes before done, make Frosting.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Break vermicelli into pieces.
Cook al dente and drain (approximately 5 minutes).
Saute mushrooms in sherry and margarine.
Bone and skin chicken; cut into large pieces.
Combine all ingredients except cheese; sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake in a flat, shallow dish at 300° for 35 minutes.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Soak gelatin in cold water.
Mix brown sugar, spices and salt in top of a double boiler.
Stir in the pumpkin.
Beat egg yolks and blend in the milk.
Add to the pumpkin mixture.
Place over boiling water.
Cook until thick (about 10 minutes), stirring often. Remove from the fire.
Add soaked gelatin, blending well. Cool until it begins to set.
Beat with a rotary eggbeater.
Make stiff meringue by beating egg whites with 1/4 teaspoon cream of tartar until stiff, gradually adding 6 tablespoons white sugar. Fold meringue into the pumpkin mixture.
Pile into baked pie shell and chill in refrigerator.

title: old-fashioned apple stack cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour together with dry ingredients.
Beat eggs and sugar together with the butter.
Mix all together to form cookie-like dough.
Prepare 8 or 9-inch pans by greasing and lining with wax paper.
Sprinkle with flour.
Pat a thin layer of dough into pans and bake until brown and crisp, about 12 minutes.
Repeat procedure until all layers are baked.
Spread apple butter, applesauce or dried apples between each layer, on top and sides.

title: candied rolls
directions: Chop cherries, pineapple and nuts.
Crush vanilla wafers, then mix all together with milk.
Make logs and roll in powdered sugar.

title: sensational double layer no bake pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar with a wire whisk until smooth.
Fold in whipping cream.
Spread on bottom of graham crust.
Pour 1 cup milk and pudding mix into bowl.
Beat with whisk until well blended.
Let stand 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread over cream cheese mixture. Refrigerate 2 hours.
Garnish with additional whipping cream and nuts as desired.

title: gumdrop applesauce cake
directions: Sift 2 cups flour over chopped gumdrops, raisins, and nuts; set aside.

title: crispy chocolate bars
directions: Melt chips and peanut butter over very low heat until smooth. Add cereal and mix together in large mixing bowl.
Spread into 13 x 9-inch pan which has been greased.
Cool at room temperature for 10 minutes, until cutting time!

title: cabbage dinner
directions: Chop steak into squares.
Fry in pan with a little oil.
While meat is cooking, chop up cabbage and cook in oil on low heat.
When meat is done, add to cabbage.
Use meat juice and water to make a simmering sauce.
Cover.
Cook about 30 minutes.
Stir often.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with rice and crackers.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all filling ingredients together. Pour into pie shell.
Bake 1 hour.
Tastes like pecan pie.

title: banana nut muffins(makes 18)
directions: Cream sugar and shortening until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Stir in mashed bananas.
Add dry ingredients and stir just enough to moisten.
Do not overbeat.
Batter will be lumpy.
Add nuts.
Fill greased 3-inch muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: oven fried herb chicken
directions: Combine salad dressing mix, flour and salt in bowl.
Blend in butter and lemon juice.
Spread mixture evenly over top of chicken.
Place skin-side up in shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until tender.
Yields 4 servings.

title: ham casserole
directions: Place first seven ingredients in baking dish; mix lemon juice, cream and soup and pour over the mixture.
Top with bread crumbs and butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: empanadas
directions: Dissolve yeast in water; set aside.
Cut shortening into dry ingredients.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Knead until dough is satiny and smooth.
Do not let rise.
Roll dough out 1/4 to 1/8-inch thick and cut with biscuit cutter or large round cookie cutter.
Place filling in center of dough; fold dough in half and seal edge with fork tines or by pinching to give ruffled effect and fry in hot fat until golden brown.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar, if desired, when cool.
Makes 2 dozen little pies.

title: skillet corn bread
directions: Mix all parts together; batter should be medium thick, no lumps.
If mixture is too thick, add cold water.
Grease a large cast-iron skillet; place in a 400° oven until smoke appears. Remove skillet; wait 5 minutes.
Pour mixture into hot skillet; place in oven for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Bread should be served hot with sweet butter.
Left over cornbread should be saved for later use in cornbread stuffing.
If Pastor does not give you a double Amen for this bread, you have done something wrong. Amen.
Serves 8.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix with fork or beater.
Layer in buttered oblong dish.

title: mississippi nut cake
directions: Crush graham crackers.
Put marshmallows and milk into saucepan.
Heat on low heat, stirring constantly, until dissolved. Do not cook, only dissolve marshmallows.
Add remaining ingredients and mix with hands.

title: sunday potatoes
directions: Layer potatoes, onion and pepper in casserole dish.
Pour soup over top evenly.
Cover and bake 2 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Grease dish or baking pan.
Mix all ingredients together and place in greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: sugarless cookies
directions: Boil raisins with apples in water for 3 minutes.
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Refrigerate for 3 to 4 hours, then drop by tablespoons on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: easy fruit dip
directions: Cream cheese should be room temperature. Blend until smooth. Chill and serve when ready.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Mix together flour, margarine and nuts.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix together cream cheese, Cool Whip and powdered sugar and spread on top of crust.
Beat the instant lemon pudding and the rest of the Cool Whip together and spread on top.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: cream cheese pie crust
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Cut in cream cheese and butter with pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Form into a ball and chill.
Divide dough into 2 sections.
Roll on lightly floured board.
Put in pie pans and trim; prick with a fork the bottom.
Bake at 450° just long enough to brown.
Don't brown if using this pie shell for my Pumpkin or Cantaloupe Pie.

title: whipping cream pound cake
directions: Sift flour and salt together.
Cream shortening and sugar in mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour mixture alternately with whipping cream, beating well after each addition.
Stir in flavorings.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool in pan for several minutes.
Invert onto serving plate.
Spread frosting over cooled cake.
Yield:
16 servings.

title: bagel bites
directions: Split Bagels to give you 20.
Mix mayonnaise and parmesan, add peppers, bacon bits, onions and tuna.
Spread about 2 Tbsp. on each bagel half and put onto ungreased cookie sheet with sides, so the bagels don't slide off.
then top each bagel with an olive slice.
Broil for about 5 minutes or until cheese is golden brown.

title: texas pralines
directions: Use a large pot, the candy needs lots of room to bubble.
Pour the buttermilk, sugar and baking soda into the pot.
Stir the mixture until the sugar is completely dissolved, then place the pot on low to medium heat and let it boil to a soft ball stage, stirring constantly.
(Soft ball means dipping a spoon into the candy and letting a small amount drip into cool water.
If you can form the syrup into a soft ball with your fingers, it is ready.) The mixture will turn a brownish color, but don't worry, it is supposed to.
Once the soft ball stage is reached, remove from heat, then add 2 cups of pecan halves, then the vanilla and butter. Beat the mixture briskly until it becomes glossy and starts to get very thick.
Quickly spoon onto greased wax paper, making little patties.
Pecan halves may be turned right side up.
Let the candy completely cool before removing it from the paper.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Layer ground beef (raw) in 2-quart baking dish.
Put salt, pepper and onion (sliced into thin rings) over beef.
Pour soup over top and spread. Add cheese and Tater Tots last.
Bake in oven for 25 or 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese apples
directions: Layer apples into Pyrex dish.
Spread the remainder of the ingredients on top.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 325° to 350° oven.

title: sugar-free pumpkin pie
directions: Pour milk into 2-quart saucepan.
Stir in pudding and pumpkin pie spice until dissolved.
Add pumpkin and blend until well combined.
Heat mixture on medium heat until it boils.
Gently cook 1 minute and stir to prevent burning.
Pour into cooled crust and chill.

title: spicy cabbage
directions: Place all ingredients in skillet.
Cover and cook 15 minutes until tender.

title: stuffed ham(southern maryland)
directions: Cover with water and precook corned ham about 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Shred cabbage, onions and kale in pot. Add seasonings and cook until tender. Save liquid for final cooking.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add one egg at a time, then add vanilla and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, then at 325° for about 30 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and bananas.
Add sifted dry ingredients; mix well.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: In a shallow bowl, mix cornmeal and flour.
Dredge both sides of tomato in the mixture, pressing the slices firmly into the mixture for a good coating.
Put enough oil or shortening in an iron skillet to come to a depth of about 1/4-inch and heat over medium-high heat.
Add tomatoes to the hot oil a few at a time without crowding.
Fry about 2 minutes or until golden brown. Turn and cook other side.
Drain on paper towels.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve hot.

title: cheese and broccoli soup
directions: Bring water to boil in a 3-quart Dutch oven and add broccoli and onion.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes. Add cheese and seasonings, stirring until cheese melts.
Stir in milk, half and half and butter.
Cook over low heat until thoroughly heated.
Combine flour and 1/2 cup cold water, stirring until smooth.
Gradually add to broccoli mixture, stirring constantly.
Cook over heat until thickened.
Yields 2 1/2 quarts.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Put tater tots in bottom of 9 x 9 -
inch pan.
Mix all the ingredients together but green beans and cheese.
Pour all ingredients in pan and top with green beans, then cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hot crabmeat dip
directions: Combine ingredients in a double boiler and heat until dip consistency. Make 1 hour before serving.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by spoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: zucchini frittata
directions: *May substitute plain Feta cheese plus 1 teaspoon sun-dried tomato bits and 1 teaspoon snipped fresh basil.

title: bread pudding
directions: Sprinkle nutmeg and cinnamon on top 6 slices of bread to taste. Pour mixture over top and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Combine white sauce, sour cream, onions, chicken stock and salt.
Blend in spinach.
Cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes if doubling.

title: sour cream biscuits
directions: Melt butter.
Mix with other ingredients.
Spray muffin tin with Pam.
Drop in dough.
Fill 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° until light brown.
Makes a dozen.

title: zucchini "crab" cakes
directions: In mixing bowl, combine grated zucchini, beaten egg and melted butter.
Add seasoned crumbs, minced onion and Old Bay seasoning; mix well.
Shape into patties.
Heat oil in frying pan.
Roll patties in flour or cracker crumbs.
Fry until golden brown on all sides; drain on absorbent paper.

title: texas hash
directions: Saute onion and pepper in oil, then add meat, rice, salt, pepper and chili powder.
Cook in a covered casserole at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: erwtensoep or dutch pea soup
directions: Mix all ingredients in a saucepan.
Warm the mixture thoroughly over medium heat.

title: pie crust mix
directions: Mix thoroughly with pastry blender.
Package in plastic sacks and refrigerate.
Lasts indefinitely.
Makes 22 to 25 single crusts.
For 1 crust use 1 cup mix and 2 tablespoons cold water.

title: cheese pineapple ball
directions: Grate or mash all the cheeses and mix them together in a large bowl.
Add the melted butter, lime juice, sherry and seasonings (except paprika).

title: flora raper's candied yams
directions: Cook potatoes until done.
Pour cold water over them to cool. Peel and cut in desired servings.
In a large glass dish, place potatoes.
Put a good amount of white sugar over potatoes (no water).
Let stand overnight.
When ready to bake, cover with brown sugar.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and a few drops of vanilla.
Add water if needed.
Bake at 350°.

title: swiss steak
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper; pound into steak. Place in skillet with shortening and brown; pour off grease. Add rest of ingredients and cover. Simmer 1 hour and 15 minutes or until tender, stirring often.

title: mexican style drumsticks
directions: Melt margarine.
Stir in taco mix, picante sauce, sugar and salt.
Roll each drumstick in mixture, then roll in chips using a small amount of chips at a time.
Place in a lightly greased shallow baking pan or on a rack in a shallow pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.
Also delicious with other chicken pieces.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms, pour boiling water over them and drain.
Mix marinade.

title: cheese soup
directions: Combine water, carrots, potatoes and onion.
Bring to a boil. Cook 10 to 15 minutes; do not drain.
Melt margarine; add flour. Stir in milk.
Add cheese.
Mix with vegetables.

title: country bean soup
directions: Soak beans in water overnight.
Drain.
Add fresh water and cook slowly with the ham bone for 2 hours.
Put in the onion, celery, potatoes, tomato sauce, parsley and the salt and pepper and simmer until vegetables are soft.
Remove the ham bone.
Trim off any meat.
Cut it up and add to soup.
Many cooks cut up hard-boiled eggs and add them to the soup.

title: sour cream devil's food cake
directions: Sift flour once, measure, add soda and salt and sift together 3 times.
Cream butter and sugar thoroughly; then chocolate, vanilla and egg; blend well.
Add flour and milk in small amounts and beat until smooth after each addition.
Bake in 2 greased 9-inch layer pans in moderate oven at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Spread with Deluxe Icing.

title: marinara sauce for pasta
directions: In a large saucepan, heat olive oil over medium heat.
Add garlic and saute for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add parsley and onion slowly.
Add tomatoes.
Add bay leaf, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil. Cover and simmer sauce over low heat for about 15 minutes for flavors to blend.
Serve sauce with spaghetti or other pasta dishes or with rice.

title: turtle brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a foil-lined 13 X 9 inch baking pan. Microwave chocolate squares & butter in microwavable bowl on HIGH 2 minutes or until butter is melted.
Stir well until chocolate is completely melted.
Stir sugar into chocolate until well blended. Mix in eggs.
Stir in flour.
Spread 1/2 batter in prepared pan. Bake 20-25 minutes or until batter is firm to touch.
Meanwhile, melt caramels & cream in microwaveable bowl on HIGH 3 minutes or until caramels begin to melt.
Whisk until smooth.
Stir in one cup of nuts.
Gently spread caramel mixture over brownie batter in pan. Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Pour remaining unbaked brownie batter evenly over caramel mixture; sprinkle with remaining nuts. (Some caramel mixture may peek through.)

title: ziti alfredo with vegetables
directions: In a large pot, cook pasta according to package directions. In a small saucepan, saute onions and garlic in olive oil till browned.
In a large saucepan, melt butter, add flour and stir. Slowly, add half-and-half and milk and simmer, stirring constantly, till thickened.
Add cheese and seasonings; stir till cheese melts.
Add tomatoes, spinach and onion mixture; heat through.
Pour over warm pasta, toss and serve.
Leftovers can be refrigerated and reheated in the microwave.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix as follows: In heavy saucepan, combine milk, sugar, salt and butter. Bring to boil over moderate heat. Boil 8 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and add peanut butter morsels. Stir well until morsels melt and mixture is smooth. Spread into a foil-lined 9-inch square pan. Chill 30 minutes.

title: brunch express
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add diced onion, bell pepper and mushrooms. Simmer for a few minutes.
Dice peeled potatoes and fry.
Then add fried potatoes to meat mixture and stir together.
Soften tortillas; then roll meat mixture in tortillas.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix together the graham crackers and 1 stick of butter. Spread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream the powdered sugar, 2 sticks butter and eggs; spread over crust.
Lay pineapple and bananas over filling.
Top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate 1 hour before serving.

title: cajun catfish stew
directions: Fry onions, cabbage and garlic in oil in a large pot.
Add all but fish and simmer, covered, 25 minutes.
Add fish and cook 10 minutes more or until all ingredients are tender.

title: the merchants crab cakes
directions: Mix first eight ingredients.
Form into 4 cakes; dredge in flour and dip in egg wash, then bread crumbs.
Deep fry 3 minutes or until browned.

title: cheesecake tarts
directions: Beat cream cheese, eggs and sugar.
Place vanilla wafer in paper baking cup and add a tablespoon of batter on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool and put a teaspoon of cherries on top.

title: spinach balls
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts; freeze before serving.
Put on cooking sheet still frozen.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: corned beef oven omelet
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs, milk and seasoned salt.
Tear corned beef into small pieces and add to egg mixture.
Stir in cheese and onions.
Pour into greased baking dish (11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inches or 8 x 8 x 2-inches).
Bake, uncovered, for 40 to 45 minutes, or until omelet is set and top is golden brown.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in 3/4 stick butter.
Add all other ingredients; stir well.
Top with 1/2 cup cheese, crushed potato chips and slivered almonds (optional).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: bacon and garlic saute
directions: Melt 1 tablespoon butter over moderate heat.
Add the bacon; saute until crisp, about 3 to 5 minutes.
Drain.
Add the remaining butter, garlic and parsley.
When the butter is melted, saute garlic and parsley for about 1 minute more.
This is great over cooked pasta or boiled, diced potatoes.

title: german chocolate icing
directions: Cook in double boiler until thick enough to spread.

title: potato and green bean salad
directions: Mix oil, vinegar and salt.
Place potatoes in bowl with beans and chopped egg.
Pour dressing over, mixing with care to avoid mashing potatoes.
Stir in or sprinkle with parsley and serve either hot or cold.

title: berry sauce(heart healthy)
directions: Clean and wash berries. Save a few berries for garnish. Puree remainder in blender or food processor. Strain seeds, if desired. Place in saucepan over medium-low heat and allow to reduce in volume by half (about 1 hour). If mixture is still too thin, add a tablespoon cornstarch mixed with 1 teaspoon water to thicken.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and slice thinly to measure about 4 cups.
Cook and stir in onions in margarine in 2-quart saucepan until tender. Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in milk and 1 1/2 cups of cheese (about 6 ounces).
Heat to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.

title: chocolate pinwheels
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar slowly.
Add egg yolk and vanilla extract.
Beat well.
Add milk; add sifted dry ingredients.
Divide dough in half.
Add melted chocolate to one half.
Roll white dough into thin rectangular sheet, then roll chocolate dough into a sheet the same size.
Place white dough over chocolate and gently press together.
Roll as for jelly roll into a tight roll.
Chill for several hours to become very firm. Cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Put on greased baking sheet.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 10 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Note:
One cup of applesauce may be substituted for oil for low-fat bread.

title: potato peanut butter roll candy
directions: In a large bowl, combine sugar, potatoes, butter and vanilla; mix well.
Will be very thick, like play dough.
Place between 2 pieces of waxed paper and roll out into a 9 x 14-inch rectangle. Spread peanut butter evenly across.
Gently roll up.
Wrap in waxed paper; chill.
Chill 2 hours; cut into 1/2-inch slices to serve.

title: bread
directions: To the scalded milk add the sugar in a large bowl.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add the yeast and stir well to dissolve.
Add eggs and melted shortening.
Slowly stir in the flour and salt.
Let rise at room temperature for 2 hours.

title: pickled mushrooms
directions: Add salt to water; wash mushrooms in this and drain.
Combine all remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Add mushrooms; boil up once, lower heat and simmer mushrooms covered for 10 minutes or until just tender.
Cool and chill for at least 2 hours in own juice.
Drain before serving.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cook pineapple, flour and sugar until thickened, stirring constantly.
Stir in margarine.
Let cool.
Peel and chop apples. Drop in salt water.
Drain and rinse well.
(Dry apples on paper towels.)
Add to pineapple mixture.
Top with Cool Whip, chopped nuts and cherries.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chunky broccoli soup
directions: In medium pan, combine white sauce mix, chicken broth and water.
Add broccoli, carrot and onion.
Bring to boil over high heat, stirring often.
Reduce heat to low and simmer 10 to 12 minutes, stirring often until vegetables are tender.
Stir in milk and pepper.
Simmer 2 minutes or until heated through.
Serves 4.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions; drain.
In a small skillet, saute the onion, green pepper and celery in 2 tablespoons butter until tender.
Transfer to a large bowl.
Add the soup, mushrooms, spaghetti, chicken and cheese; toss to coat.

title: 1-2-3 meat loaf
directions: Mixing with wet hands, shape into 4 individual loaves.
Place in a shallow ungreased baking pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: honey-lime barbecued chicken
directions: Soak overnight.
Barbecue over medium heat for 40 minutes. Start with skinless side down.
Turn 3 times; baste often.

title: bean dip
directions: Fry hamburger meat and onion together.
Drain grease.
Add seasoning mix, sour cream, refried beans and taco sauce.
Mix together and put in large baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: tavern nut crunch
directions: In a large bowl, toss together the peanuts, Rice, Wheat and Bran Chex cereal and raisins.
Melt margarine in saucepan. Stir in honey, vanilla and cinnamon until well blended.
Pour syrup over nut-cereal mixture and toss to coat all pieces well.
Spread mixture on a large, ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Turn off oven and leave in oven for another 10 minutes. Store in an airtight container.

title: buckwheat pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients well in large bowl.
Cook on hot griddle.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Roll cookie dough onto a pizza pan or cookie sheet and bake until brown.
While cookie is cooling, mix together cream cheese and sugar well, then add in Cool Whip.
Spread mixture on top of cookie.
Cut into 2-inch squares and add a small piece of sliced fruit onto each square.

title: chocolate dreams
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease baking sheets and set aside.

title: taco bean dip platter
directions: Spread beans evenly on bottom of a cookie sheet.
Mix together sour cream and taco mix and layer on top of beans.
Add onions, then the olives and tomatoes.
Cover generously with grated cheese.
Serve with chips.
Great for parties!

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and enjoy with apple slices of your choice.
Granny Smith's work well!

title: layered mild taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and mayonnaise and pour into serving dish to form bottom layer; then pour salsa over.
Layer next 5 ingredients, finishing with tomatoes.
Cover and chill at least 8 hours; serve with large taco chips or crackers.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In a small saucepan saute onion and margarine until onion is tender.
Mix green beans, soup, onion and margarine and 1/2 cup of cheese in 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top and then cover with fried onions.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruited chicken
directions: Chop prunes and soak in water for 1 hour. In large skillet, heat butter & oil; add chicken and brown 5-10 minutes on all sides. Arrange chicken in shallow baking dish. Add onions to skillet and saute' 5 minutes. Stir in garlic, tomatoes, salt & pepper, and nutmeg. Simmer 5 minutes. Pour over chicken and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Pour prune mixture over chicken and bake until chicken is tender. Serves six.

title: apple bread pudding
directions: In buttered 1-quart baking dish, soak bread in milk.
Combine eggs, sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Stir into bread mixture.
Place apple slices over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until almost set in center.

title: ava's huckleberry dessert
directions: Combine flour, nuts and margarine.
Press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 325°.
Cool.

title: spinach casserole(hot!)
directions: Cook spinach.
Drain.
Reserve liquid.
In skillet, melt margarine, add flour and onion; cook until soft.
Add liquids. Cook until thick.
Add seasonings and cheese.
Melt cheese. Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until bubbly (can be made ahead).

title: pasta and chicken salad
directions: Use the quantity of each that is to your taste to make a salad to feed 5 to 8 people.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown ground beef and add rest of ingredients, except rice. Blend together and bring to a boil.
Add rice.
Remove from heat and let stand for 5 minutes.

title: rotini salad
directions: Cook, drain and cool noodles.
Add other ingredients and toss together with Italian dressing.

title: aunt betty's mandarin cake
directions: Beat together until spreading consistency.
Frost cool cake. Sprinkle with nuts and coconut.

title: carne asada(marinade)
directions: Blend jalapenos and juice or water in blender.
Add lemon or lime juice and soy sauce and garlic powder.
Blend well.
Add beer and stir.
Marinate steak 24 hours and grill.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix lettuce, onion, tomatoes and beans together.
Add meat, grated cheese, Doritos and salad dressing just before serving.

title: lemon rice(serves 4)
directions: Heat the broth and garlic in heavy saucepan to boiling.
Stir in the rice; cover and simmer until liquid is absorbed (about 20 minutes).
Remove from heat.
Stir in lemon zest and let stand covered for five minutes.
Remove garlic clove.
Gently stir in dill and butter.
Season to taste with pepper.
Serve.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, with mixer at medium speed, beat all ingredients until well mixed, scraping bowl.
Drop by teaspoonfuls, 1 inch apart, on sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Immediately remove cookies to wire racks; cool.

title: meat and potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes and carrots until tender; drain.
Brown meat, then pepper and onions; drain.
Mix milk, margarine and flour. Bring to a boil to make a thin sauce, then layer potatoes and carrots in baking dish with meat.
Add sauce and bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: stephenson's apple crisp
directions: Place apples in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix and sprinkle/toss with apples the white sugar, salt, cinnamon and 2 tablespoons flour.

title: quince cobbler
directions: Cut quince in quarters, core and peel.
Cover with water and boil in covered pan until tender.
Place fruit juice in covered jar and refrigerate until needed.
Pinch 3/4 of one slice of bread into 1-inch pieces to cover bottom of small baking dish.
Pour quince pieces and some juice on top of bread.
Sprinkle raisins over quince and bread.
Make another layer of bread.
Place small pieces of margarine over top and sprinkle brown sugar on top.
Add juice to within 1-inch of top of mixture.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for about 20 to 30 minutes or until top is brown and juice is thickened.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Brown ground beef and drain. Add onion soup mix, mushroom soup, chicken broth and 1 cup water. Simmer for about 25 minutes. Mix the meat mixture with crumbled cornbread. Put into 9 x 13 baking dish in the oven for about 20 minutes at 350°.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Boil chicken and shred into bite-sized pieces.
Layer on bottom of long rectangular casserole dish.
Mix cream of mushroom soup, cream of celery soup and sour cream.
Pour on top of chicken.
Sprinkle crushed Ritz crackers.
Melt butter and pour on top of crackers.
Sprinkle with poppy seed.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon luscious
directions: Mix flour, butter and pecans as a biscuit dough and spread in rectangle baking dish.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.

title: tuna chow mein
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chelsea's potato candy
directions: Boil one small potato.
Peel and mash in mixing bowl.
Add powdered sugar until able to be rolled flat.
After rolled flat, spread with peanut butter.
Roll up like jelly roll.
Wrap wax paper around roll and put in refrigerator to let chill.
Slice and serve.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix together everything, but the cheese.
Pour half of the mixture in a well-greased, hot skillet (iron pan is best). Sprinkle 1/2 cheese on top of this mixture.
Pour rest of combined mix on top of this and then sprinkle rest of cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine flour, cinnamon, salt and soda; set aside.
Combine oil, eggs and sugar; mix well with electric mixer on medium speed. Add dry ingredients slowly, stirring until all are moist.
Stir in nuts and strawberries.
Put in 2 greased and floured 8 x 4 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour until pick comes out clean.
Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Remove on wire rack.

title: grandma's potato soup
directions: Fry bacon until very crisp.
Remove bacon from large pot. Pour off some of the fat, but reserve a large portion to saute chopped onion.
Add balance of ingredients except reserved bacon. Bring to a boil, then turn way down and simmer 1/2 hour.
Add crushed, crisp bacon and simmer another 45 minutes to 1 hour. Take a potato masher and run it through the soup to break up some of the chunks.
Serve with fresh rye or pumpernickel bread and butter.
Hearty winter meal.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: turkey or chicken chop suey
directions: Cook onion and celery in oil about 5 minutes in electric frypan.
Add next 3 ingredients and 1 1/2 or 2 cups hot water. Bring to a boil and simmer 5 minutes.
Add 2 tablespoons soy sauce.
Blend cornstarch and 1/4 cup water.
Add to mixture and cook, stirring until thickened.
Season with salt and pepper and serve on rice with additional soy sauce.
Serves 4.

title: chili
directions: Brown first 4 ingredients until tender.
In large pot, mix all ingredients and simmer for 1 hour.

title: rice krispie treats on a stick
directions: You will need 12 wooden popsicle sticks.

title: old fashioned stuffed cabbage
directions: Shred remaining cabbage.
Boil 10 minutes in small amount of water.
Drain and cool.
Mix together the cracker crumbs, eggs, milk, flour, salt and pepper.
Stir until well blended; add to cooked cabbage.
Shape 6 cabbage leaves inside a white cloth.
Fill with a combined cooked cabbage and egg and cracker mixture.
Tie cloth at top so mixture will hold its shape and resemble a cabbage head.
Fill a pot 2/3 full of water and put cloth containing cabbage leaves filled with mixture in it and boil 20 to 25 minutes. Untie cloth and turn upside down on platter.
Pour browned butter over top and serve.
This takes a little time but is very good.

title: strawberry-banana salad
directions: Take the juice of the pineapple and berries and add enough water to make 1 1/2 cups. Bring to a boil and mix with other ingredients. Put half of the mixture in the refrigerator until it jells. Spread sour cream over it and add other half of mixture. Return to the refrigerator to let fully congeal.

title: baked pineapple stuffing
directions: Mix pineapple, sugar, flour and eggs; put in a greased casserole.
Melt margarine in skillet, add bread cubes and brown lightly.
Place cubes on top of pineapple mixture and brown lightly.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken or seafood dipping sauce
directions: Bring first four ingredients to boil.
Stir in Jack Daniels and simmer 5 minutes.
Cool and refrigerate.

title: squash hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Drop by spoonfuls in deep oil until floats on top and browns on both sides.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken until meat pulls away from ends of leg bones or until done.
Cool and take meat off bones, pulling into chunks or bite size pieces.
Using a 2 or 3-quart casserole dish, layer chicken on bottom.
Partially cook broccoli and layer on top of chicken.
Slice hard-boiled eggs and place on top of broccoli (optional).
In separate bowl, mix together the sour cream, soups, salt and pepper.
Spread over the top of casserole.
Top with cheese.
Refrigerate until ready to bake.
Best if made the day before and baked the next day.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes (or until bubbly).
Serve over cooked rice.
Yields 5 to 6 servings.
Also good with asparagus instead of broccoli.

title: sugar-free cookies
directions: Friends must be cared for and tended, not put on the back burner.
Shower them with love letters, phone calls, gifts and compliments.
Contacts need to be regular.

title: baked alaska
directions: Grease and flour 9-inch pan.
Sift flour with sugar, baking powder and salt into mixing bowl.
Add shortening and milk.
Beat 1 1/2 minutes at low speed with mixer or 225 strokes with a spoon. Add egg and vanilla extract.
Beat 1 1/2 minutes more.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, until cake springs back when lightly touched in center.

title: broccoli casserole (2)
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bread crumbs or crushed potato chips, and put into buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs or potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cut into squares.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream the shortening, sugar, butter, peanut butter and eggs thoroughly.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Heat oven to 375°.
Roll dough into balls the size of walnuts.
Place 3-inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet. Flatten and crisscross with fork dipped in flour.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add applesauce.
Gradually stir in flour and other dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add vanilla.
Add raisins that have been coated with a little of the flour.
Grease and flour 2 (8-inch) cake pans.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Invert and leave pans over cake until perfectly cold before handling.
Frost with White Icing.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except cookies.
Layer pudding mixture and Oreos ending with Oreo cookies.
Use a new, clean flower pot with artificial flowers or use vanilla sandwich cookies instead of Oreo and put in a clean pail with shovel (looks like beach sand).

title: dilled onion rings
directions: Thinly slice onion and separate into rings.
Place in small bowl or pack into 2-cup jar.
Combine sugar, salt, dill weed, vinegar and water in small pan.

title: bacon twists
