directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Unroll dough carefully into 4 rectangles.
Do not separate into triangles.
On a floured surface, roll out each rectangle to 9 x 4-inches.
Cut each rectangle lengthwise into 3 strips.
Stretch bacon into 9-inch strips.
Twist each piece of bacon with a strip of dough.
Place twists on a baking sheet.
Brush with beaten egg.
Bake for 15 minutes or until dough is golden.
Cool slightly and then serve warm.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Cook cornbread per package directions.
Cool.
Crumble into a large bowl.
Add 1 chopped green pepper, chopped onion, mayonnaise, tomatoes and season to taste.
Chill and serve.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottoms only of two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Mix sugar and shortening in a 2 1/2-quart bowl.
Stir in zucchini, water and eggs.
Mix in flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, cloves, vanilla and baking powder.
Stir in nuts and raisins (or pineapple).
Pour into pans.
Bake until a wooden pick comes out clean when inserted in center, 60 to 70 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.

title: triple chocolate brownies
directions: Cook pudding with 2 cups milk as per instructions on package. Add pudding and applesauce (for moistness) to cake mix and beat for 3 minutes or until smooth.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on the top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Test done with toothpick.
Do not overbake!
May sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: marshmallow fudge
directions: Put first three ingredients in large heavy pan and bring to a boil until soft ball stage.
Remove from fire and add marshmallow cream, nuts, vanilla and chips.
Stir until chocolate melts. Pour into a buttered pan.
Cut in squares when cool.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Separate eggs and beat whites until stiff.
Set aside.
Cream margarine and shortening and add sugar.
Add egg yolks, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk; add alternately with flour.
Beat well.
Add coconut, nuts and extracts.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.

title: everything cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine ingredients as listed.	Drop by teaspoonful on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cookies will be crunchy.

title: sweet potato and jalapeno pepper soup
directions: Melt butter in large casserole dish.
Add onion.
Cook (stirring until brown) approximately 5 minutes.
Reduce heat to moderate-low and cover.
Cook until soft, then stir in sweet potatoes and chicken broth.
Bring to boil.
Lower heat and simmer, partially covered, approximately 25 minutes.
Next strain soup.
Reserve solid and liquid separately.
Put solid in blender and puree.
Whisk puree into a liquid and return to casserole. Stir in jalapeno pepper and corn.
Cook 5 minutes until pepper is crisp and tender.
Whisk in cream, juice and grated rind.
Season with salt and pepper.
Gently heat.
Serve with individual dollops of sour cream and parsley; enjoy.

title: honey bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add milk, salt, honey and shortening.
Beat in 1/2 of flour.
Mix well.
Gradually add remaining flour.
Let raise until double.
Make 2 loaves or sweet rolls.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mash squash.
Mix all ingredients together and blend well. Pour into a buttered dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until set.

title: cream cheese coffee cake with preserves
directions: Cut cream cheese and butter into Bisquick until crumbly. Blend in 1/3 cup milk.
Turn onto floured board.
Knead 8 to 10 strokes.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Cook rice as usual.
Set aside.
Blend spices with butter in skillet, add shrimp and cook.
Put rice in casserole, add shrimp and broth, bake 25 minutes at 350°.
May add other spices- Cajun type.
Delicious!
12 oz. spaghetti, cooked and 8 oz. cubed Velveeta cheese may be substituted for rice.

title: tomatoes and okra
directions: Fry
bacon
until
crisp;
drain and reserve drippings. Cook okra
in bacon drippings. Add green peppers and onions to okra. Stir in tomatoes and cooked bacon; add salt and pepper. Cover skillet and cook about 15 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: antipasto bean salad
directions: Combine beans, dressing and seasonings; toss gently.
Cover and refrigerate until chilled.
Place marinated beans in large salad bowl.
Arrange fresh vegetables around sides of the bowl and garnish with fresh parsley.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: english nut cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, butter and salt.
Add the well beaten eggs and milk.
Mix with a wooden spoon.
Add raisins and pecans.
Add lemon extract last and mix well.
Grease and flour a loaf pan.
Add batter mixture and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Beat cake mix, jello, eggs, water and flour two minutes at medium speed.
Add strawberries.
Beat 1 minute more.
Add oil and beat one more minute.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes in two round or square 9-inch pans.
Can also be made in 9 x 13-inch pan. Let set 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: mile high strawberry pie
directions: Put first 5 ingredients into large bowl.
Beat at high speed for a full 15 minutes.
The mixture should come to the top of the bowl.
Beat cream and vanilla, fold into mixture.
Put in baked pie shell.
Put in the freezer until ready to serve.

title: peach pie
directions: Combine milk, lemon juice, peaches and Cool Whip.
Pour into pie crust and chill.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Place Twinkies in bottom of 9 x 12-inch dish.
Prepare pudding mix.
Spread pudding over Twinkies.
Layer bananas, pineapple and strawberries (with juice).
Top with Cool Whip.
Chill until serving time.

title: bush buns
directions: Brown beef and onion together.
Add remaining ingredients, except hot roll mix and Crisco.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer about 20 to 30 minutes.
Mix roll mix according to package directions. Divide dough into 24 equal parts (small balls).
Flatten each dough ball and place 1 spoonful of mixture in center.
Form dough around meat mixture, sealing seams so juice stays inside.
Allow dough to rise again.
Deep-fry in hot Crisco at 360° for about 5 minutes or until golden brown.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Best when eaten immediately, but also good to warm up leftovers in microwave.

title: mini pumpkin cheesecakes
directions: Mix crumb mixture as directed on package.
Press onto bottoms of 12 paper-lined muffin cups.
Beat milk, filling mix, pumpkin and spice with electric mixer on low speed until blended.
Beat on medium speed 3 minutes.
Filling will be thick.
Spoon over crumb mixture.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour or until ready to serve. Garnish as desired.
Makes 12.

title: apple betty granola crisp
directions: Peel apples; slice into buttered glass pie plate.
Drizzle orange juice over apples.
Make topping by mixing the remaining ingredients together until mealy.
Sprinkle on top of apples. Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes or until apples are soft.
Makes 6 servings.

title: ham fried rice
directions: Combine eggs and water in a small bowl.
Cover with heavy-duty plastic wrap and microwave on High for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until eggs are set, stirring after 1 minute.
Chop eggs and set aside.

title: frank's chili without beans
directions: Brown hamburger; cook with onions.
Add remaining ingredients; cook 1 1/2 hours.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until thick.
Add corn syrup, pecans and vanilla.
Pour into 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: krista's country tomato and alphabet soup
directions: Brown beef; remove fat.
Add water and simmer 20 minutes. Stir in tomatoes, bouillon and spices.
Simmer for one hour.
Add vegetables and alphabet soup; cook for 30 minutes.

title: extra good brownies
directions: Prepare brownie mix as directed and put in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Beat in bowl the cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Add egg and mix.
Pour creamed mixture over brownie mix and swirl with knife. Sprinkle top with chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: almond bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat (dry) cake mix, margarine and eggs on low speed until dough forms.
Press into ungreased jelly roll pan (15 x 10 x 1-inch).
Bake until golden brown and crust begins to pull away from sides of pan or until toothpick comes out clean, 20 to 25 minutes.

title: date nut muffins
directions: Cream together sugar and oleo, adding eggs last.
Combine flour, salt, nuts and chopped dates.
Mix soda with boiling water and let stand for 5 minutes.
Combine all three mixtures.
Bake in greased muffin tins.
Makes 24 muffins.
You may also add bananas.

title: strawberry cream pie
directions: Crush strawberries and add sugar.
Let mixture stand for a half hour.
Soak gelatin in 3 tablespoons water.
Dissolve this in 3 tablespoons of boiling water.
Stir gelatin into strawberries and cool.
When softly set, lightly fold in whipped cream and pour into pie shell.

title: old world dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: grandmother's apple pie
directions: Combine apples and water in large saucepan; bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes, until apples are tender. Drain well.
Return to saucepan and mash slightly with potato masher.
Stir in sugar, allspice and salt.

title: country homemade ice cream
directions: Add sugar gradually to beaten eggs, beating well after each addition.
When mixture becomes very stiff, add other ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Freeze in gallon ice cream freezer.

title: barbecue country style ribs
directions: Boil ribs 10 minutes.
Remove and place in crock-pot.
Pour in barbecue sauce and add 1 cup water.
Do not make too watery. Season with salt and pepper.
Cook on low heat for 6 to 8 hours.

title: classic green bean bake
directions: Microwave Oven:
In 1 1/2-quart microwave-safe casserole, combine soup, milk, soy sauce and pepper.
Stir in beans and 1/2 of the onions.
Cover; microwave on High for 7 minutes or until hot, stirring once during cooking.
Sprinkle with remaining onions.
Microwave, uncovered, on High for 1 minute.
Makes 6 servings.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix together and pour in a glass dish.

title: beef stir-fry
directions: Cut beef steak lengthwise into 1/8-inch strips.
Combine soy sauce, 2 teaspoons oil, sugar and cornstarch.
Stir into strips. Heat remaining 2 teaspoons oil in large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add garlic, ginger and pepper pods; cook 30 seconds.
Add bell pepper and corn; stir-fry
1 1/2 minutes.
Makes four servings.

title: meatballs with spinach
directions: Mix all ingredients well; make one-inch balls and drop into hot tomato sauce.
Simmer about 2 hours.

title: best ever brownies
directions: Cut a square of wax paper to line a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Preheat the oven to 350°.
Melt the chocolate and butter and set aside.
Beat the eggs, gradually add the sugar until well blended. Add salt and vanilla, then add the flour and nuts and finally the chocolate mixture.
Pour into pan immediately and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Test with a toothpick.
Remove from the pan and peel off the wax paper. Cool completely before cutting into desired size.

title: crustless zucchini quiche
directions: Beat eggs; add zucchini, onion, oil, Bisquick mix, cheese and spices.
Mix until well blended.
Pour into buttered 12-inch pie plate or oblong dish.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: shortcut fondue dip
directions: Combine soup, cheese, Worcestershire, lemon juice and chives. Cover and heat in slow cooking pot for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Stir until smooth.
Keep hot in pot and dip celery, cauliflower and corn chips.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Cut chicken into serving pieces.
Spray a 6 x 12-inch casserole dish with Pam.
Put rice in dish.
Sprinkle dry onion soup over rice; add water.
Place chicken in single layer, skin side up, on top of rice.
Spoon celery soup, saving 1/2 can for heating over. Bake, uncovered, at 350°.

title: colorful pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta as directed.
Drain.
Pour about 1 cup of the salad dressing over the pasta and refrigerate.
Once cool, add the vegetables and more dressing to taste.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: so easy pecan bars
directions: Combine all the ingredients except powdered sugar and blend well.
Pour into Pam sprayed or greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool thoroughly before slicing.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Turn your oven to 375°.
In the small pan, melt butter.
While it's hot, add both sugars; stir, then let cool a bit.
While the butter mixture is cooling, mix the flour, soda and salt in the mixing bowl.
In small bowl, beat egg lightly.
Add egg and vanilla to butter.
Add butter, egg and vanilla to flour.
Stir. Add chocolate chips and nuts if you want them.
Stir well; refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Roll dough into walnut size balls. Place on cookie sheet; bake 12 minutes.

title: sweet and sour pork chops
directions: Brown chops in oil; transfer to baking dish.
Discard all but 2 tablespoons of oil and meat drippings.
Lightly saute onion and garlic.
Sprinkle cornstarch over this.
Add everything else but almonds.
Simmer, covered, for 5 minutes.
Pour mixture over chops.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Sprinkle almonds on top.
Bake, covered, another 1/2 hour.

title: hawaiian chicken salad
directions: Serve on lettuce leaf, garnished with paprika.
Serves 6.

title: stephanie's spinach quiche
directions: Defrost
spinach.
Set aside.
Beat eggs and soup.
Add mushrooms and cream; mix.
Dice onion and garlic.
Add spinach and salt.
Combine all ingredients.
Turn into shell and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: fruit salad mix
directions: Combine and bring to boil; let cool.
Pour over fruit: apples, bananas, oranges, grapes, pears, maraschino cherries and chopped nuts.
Top with cherries.

title: ham and pasta skillet
directions: In 10-inch skillet, combine soup, milk and mustard.
Over medium heat, heat to boiling.
Stir in broccoli.
Return to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and cook for 5 minutes or until broccoli is tender.
Stir in macaroni and ham.
Heat through, stirring occasionally.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Mix ingredients together. Bake in 9 x 13 pan at 350° until done. Test with toothpick.

title: turtle cake
directions: Pour half of cake batter in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
While cake is baking, mix caramels, milk and butter.
Heat just until melted.
Pour caramel mixture over the baked half of cake.
Sprinkle on nuts and chocolate chips.
Then pour the second half of batter on.
Bake for 20 minutes more.

title: strawberry figs
directions: Mash up figs.
Add sugar and jello.
Cook until thick.
Pour up in jars.

title: party potatoes
directions: Mix all together.
If too stiff, add milk.
Put in casserole and brush top with melted butter.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hamburger cheese casserole
directions: Brown the ground beef.
Pour off fat.
Add garlic salt, salt, sugar and pepper.
Cook until well blended and add tomato sauce. Simmer for 15 minutes.
Soften the cream cheese and mix with the sour cream and sliced onions.
Cook noodles as directed on package and drain.

title: macaroni and cheese pie
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Beat eggs.
Add canned milk.
When you drain macaroni, add oleo and let melt.
Slice cheese.
Add macaroni and butter to egg mixture, then place layer of cheese.
Push down to bottom of dish, then top with another layer.
Bake at 450° until lightly browned.
Bake in an 8 x 8-inch dish.

title: pineapple nut cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oranges and oil together.
Mix well.
Add eggs one at a time.
Fold in nuts and bake in three round pans, greased and floured.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 325°.
Cool 10 minutes. Then turn upside down on racks.
Cool completely.
Mix together Cool Whip, pudding and pineapple (with juice).
Frost cakes with mixture.

title: jiffy goober haystacks
directions: Melt peanut butter and butterscotch morsels together in heavy saucepan over low heat.
Stir in noodles and peanuts until all ingredients are well moistened.

title: raw broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Bake in unbaked pie shell at 400° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 50 minutes.
This makes 7 cups of filling, so it will yield 3 small pies or 2 large ones.
Can also bake as a pudding!

title: honeyed carrots
directions: Combine the carrots, water, orange juice, lemon zest, butter, salt, ginger and honey in a saucepan.
Place over low heat.
Cover and cook about 20 minutes or until carrots are tender.
Serves 4.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water to cover 30 minutes or until tender.
Drain and cool slightly.
Peel potatoes; cut into 1/2-inch cubes.
Cook bacon in a skillet until crisp.
Remove bacon, reserving 1/4 cup drippings in skillet.
Crumble bacon and set aside.
Add sugar, flour, water and vinegar to pan drippings, stirring well.
Cook mixture over medium heat until slightly thickened.
Combine potatoes, bacon, green pepper, onion, celery and pimiento in a large bowl.
Top with vinegar mixture and toss gently.
Serve hot.
Makes 6 servings.
(You may serve the peppers, onion and celery raw or cooked with salad.)

title: chicken thighs casserole
directions: Cook chicken thighs in butter until brown.
Set aside.
Cook rice. Combine soups and bring to a boil.
Grease 9 x 12 pan.
Put in rice and chicken.
Cover with soup mix.
Sprinkle with Heinz 57 sauce. Cover with sliced Velveeta.
Bake at 350° until cheese turns light brown, about 30 minutes.

title: slow cooker beef stroganoff
directions: Put all ingredients except wine, flour and sour cream in slow cooker.
Cook low, 6 to 8 hours.
Turn to high; add wine. Dissolve flour in water and stir until well blended.
Cook on high for 15 minutes until thickened.
Stir in sour cream and heat thoroughly.
Serve over noodles.
Serves 4.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into bite-sized pieces.
This should take about 4 months.
Cook over kerosene fire for approximately 4 weeks or until tender.
Add onions, cook until tender.
This will feed about 3,000 hungry hikers.
If more are expected, add the 2 rabbits.
But do this only if necessary, as most people don't like hare in their stew.

title: ham and macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions on package and drain. Combine with other ingredients.
Toss and chill.

title: candy
directions: Melt almond bark in microwave, then add peanut butter; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper.
Yields 50.

title: greenwood farm salad dressing
directions: Combine ingredients in large glass container and shake well. Store in refrigerator. Let sit several hours to combine flavors before serving.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Mix sugar and powdered milk. Add butter and water; mix until smooth. Refrigerate. Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: play putty
directions: Combine.
Stir vigorously with a spoon until it becomes stiff, then knead it with your fingers, mixing all the glue bubbles.
Keep in airtight container to retain suppleness.
If left in open air, it will melt and then turn hard.
If putty dries out, dip it in water and knead.

title: venison burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into thick patties.
Grill in oven or on grill for 10 minutes.

title: hot matzie
directions: Combine all the ingredients.
Spread on party rye or small pita bread and broil until bubbly.

title: grape-nuts
directions: Add soda to milk before you add to dry ingredients.
Put in pans and bake at 350° until done.
Grate when still warm and dry on low heat in oven.

title: smackers
directions: Beat egg white	to a peak;
add flour, sugar and vanilla. Fold pecans

Coat

Spread

Cook 30 minutes. Turn heat off and leave in oven for 30 minutes with heat off.

title: tuna cheese twist
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease a cookie sheet.
Mix the tuna, celery, green pepper, onion and 1/2 cup soup.
Set aside.
In another bowl, mix the Bisquick, 1/2 cup cold water until soft dough forms.
Gently smooth dough into a ball.
Knead 5 times. Roll dough into rectangle (14 x 11-inch approximately) and place on cookie sheet.
Spoon tuna mixture lengthwise on dough and sprinkle with 1 cup cheese.
Make or cut strips along edges that are 2 1/3 inches long and 1-inch wide.
Fold them alternately over top of mixture for a braided or lattice-work effect.
Mix egg and 1 tablespoon of water.
Brush over top of dough.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes, until lightly browned.

title: chicken breasts in cream sauce
directions: Season chicken breasts with paprika, salt and pepper.
Bake, covered, in an oven preheated to 350° for 35 minutes.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in a pan.
Add the flour and stir well.
Cook for a couple of minutes; don't brown.
Add hot chicken stock and continue stirring until smooth.
Set aside.

title: pork fried rice
directions: Heat wok or skillet.
Add oil; fry half of the onion and garlic until garlic turns slightly brown.
Add pork; cook until done or 5 minutes, then add rice to the meat.
Stir thoroughly until mixed and heated through.
Push rice to side of the wok or skillet.
Pour in egg mixture.
Add salt and pepper in the center (if desired).
Scramble eggs until set; mix with rice and sprinkle soy sauce over the rice.
Raise heat for 1 minute; remove.
Add rest of the onion; mix thoroughly.
Serve hot.

title: cocoa nuggets
directions: In a medium bowl, combine flour, 1/2 cup cocoa and salt; set aside.
In a large mixer bowl (at medium speed), cream the butter and granulated sugar.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Gradually add dry ingredients and vanilla; beat until well blended.
Stir in nuts.
Wrap and chill dough for at least 1 hour.

title: rhubarb cream pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425° and place rack in lower part of oven. Mix 2/3 cup sugar with flour.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons over bottom of pie shell.

title: ritz cracker dessert
directions: Set aside 1/2 cup cracker crumbs for top.
Mix cracker crumbs and melted butter together and spread flat in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix all other ingredients together and pour over the crumb mix.
Keep refrigerated.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup of crumbs on top and serve.

title: nana's cheese ball
directions: Put Cheddar cheese through food grinder, using finest blade. Soften and whip cream cheese.
Put cashews through grinder; same blade.
Mix all ingredients except paprika.
Shape into a roll or ball.
Then roll in lots of paprika or parsley.
The roll should be really red or green on the outside.
Wrap in wax paper and refrigerate.
This keeps well in your refrigerator.

title: oven meat balls
directions: Meat Balls:
Mix first 6 ingredients.
Shape in balls.
Place on baking sheet 20 to 30 minutes in oven at 350°.

title: rhubarb shortcake
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, sugar, and margarine.
Cut in shortening as for pie crust.
Place egg in 1 cup measuring cup. Add milk to make 1 cup, add vanilla.
Stir until well blended. Spread in prepared pan.
Add rhubarb.
Spread over short cake. Sprinkle jello on top of rhubarb.
Combine sugar and flour in bowl.
Cut in margarine and sprinkle on top of the above.
Bake 375° or 350° for glass pan for 40 minutes.

title: peach cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, eggs, soda, cinnamon and peaches.
Bake 350 degrees until done.
For topping cook rest of ingredients until thick and pour on cake.

title: apple shelly pie
directions: Put apples in a 13 x 9-inch pan, heaping up in the middle. Mix all dry ingredients and butter until crumbly.
Pour on top of apples.
Sprinkle with orange juice.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 45 to 50 minutes or until done.

title: kart-wheels
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix flour, butter, powdered sugar and just enough milk until dough forms (if dough seems dry, add more milk, 1 teaspoon at a time).
Divide the dough into 6 equal parts.
Shape each part into a ball.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten slightly.
Make an indentation 1 3/4-inch in diameter and 3/4 inch deep in the center of each.
Fill each indentation with approximately 2 tablespoons of pie filling.
Bake until the edges begin to brown, 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 6 Kart-Wheels.

title: collard greens(makes 6 servings; prep time: 1 hour)
directions: Place the hock in a pot with cold water to cover.
Add the red pepper flakes; put on the lid.
Bring to a boil; reduce the heat and simmer until tender, 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Add more water if necessary.
When the hock is done, add the greens and remaining ingredients to the pot.
Lower the heat and simmer until tender, which is usually about 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Stir occasionally during this time.
Season to taste and serve with extra vinegar and hot sauce on the side and a little chopped onions.

title: microwave bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix all ingredients together and microwave on High power 7 minutes.
Put in containers and store in refrigerator.

title: caramel oatmeal chewies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Combine oats, flour, brown sugar, soda and salt; mix well.
Stir in butter.
Blend well.
Remove 1 cup; set aside.
Press remaining onto bottom of pan.
Bake for 10 minutes; cool 10 minutes.
Top with nuts and chocolate chips.

title: company best pickles(mother's recipe)
directions: Cover whole cucumbers with boiling water; let stand overnight. Drain.
Repeat 3 more mornings.
On the fifth day, drain and slice in 1/4-inch pieces.
Combine sugar and spices, salt and vinegar; bring to a boil and pour over cucumbers.
Let stand 2 days.
On the third day, bring to a boil and seal in sterilized jars.

title: old fashion buttermilk pie
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add flour and eggs. Beat well. Stir in buttermilk, vanilla and nutmeg.
Pour in pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: seafood mousse
directions: Heat the soup in a medium saucepan until warm. Remove from heat and stir in gelatin.
In a large bowl, beat the cream cheese until soft and smooth.
Add the soup mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in the celery, onion, mayonnaise, Tabasco, shrimp and crabmeat.
Pour into two 4 1/2 cup molds
that have been sprayed with cooking spray.
Chill for about 3 hours or until set.
Unmold and serve with assorted crackers.

title: spiced peach salad
directions: Drain syrup from peaches and bring to boil.
Add dissolved gelatin.
Mash peaches; add to gelatin.
Mix cheese and nuts. Form into small balls; add to gelatin.
Chill.

title: low-fat fruit shake
directions: Blend all in blender until mixed.
Chill, shake and drink.
You may use any blend of fruit.
Juice is to flavor.

title: applesauce cookies(diabetic)
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: baby ruth cookies
directions: In a small bowl, sift together the flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In large bowl, with electric mixer at medium speed, beat margarine or butter blend and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Stir in chopped candy and dry ingredients until well blended.
Chill dough 30 minutes.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes, or until golden brown.
Remove from baking sheets; cool on wire racks.

title: golden potato cakes
directions: Combine potatoes, flour, milk, egg and onion in a bowl; mix well.
Drop by tablespoon into hot oil. Brown on both sides, pressing with spatula to flatten.
Makes 12 cakes.

title: magic pumpkin pie
directions: In a large mixing bowl, blend all ingredients.
Turn mixture into pie shell and bake at 375° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Refrigerate 1 hour before serving.

title: father's breakfast
directions: Combine Cap'n Crunch with milk in a Smurf bowl.
Take a Mickey Mouse spoon to stir coffee, then eat cereal.
Take coffee and donuts along while you watch Saturday morning cartoons on T.V. with the kids.
Yields 1/2 serving (kids got the other half).

title: tex-mex crispix mix
directions: Combine taco seasoning mix and spices; set aside.
In a 2-gallon storage bag, combine Crispix cereal, corn chips and toasted onion.
Pour oil over cereal mixture, tossing gently to coat.
Add taco seasoning mixture to bag, tossing gently until cereal mixture is thoroughly coated.
Store in airtight container.

title: fast and easy cookies
directions: Heat oven
to
In
large bowl, combine cake mix, egg, oil
and
water;
mix well and add remaining ingredients. Drop by tablespoons
onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes. Remove immediately.

title: wilted waldorf salad
directions: In a 10 to 12-inch skillet, heat nuts until light brown; remove from pan and set aside.
Peel apple and chop into small cubes.
Put in bowl and add sugar and 4 tablespoons of vinegar; stir and set aside.
Add oil, onion, garlic and caraway seed to frying pan.
Heat until onion is limp, stirring.
Add cabbage and remaining 2 tablespoons of vinegar.
Stir until cabbage is wilted, about 2 or 3 minutes.
Pour cabbage mixture in bowl.
Top with apple mixture and nuts.
Mix and salt to taste.
Serves about 6.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Blend thoroughly and roll out.
Bake as necessary for pie you will be making.

title: cheeseburger loaves
directions: Crush cereal and other ingredients.
Shape into loaves and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Add cheese to top.

title: hearty beef 'n beans
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.

title: blackened redfish
directions: Combine onion powder, garlic powder, white pepper, red pepper, black pepper, dried thyme and salt.
Heat 12-inch iron skillet or heavy aluminum skillet.
Brush fish with seasoning mixture.
Add fish to unoiled skillet.
Drizzle a little butter over each fillet. Cook, uncovered, over high heat for 2 to 3 minutes.
Turn.
Drizzle with butter and cook 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until fish flakes with a fork.
Serves 4.

title: hungry jack appetizers
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters.
Place in baking dish.
Spread lightly with margarine.
Sprinkle with finely chopped onion and green pepper.
Cover with shredded Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350°.

title: grammy clem's crazy cake
directions: Combine all dry ingredients in 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan. When well mixed, make 3 holes in the mix and add one of liquid ingredients to each hole.
Pour 1 cup water over all and mix with a fork until smooth.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Double everything for a 9 x 13 x 2-inch cake.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients.
Add beaten egg.
Melt shortening and add to ingredients.
Stir in milk.
Fold in floured berries. Fill greased tins 2/3 full and bake 15 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cube bread and place in baking dish.
Saute sausage, drain and spread evenly over bread.
Spread cheese evenly over sausage. Mix eggs and milk together and pour evenly over cheese.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: spicy pecan pork
directions: Slice pork loin crosswise into 4 equal slices.
Place meat between two sheets of plastic wrap; pound with flat side of a meat mallet to 1/4-inch thickness.
In shallow bowl, combine egg, egg white, mustard and red pepper.
In another bowl, combine bread and pecans.
Coat pork in flour; dip slices one at a time in egg mixture, then coat with bread and pecan mixture.
In a 12-inch skillet, heat oil to medium to medium-high heat.
Add pork; cook uncovered 6 to 8 minutes or until tender and just slightly pink, turning once.
Add fresh hot peppers.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients together and shape into a loaf.
Top with a thin layer of ketchup.
Put water in baking pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: mayo-parmesan bread
directions: In a small mixing bowl, combine Parmesan cheese and mayonnaise. Stir in parsley (if desired), set aside.
Place bread slices on the rack of an unheated oven.
Broil about 1 minute or until the bread is toasted.
Turn bread over.
Put mix on the untoasted side of the toast.
Broil for 2 to 3 minutes or until light brown.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Boil zucchini and onion in water for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Mix soup and sour cream, then add carrots, then zucchini and onion. Mix butter and stuffing mix with a fork.
Place half of the Stove Top mix in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Then add vegetable filling. Top with remaining Stove Top mix.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: cranberry-apple salad
directions: Melt cranberry sauce over medium heat.
Drain, reserving liquid and berries. Mix together cranberry liquid, boiling water and gelatin.
Stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Add lemon juice and salt.
Chill until mixture mounds slightly on a spoon.
Add real mayonnaise; beat until smooth.
Fold in cranberries, apple and nuts.
Pour into a 2-quart mold.
Chill overnight.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Brown sausage.
Drain. Roll off 4 triangles of crescent roll. Pinch dotted line to form 1 long sheet.
Spread cream cheese. Sprinkle with sausage and roll up jelly roll style in wax paper. Chill 1 hour or overnight.
Do same to remaining 4 triangles. When ready to serve, slice in pinwheels and bake until brown by directions on crescent roll can.

title: beaver dams
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels over hot water.
Stir in peanut butter.
Take off heat and add noodles and marshmallows.
Spoon on wax paper and put in refrigerator.

title: baked apricots
directions: Drain apricots well.
Layer apricots in buttered 8 x 12-inch Pyrex.
Crumble sugar over apricots.
Coarsely crumble Ritz crackers over that (2/3 box of Ritz crackers).
Pour melted margarine over all.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni slightly short of package directions (if macaroni is cooked too long before adding ingredients, it wil be sticky when cheese is melted).
Drain and add other ingredients. Cook at medium heat until cheese is melted.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Thaw hash browns and add soup, sour cream and cheese.
Melt oleo, crunch corn flakes into oleo and add salt and pepper. Spread corn flakes mixture over potato mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: chinese hamburger
directions: Brown hamburger until slightly crumbly.
Add remaining ingredients, except noodles, with 1 1/2 cups water.
Bake, covered, 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 45 minutes.
Serve over noodles.
Bake at 350°.

title: baked lima beans
directions: Combine beans with garlic salt in large saucepan.
Add enough water to cover.
Let stand overnight; drain.
Fry bacon in skillet until crisp.
Remove bacon to paper towels to drain.
Crumble. Add soup and brown sugar to bacon drippings in saucepan; mix well. Stir in onion, salt and pepper.
Combine soup mixture and bacon with lima beans in baking dish.
Bake at 300° for 3 to 4 hours or until beans are tender, stirring occasionally.
May simmer on stove top if preferred.
Yield:
10 servings.

title: lemon meringue tarts or pies
directions: Bake two 8-inch pie shells or 16 small tart shells.
Cool.
Mix 1 1/4 cups sugar, cornstarch and salt in saucepan.
Add boiling water and lemon rind.
Cook over direct heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Continue cooking for about 20 minutes.
Remove from heat and add butter.
Pour mixture over egg yolks and lemon juice which have been mixed together.
Beat until smooth and well blended.
Return to heat and allow to become steaming hot again, stirring to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat.
Fill baked shells and bake at 400° for 5 minutes, no more.
Remove from oven and cover with meringue made from egg whites and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes until delicately brown.

title: my best pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line 9-inch pan with pastry and chill while fixing the filling.
Beat eggs lightly.
Stir in butter, sugars, syrups, vanilla, salt and pecans.
Pour into prepared shell.
Bake 45 minutes or until done.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar, oleo, milk and cocoa in saucepan.
Boil hard 1 minute, stirring.
Remove from stove.
Add oats, peanut butter and maple flavoring.
Mix well and drop onto wax paper.
Place in freezer for a few minutes to harden.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: In a saucepan, melt the butter; stir in flour, salt and pepper until blended.
Add chicken broth, stirring over medium heat until mixture thickens.
Add the milk and stir until smooth.
Pour into a blender the cream and 5 broccoli spears.
Blend until smooth. Add to the cooked mixture.
Chop the remaining broccoli and add to the soup.
Simmer for 5 minutes and serve.
Serves 6.

title: layered mexican dip
directions: On a large platter, spread the ingredients, decreasing the circumference of each layer.
Sour cream and dry Ranch dressing should be mixed together.
Chill.
Serve with tortilla chips. (Fat-free sour cream, refried beans and Guiltless gourmet tortilla chips may be substituted.)

title: velveeta cheese twirls
directions: Roll process cheese spread between 2 pieces of wax paper to form 9 x 12-inch rectangle.
Beat cream cheese, olives and cilantro until well blended.
Spread over process cheese spread. Roll up, starting at narrow side to form 9-inch roll.
Garnish with additional cilantro, if desired.
Chill, covered, until firm.
Serve with assorted crackers.
Makes approximately 36 appetizers.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add taco seasoning. Using large bowl, layer ingredients.
Start with lettuce and with cheese.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix milk, sugar and pudding together; beat for approximately 3 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip.
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, layer bottom crackers, then pudding, then crackers.
Then layer again pudding and crackers.
Last layer would be graham crackers.
Refrigerate for 3 hours, at least.
Top with frosting and serve.

title: crunchy pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill.
Line punch bowl with Boston lettuce.
Garnish with crisp-cooked, crumbled bacon.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients well.

title: george's meat loaf
directions: Break bread into pieces.
Crush crackers.
Combine bread, crackers, egg and milk.
Beat with mixer until blended.
Add meat, onion, vinegar, sage and salt.
Put into pan; form into a loaf. Combine brown sugar and catsup.
Brush over top of meat loaf. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cracker salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except crackers.
Chill.
When ready to serve, stir crushed crackers in.

title: wttf cranberry salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and boil 10 minutes.
Add soda, sugar and Jell-O.
Stir until dissolved.
Add marshmallows.
Cool and add remaining ingredients.

title: never fail egg custard
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar, flavoring, flour, milk and beaten egg yolks.
Mix well.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: corn light bread
directions: Sift together first 3 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix all well with electric mixer.
Bake in a loaf pan that has been sprayed well with Pam.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: our favorite bean salad
directions: Drain and mix together the green beans, wax beans, kidney beans and garbanzo beans.
Mix together white sugar, salad oil, tarragon vinegar, celery seed, salt, pepper, garlic, onion and green pepper. Add bean mixture and let stand at least overnight to obtain best flavor.
Keeps well.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Melt stick of butter in bottom of Dutch oven and then cool. Mix remaining ingredients, except fruit, in a bowl.
Pour this batter over melted butter in the oven.
Do not stir.
Pour fruit on top.
Do not stir.
Bake in Dutch oven until golden brown.

title: hortense's rolls
directions: Mix the milk, 2/3 cup sugar, shortening and salt and heat to lukewarm.
Let cool.
Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water and 1/2 teaspoon of sugar.
When cool, mix yeast, egg and flour with soda, baking powder and salt already added.
Let rise, then make out rolls.
Let rise again.
Bake at 375°.

title: string beans oregano
directions: Cook string beans until tender.
Drain and set aside.
In a frying pan, saute garlic in the olive oil.
Add bread crumbs and mix together.
Add beans and mix together.
Put in a casserole, then sprinkle on Parmesan cheese.
Mix in pats of butter.
Heat in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix and put in large pan.
